text: A trinket we shall place with the other baubles in the vaults at Couronne.
It is no Grail… but you have our gratitude.
The worth of such a gift could feed the smallfolk of an entire dukedom for months… we shall place it in the vault.
I prayed to the Lady for an answer and she deemed it wise.
The Grail Knights gather - a sign we should accept.
I saw a vision of Gilles le Breton, he told me to agree to this.
This is no surprise, yours is a people of no honour.
Fine. There is no treaty when such foul deeds are abroad!
Bretonnia will deal with you no longer!
We do not accept this! Bretonnia's honour is worth far more.
You offend the Lady with this rejection.
Fine! Bretonnia weeps at your refusal.
The Green Knight comes to my dreams with sword drawn.
The Knights sally forth. We are prepared for you!
So be it. We have the Lady's protection!
Our chivalric code cannot be compromised, this treaty is over!
The treaty is done, due to your unchivalrous actions!
We must void this treaty, the Fey commands it.
Surely your honour is at stake, you must fight with us!
Join us, and this day will be a red day for our enemy indeed!
Now is the time to fulfil the chivalric code and join us in battle!
A debt must be paid, the Royarch demands it!
You owe our Lady - pay up, my lord.
We do not mean to besmirch your honour, but the debt accrued to Bretonnia is due.
You defile the name of Gilles the Uniter with this display of arrogance!
You are not worthy of mantle, Knight, yet we must discuss the matter at hand.
We are all dukes and lords, we will find common ground.
I have seen the way you treat your smallfolk - far too lenient for my liking. Still, there are matters to attend.
Come, my lord, we must talk, the Lady deigns it.
We must come together, my lord, let us speak on how best to serve the Lady.
Bretonnia will never be yours, Northmen. Come, parley and we will tell you why!
We will purge your filth from our holy lands, but first a meeting!
There is an offer for you, minion of Chaos, but your fell masters won't like it.
We make our demands in good faith, Northman, are your Gods even capable of the same?
Should you leave the shores of Bretonnia unmolested, then perhaps an offer can be made.
We make no pacts with the Chaos Gods - willingly - but perhaps, my Lady sees an opportunity for an offer to be made?
Yet again, the Dwarfs look down upon us from the Grey Mountains with faces of scorn. Now it is our turn to look down upon them - we demand an audience.
You have little time Dwarf, meet our demands.
Will the Dwarfs consider an audience, or are they too busy counting coin in their deepest vaults?
We have an offer, if only the Dwarfs deem an ally worth listening to.
The Dwarfs are an honourable race, will they hear us out?
Many a battle has been fought with Dwarf and Knight as one - will you hear us now?
Trouble comes to Bretonnia and, of course, the Empire remains deaf to our pleas for a simple audience.
A curse on Sigmar and his unchivalrous sons - we are Bretonnia and demand you hear us!
Does the new Emperor forsake Bretonnia? Or will he hear us out?
This is no border skirmish around Axe Bite Pass, we have a proposal.
We humbly suggest that the Prince of Altdorf and his allies take note of this offer.
Will Sigmar's envoys hear the ambassadors of the Lady?
Ugh! I wish nothing more to send your wretched hide back to the Massif Orcal, but first we must talk.
We have a proposal, hear us out, Orc-scum, and then you may try and duel me with that crude weapon of yours.
Come, Greenskins, it is hoped you have your uses than merely a thing to spit on our lances?
We have an offer for you, do you even understand the concept, Orc?
The Lady's protection on us, but I make an offer and wonder if you even have a mind worthy of accepting it?
Do the Orcs not want for anything other than blood? Maybe this offer will change your mind?
The Royal Decree is pronounced - hear it and quail!
Hear us! Your honour demands it!
If you do not offer an audience then the Fey Enchantress shall hear of it!
We have an offer, blessed by the Lady herself.
A simple audience is requested, surely you will not sully your honour by refusing to grant us that.
We have a small request, the risks are minimal to you.
Our proud Knights salute you, will you give us the same courtesy?
The laws of chivalry state that our hospitality is yours…
We offer greetings, and that your will hear our offer.
Make no mistake, liche, we despise all your Unliving kind… but the Lady wishes you to know of an offer…
Vile breathless corpse-fodder! I sully my honour just being near you! Still I must make this demand upon your master.
We wish no repeat of La Maisontaal Abbey… let us be quick and strike a deal.
Creature of Mousillon, hear our offer and be gone.
We are used to dealing with the living dead - our lands have been blighted by your kind since the death of Landuin. Still, I take no pleasure in this meeting.
We have an offer - you would be wise to accept, for the world is teeming with Dark Lords and won't miss the loss of one.
Perhaps a treaty?
The Damsels agree, a treaty would be most wise.
We seek co-operation. Unity is our best course, don't you think?
Let us make Gilles proud, for a united Bretonnia!
The Flower of Bretonnia - our Knights - must work as one.
If the Northmen agree, we will cross the bridge that is their inevitable treachery on another day.
To have a treaty with Chaos is a mark upon our honour, but a stain can be cleaned off when washed in the waters of the Lady.
Do the Dwarfs still hold honour? I'd wager that they do…
Join with us, brave Dwarfs, together we can purge our lands and mountains.
I say to the Empire that now is the time to sign treaties and work for all of mankind.
We offer a treaty, in good faith, to the men of the Empire. Will the Grand Prince Altdorf, hear us?
Sign the treaty, Orc, and may it keep your Green Godz in line - though I doubt it.
We offer the Orcs a treaty, I pray to the Lady for their understanding.
The Undead are used to pacts and unbreakable vows. It is how their Dark Magic works - perhaps a treaty will shackle them?
Will the Undead lords accept our terms?
Here is a token of appreciation.
It is nothing, a small furbelow to mark our friendship.
Please accept our gift, and blessing of Shallya.
Bretonnia is willing and able!
Our lances are sharp and eager, we will join your cause!
It is war, the laws of chivalry demands we act.
The Lady craves peace with you, her will must be done.
There is honour in sheathing a sword as well as wielding it.
Yes, peace - it is a fine thing. For the peasants must return to my farms.
We need peace within our borders. The peasants are rioting!
Our nations must be stable, the Lady demands it.
Peace with Chaos is surely an impossible thing, but I must request it anyway.
The offer of peace will fall upon merciless ears, I know, but my Lady asks anyway.
The Dwarfholds will prosper better with peace between us.
Let our swords be put on the racks and your beards grow long, for there is no need for war.
The fate of the Old World needs the Empire and Bretonnia to be as one.
We are all men, and should not be at each other's throats. There is much honour between us and plenty of enemies without.
Fight amongst yourselves, Orcs, keep us out of this!
Do the Greenskins even understand… peace?
Back to Mousillon with you! Go now and we will not pursue.
We do not wish to fight you anymore, there is no honour in it!
There is no alliance with Bretonnia!
We do not need you for this!
We fight for the Lady - you do not!
Shallya will not walk here this day, for war calls and Bretonnia answers.
There can be no peace - the Knights will charge!
Your ways are unchivalrous and will be punished!
For defying the will of Leoncoeur, you will be chastised.
It is you who broke the Lady's peace and we that will finish it.
Peace with Chaos! Ha! Never!
We will not fall for your ruse, Chaos scum - this war will end with your deaths not until then.
The hearts of Dwarfs and men are no longer aligned – we reject peace.
It is too late, Dwarf, you no longer have any honour.
We had high hopes for this Karl Franz von Holswig-Schliestein, but now it will end in bloodshed.
You have never been good neighbours and now you must reap what you have sown.
Peace? The Greenskins do not know the meaning of such a word!
There will never be peace with the Orcs and the Goblins - they have ever-been enemies of Bretonnia!
We will purge your kind from mine Lady's lands.
No, Vampire, the war is not over until the sun shines upon Mousillon again.
Sally forth! Bretonnia rides to war!
The Green Knight has been seen, it is war!
The Prophetess foresees war!
You bring dishonour on us all - war is the only answer!
As you refuse to obey the king, then it is war!
It is war, Northmen, prepare to be humbled!
Against Chaos, there can only be war!
Never again will we rely on Dwarfen promises - war it is!
War with the Dwarfs, so be it.
We go to war with Reikland and its puppets!
The Empire must be taught that it cannot treat us with such contempt - to war!
War with the Orcs!
Chivalry demands war against the Greenskin invaders!
We make war with the Undead!
The Undead will know fear again - when our Knights charge forth - to war!
Yes, although, the Grail is something a commoner like you could never dream to sup from.
Agreed but do not think to dictate to me what the terms are, peasant.
The Lady agrees, yet I find the whole affair odious.
By the Lady's will - and only by her will - do I accept.
I have spoken with the devoted of the Goddess, they advise me to accept terms.
Your petition has been heard and accepted.
Good, there might be aid from the dukedom forthcoming.
I have prayed to the Lady and believe she agrees.
This will be an alliance worthy of the legends!
I am an honourable servant of the Lady. What are your vile demands?
What are your demands?
Only the Grail Companions of old could hope to best me, yet you would try with words?
What do you want?
The laws of chivalry demand I hear you.
The Lady grants you safe passage in these lands…
Welcome friends. Let's hope we come to an accommodation.
Welcome to fair Bretonnia.
Welcome to fair Bretonnia. Now is the time to unite, yes?
You may have once been men, but yours is a disgusting race! There is no treaty - ever!
The Chaos Gods curse us - we are forced to take their terms.
We'll accept, Northman, but this is a temporary contract, ensure your masters understand that.
Very well - the Lady weeps, but it must be done.
We'll work with you this time, Northman, may the Lady forgive me!
This is the only possible course or so the Fey Enchantress claims.
We have nothing to say to the fetid scum of Chaos, I am an honourable servant of the Lady!
Giles the Uniter once spoke to Chaos filth before he took their lives, I am reliving that moment…
What are your demands, Chaos filth?
It is fitting that creatures of Chaos come to fair Bretonnia to bow and scrape and plead for our aid.
What do the Northmen want, and why are you even still alive in my presence, Chaos-creature?
It is a brave being that ravages my lands and then graces my presence and expects to live.
The northern tribes will be wiped from the lands, and the Lady will rejoice. I have foreseen it!
No, Chaos spawn, the Green Knight will come for all your fetid kind!
No, never, the sacred places of our lands will not be despoiled by your vile kind!
To even suggest it is to invite your ruin, servant of Chaos!
Do you Dark Gods think us fools, Chaos man?
Take your offer back to your foul masters and tell them that Bretonnia shall never fall!
Yes, Bretonnia will bail out the Dwarfs, yet again - best remove us from your grudge tome?
The Lady speaks through the Damsels, and they say we should agree, but I know you too well, Dwarfs!
I suppose, but Bretonnia will not be taken advantage of as you and the Empire are want to do.
My king agrees, but I'm less swayed, Dwarf - too many times have I been bruised by your spiteful tongues.
So it shall be, Dwarf.
Agreed - an alliance of old shall be reborn!
Dwarf, you come helmet in hand - you must be in trouble, looking to fare Bretonnia to bail you out!
I might have known, the days are doom-laden and so the Dwarfs come begging for help!
Mountain-folk come to treat - I hope you have something worthy to offer?
Dwarfs! How may the Lady and her valiant Knights help you?
How do the Dwarf realms fare in these dark days?
Mountain-folk, the Lady has always respected your ancestors, let's hope we come to an accommodation.
No, let the Karaz Ankor fail - it matters not to Bretonnia.
Your on your own, Dwarfs, you'd best get used to eating rock and gold!
Not this time, Dwarf, go about your business and Bretonnia will go about hers.
No, Dwarf - you are on your own this time.
I'm afraid not, Dwarf, it is ill-timed.
Sorry, tell your High King, our resources are simply stretched too thin.
I am ordered to agree, but your greedy burgomeisters will not profit from Bretonnia.
The Damsels have screaming visions of the Empire's doom - we must agree the treaty for the sake of our realm.
Yes, this suits our needs as much as yours, Reiklander.
King Leoncoeur would agree so I must as well.
Agreed - my king will be pleased that the Sons of Sigmar ascent.
Good, kingdom and empire will combine for the fate of man.
What do Sigmar's sorry gets, need from the valiant Knights of Bretonnia this time?
The Empire - a land of peasants and low-born pocket-changers. I have no respect for such people.
Hail, Sigmar's Sons, do you come looking for aid or to cause trouble? I never know with Reiklanders.
What does the Emperor need that he cannot already find in his vast, if tainted, lands.
Welcome, friends - what do the Men of the Hammer require this day?
Hail, fellow nation of men, now is the time to unite, yes?
No, you and your greedy, blood-soaked Guilds are on your own, Reiklander!
Tell your Emperor to keep his truces and his Runefangs - no help from my realm will come!
No, you may be men, but are selfish, greedy… untrustworthy.
You have Knights in the Empire, but it is no coincidence that they have never been gifted with a Grail vision.
No, maybe in the dark days to come but for now, Bretonnia forges its own path.
The Lady cannot help Sigmar this day.
This is a travesty of fate! Yet I must concede.
Lady forgive us, but the Greenskins need to be appeased!
For the gods and the Lady above all - I am compelled to agree.
By the Grail, we are forced to work with the Greenskins!
Yes, why not? Morrslieb hangs low and the world gets stranger every day!
I have checked the histories - it has happened once before. We will work with you this time, Orc.
Orc scum, you dare! What are your vile demands?!
Abase your filthy body, Orc! Only then will I hear your message.
What do you even know of chivalry, Orc?
Greenskin, you come as supplicant, I will hear you out of curiosity rather than need!
I will hear you, Orc, for it amuses me.
Greenskin, you petition a duke of Bretonnia. I only hope you speak sense.
Now is the time of Louen Orc-Slayer once again! Your deaths will be swift, Greenskins!
No, never - you are the Lady's enemies - green despoilers that will be slain on sight!
I'll have you chased from here, Orc, with a full stable of Knights Errant!
Greenskins, your time has come. There will be no help or aid from Bretonnia - we are your mortal foes!
Get out of my sight, Orc - while your notion still amuses me.
No, Orc - Bretonnia is pure, your race is not.
Whether chivalrous or not, I will strike you down, scum, if your words displease me!
Only the Grail Companions of old could hope to best me, yet you would try with words?
What vile filth stands before me?
Bow before the rightful Lords of these lands and I will hear your demands.
These lands are ours by the right granted from the Lady of the Lake! What do you want?
The laws of chivalry demand I hear you.
Welcome to fair Bretonnia, commoner.
Bow before the rightful Lords of these lands and I will hear your demands.
The Lady grants you safe passage in these lands.
No, the Green Knight will be coming for a wretch like you.
No, impure one, there will be no aid from Bretonnia for you.
Never - there is nothing I despise more than the begging and pleading of the unworthy.
Not this day, or the next - Bretonnia's lands and riches are forbidden to you.
Only those who have faith in the Grail can take from these lands, that does not include you.
I will vanquish your armies, should you come crawling back to these lands!
No, Bretonnia weeps, but we cannot help you.
I prayed to the Lady for guidance, yet no answer came.
Another season maybe, but, for now, the peasants must get the harvest in.
This is unfortunate, but for the sake of the sacred stones and lakes, I agree the terms.
I have conferred with King Leoncoeur and, against my judgement, he accepts the ghoul-keeper's offer.
I am forced to agree, liche, but this is not the end of it.
Yes - don't take this treaty as an ascent that your foul race should exist in these fair lands!
Against my own preferences, we have agreement.
Very well - but keep your fetid ghoul-creatures away from the menhirs.
Tomb-scum, what do you have to say to me that would not affront mine Lady's ears?
You think evading Morr is impressive? By the Lady's Will, I will send you back to Him myself!
Undead creature - are you bold, foolish or just arrogant to approach a servant of the Lady this way?
Your offer best be good, Vampire, for I am itching to stake you here and now!
Speak, Vampire, so that I may readily reject your petition!
You must be desperate indeed, liche, to seek the aid of the chivalrous Bretonnian might!
Get into the daylight, Vampire - I'll see the sun burn your skin off before I agree to any pact!
For the Grail and the Lady, I reject your offer and your very existence!
I reject this with joy in my heart, no treaty with Undead filth!
No, back to the cemeteries with you!
You are bold, creature I will give you that, but there is nothing else I would ever offer.
No, I cannot let your hordes blight our lands!
I am an honourable servant of the lady. What are your vile demands?
What are your demands?
Only the Grail Companions of old could hope to best me, yet you would try with words?
What do you want?
The laws of chivalry demand I hear you.
The Lady grants you safe passage in these lands…
Welcome friends.  Let's hope we come to an accommodation.
Welcome to fair Bretonnia.
Welcome to fair Bretonnia. Now is the time to unite, yes?
We have nothing to say to the fetid scum of Chaos, I am an honourable servant of the Lady!
Gilles the Uniter once spoke to Chaos filth before he took their lives. I am reliving that moment…
What are your demands, Chaos filth?
It is fitting that creatures of Chaos come to fair Bretonnia to bow and scrape and plead for our aid.
What do the Northmen want, and why are you even still alive in my presence, Chaos-creature?
It is a brave being that ravages my lands and then graces my presence and expects to live.
Dwarf, you come helmet in hand - you must be in trouble, looking to fair Bretonnia to bail you out!
I might have known, the days are doom-laden and so the Dwarfs come begging for help!
Mountain-folk come to treat - I hope you have something worthy to offer?
Dwarfs! How may the Lady and her valiant Knights help you?
How do the Dwarf realms fare in these dark days?
Mountain-folk, the Lady has always respected your ancestors. Let's hope we come to an accommodation.
What do Sigmar's sorry gets need from the valiant Knights of Bretonnia this time?
The Empire - a land of peasants and low-born pocket-changers. I have no respect for such people.
Hail, Sigmar's Sons, do you come looking for aid or to cause trouble? I never know with Reiklanders.
What does the Emperor need that he cannot already find in his vast, if tainted lands.
Welcome, friends - what do the Men of the Hammer require this day?
Hail, fellow nation of men. Now is the time to unite, yes?
Orc scum, you dare! What are your vile demands?!
Abase your filthy body Orc! Only then will I hear your message.
What do you even know of chivalry, Orc?
Greenskin, you come as supplicant, I will hear you out of curiosity rather than need!
I will hear you, Orc, for it amuses me.
Greenskin, you petition a duke of Bretonnia. I only hope you speak sense.
Whether chivalrous or not, I will strike you down, scum, if your words displease me!
Only the Grail Companions of old could hope to best me, yet you would try with words?
What vile filth stands before me?
Bow before the rightful lords of these lands and I will hear your demands.
These lands are ours by the right granted by the Lady of the Lake! What do you want?
The laws of chivalry demand I hear you.
Welcome to fair Bretonnia, commoner.
Bow before the rightful lords of these lands and I will hear your demands.
The Lady grants you safe passage in these lands.
Tomb-scum, what do you have to say to me that would not affront mine Lady's ears?
You think evading Morr is impressive? By the Lady's Will, I will send you back to Him myself!
Undead creature - are you bold, foolish or just arrogant to approach a servant of the Lady this way?
Your offer best be good, Vampire, for I am itching to stake you here and now!
Speak, Vampire, so that I may readily reject your petition!
You must be desperate indeed, liche, to seek the aid of the chivalrous Bretonnian might!
I want to vanquish you, but the Enchantress counsels me to accept.
Don't make me regret this decision, the consequences for you will be great.
The Council of Nobles rejects this offer… and so I accept, don't make me a fool for this!
Very well, the treaty is signed. By the Grail, I hope I make a wise recourse.
The Fay Enchantress whispers to me - this is an agreement I must make.
Yes, but do not let this pageantry blind you… Or mistake me for a fool…
We have an accord, let's mark this day with a great tournament!
Yes, the nobles will be pleased – it's always good to halt their plotting for a time.
An agreement then! Bring out the wine - the 1532 Bordeleaux will do for this occasion.
I must - may the kingdom forgive me!
It galls me - I am compelled to follow a prophecy given by the Enchantress.
If I must, but I will see you on my lance for this, scum!
Yes - Lady guide me, for I make a terrible decision.
I am not happy about this, but I must consent.
So it must be.
Chaos filth! Get back on your longship, before I order it sank by trebuchet!
I'll bring about the end of your tribes, Northmen - Bretonnia will take it all in the Lady's name.
You dare come before me, Northman? What do your fell masters want of Bretonnia?
There is still pride in Bretonnia enough to listen and reject the lies of Chaos maggots!
I'll hear you out, Chaos worm, but do not expect blessings from the King of Bretonnia!
What could the Northmen want that they deem it necessary to parley?
Never! I would renounce my throne and let my bastard sit on it before siding with you!
The Ruinous Powers take too many liberties with my kingdom - they will pay!
A vile notion - one I would dearly like to punish with your death, Chaos filth.
I reject your 'offer' and your vile Gods!
I have ruled for two decades - do you think me greener than the Green Knight? Be gone!
I'll let you leave alive, agent of Chaos, but my Knights hanker to run you through - consider this a head start.
Fine - Bretonnia accepts the Dwarf plan for the good of my nation, not the Karaz Ankor.
I suppose so, Dwarf, but I do this of necessity, not goodwill. Your kind has burnt all goodwill from me.
Good, an agreement is reached. Do not let me down again, Dwarf.
We have worked together before. Just temper your spite, grudge-holder, and this treaty can last.
We have a treaty, Dwarf - forgive me if I celebrate with a robust red instead of that grog you enjoy so much.
Yes, two honourable races join in alliance.
You vex me greatly, Dwarf. Maybe I should just slay you instead?
Here come the Dwarfs to lecture, criticise, and demand - what do you want?
You come as a supplicant, Dwarf? Not too proud to ask for favours now?
How can the King of Bretonnia aid the Dwarfholds? What boon do you ask of me?
The Dwarfs have ever-been friends of Bretonnia - what brings you down from your mountain, Dawi?
Welcome, Dwarf, do you bring news from the mountain realms?
No, Grudge-kin, my patience for your race has worn thin.
No, Thorgrim does not deign to come himself and treat with me king to king.
I have no time for the petty offences of the Dwarfs - too much is at stake.
Stay your hand, Dwarf, there is no agreement - tell Thorgrim so.
Bad news for your High King. Bretonnia cannot aid you on this occasion.
Not this time, Dwarf, try again next feast day.
Agreed, but my terms are strict in these doomed times.
Reiklander, I do not care for this Emperor - too arrogant by far - Yet I'm forced into ascent.
Yes, we have a treaty. The terms are set, do not think to change them, Reiklander.
Despite your insolence, Reiklander, I will agree to this.
An alliance of men - the strongest pact this world has ever seen!
Yes, together the creatures of Chaos do not stand a chance.
As expected, Franz, only comes calling when he needs something, but it is far too late!
My Lady speaks unfavourably of Sigmar. You worship a false god, so why should I listen?
It's late in the day for the Empire to send its ambassadors to my door!
The Empire only cross the Grey Mountains when they need something from me. What is it this time?
Our neighbours in the east deign to visit - I hope you bring glad tidings.
Welcome, how fares the Emperor in these dark times?
No - the Empire is too fractured. Your nation is doomed, yet my kingdom can survive.
There is no treaty, Reiklander - I forbid it!
No, this time the Empire must fare on its own.
Too many times Bretonnian has sought alliance with the Empire and been rebuffed. Now it is their turn…
I would like nothing better than to join our two nations, but the time is not right.
No, tell Franz he approaches me at an inopportune time.
If we must work with Orcs, I will - although it shames Gilles the Uniter's legacy.
Hide the eyes of the Damsels, for I must agree this treaty with fell Orcs.
Very well, it serves Bretonnia, but I'll be keeping a close eye on you, Greenskin.
Yes, I do this for the Grail - not for your disgusting kind.
Very well, the Lady informs me this suits Bretonnian interests for now.
Fine, do your thing, Orc, as long as it is not in Bretonnian lands.
Orc, you defile my sacred groves and yet come to parley - don't expect to keep your green head!
I will not treat with Orc scum - theirs is a vile race that needs scouring from my lands!
Beast! My ancestor was Louen Orc-Slayer, should I invoke his name?
Tell me why I do not issue an Errantry War against your entire race right now, Orc?
Orcs! That is all I need! What do you want, Greenskin?
Can you even talk with that guttural mouth, Orc?
No - I do not talk to Greenskins, we behead them!
Be gone, green filth - never darken this realm again!
No, Orc, I'll see your tribe massacred rather than broker a deal with you!
I think not, Greenskin - I'll have Beaquis feed on your innards rather than work with you.
The Lady forbids that we ally with Orcs!
Ha! The whole concept is beyond understanding, back to your fouls dwellings, Orcs!
Not one step further, stranger - you do not walk my lands without my blessing - which you don't have!
This is Bretonnia; I am its king! For the Lady's sake, state your demands, so I can reject them!
You are a guest in my realm. You will act like it, or I will strike you down where you stand!
You come to Bretonnia, stranger. I am its king - let us hope you leave as a friend…
You tread upon Bretonnian land. I'll have your will, and I'll have it now!
I am King Leoncoeur. So, do you come to Bretonnia as its friend or enemy?
Let the supplicant come forward.
Do you wish the Lady's favour?
You ask for a boon, speak and I will see if it is within my power to give.
Do not think to command me! I am the king of this realm! Now go, before my Knights set about you.
Yours is a race I despise. There is no agreement and never will be!
Get from my sign, cur, before I summon the Grail Knights to bring me your head!
No, Bretonnia is best served by banishing you from the realm.
I reject this notion - as is my right, granted to me by the Lady herself!
What you ask for is something that should be dressed in motley and called a fool's wish!
No, I fear this will end in tears.
I'm afraid not - the dukes would be in uproar!
We must adjourn this meeting. Another time perhaps?
So it must be. A fell choice.
Yes, but I despise your kind, and will crusade until you are all are back in Morr's realm.
I am forced into this by circumstances, liche - know that I will break it as soon as I can.
Yes - it galls me greatly, but… yes.
A necessary pact.
We have agreement, but I take no joy in it.
Spawn of Mousillon, Beaquis will feast on your entrails for even daring to be in my presence!
I feel the Lady's anger at your presence, Vampire - say what you will, but be quick!
Your mocking bow does not frighten me, Corpse-spawn - I'll have that head as I have many of your kind.
What is your message, tomb-scum? Speak it now so my Lady can reject its unholy words.
Dread Knight of Mousillon - what do you want?
I will hear you out, Vampire-spawn, but make no promises as to the conduct of my Knights…
By the Grail, no! I am king of this fair realm, not some disgusting liche!
Never - Kemmler, the von Carsteins - none are welcome here!
Be gone from my lands, Undead filth. The Knights Errant will be on your trail soon enough!
Tell Kemmler and all his ilk, I will hunt you down and raise Mousillon to the ground!
The Lady would never forgive me! No!
Get from my sight, foul creature.
Gah! It gals me, but yes!
I have the rage of Khorne for this, but my masters order me to agree!
So be it, mortal scum, but your flayed skin will adorn my cloak for this outrage!
Such a pact is possible, but I sense betrayal on your mind. That will be your last mistake.
I have consulted with hellish oracles on this and they agree to the pact.
My loyal Swords of Chaos counsel against this, but I feel I should accept.
Very well, we have a pact. However, your very existence is forfeit should you betray my will.
It seems we have an agreement, witnessed by the Chaos Gods.
And now we will complete the concord with a sacrifice…
This must be another trial by my Dark Gods, for I am forced into a pact with backwater yokels.
Gaarh! Tzeentch spites me! Yes, we have a truce of sorts, Bretonnian scum!
Yes, we may have a compact, providing the low-born sacrifices are delivered as promised!
Agreed, but should that mer-witch you "worship" show up - I'll ravage it.
Ha, why not?! I accept!
The arrogance of Bretonnian Knights - I can use this.
There is not one thing - not one trinket - you can offer, that will prevent me from obliterating Bretonnia and wiping it from the map!
Bretonnia's fate is sealed. I will murder everyone within its borders, salt the fields and taint its lakes!
An idiotic notion! Bretonnia is a backwater, it holds little for me except for blood and slaughter.
No - your Knights are nothing; your peasants' souls are weak and brittle. I'll take them all from you anyway!
Hahaha, you wish for some pact? My rivals would mock and fell me from my noble station!
I have the favour of all four Great Powers, why would I jeopardise that by working with… Bretonnians!
Yes-yes, we will ally, but your utter abasement is more than necessary, it is assured.
Very well - but do not attempt usurp me! I have a special hell for traitors to the Everchosen.
Good, an alliance will benefit this invasion and see gifts from the masters rain down upon us both.
I expect total obedience, but in reward for your support, apotheosis awaits.
Good - our armies shall march as one.
This is well, friend, the Chaos Gods are pleased - I can feel it.
I have no use for you. You shall be slaughtered and your forces subsumed by mine own.
No, I care not for your warband of dogs. Get from here, before I send the Swords of Chaos to do my will.
No, you bring nothing but mongrels. It is tribes such as the Kurgan I need, not this maggoty stock.
You play at war, boy, but this is a man's game. You are not worthy of that mark upon your neck!
No, you seek my titles, not my favour. Your end will be miserable for that.
You interrupt my plans, with your pathetic whimpers.
I'll agree Dwarf, just to see you shamed before all your stunted race. Chaos will always triumph!
Very well, Dawi-scum, tell your self-important kings that the Everchosen ascents. Your souls are mine!
Ai, Dwarfs, we have a contract. I pray you break it, so I may reap a bloody revenge through the Karak Ankor!
Yes, and I'll have the soul of every Son of Grungni in payment.
I'll have your honour sealed in mine own grimoire, Dwarf. Such irony don't you think?
To see the abasement and cowering of Dwarfs, the Ruinous Powers will be pleased!
Stunted-scum, you offer me nothing, I cannot take with such little effort.
The Grudgebearer is desperate! When I see your High King, I will knock him off his little stone chair!
No, Dwarfs. My counter-offer is your utter destruction!
Not this time, Dwarf, or ever. Flee back to the mountains and cower in your halls - for I come!
Ha - what a strange prospect! Have you turned to your kin in the Dark Lands for advice!
Why would I even need to ally with you, honourless creatures?
So be it, but remember, pacts are ephemeral, mortal, and I have been awaiting your extinction for over a century!
I will ascent, but know that I was once one of you - I know Sigmar's secret - the thing Volkmar dare not say! You are all damned!
So be it - a pact with Sigmar's inbred progeny. The fates mock us!
It serves me to work with this Franz, but I will have his head - that is a promise and I never break those.
Very well - we have a temporary alliance, at best.
Haha! Yes, Tzeentch truly works in intricate ways!
Craven fools! I am Lord of the End Times - there is no offer! No pact! My only promise is your utter destruction!
The Empire is dead! Soon your cities will be ransacked, your citizens maimed and praying for my mercy!
Do you take me for some simpering fool? Of course there is no alliance - I have but to order it and the Empire will fall!
No, not now or ever, run back to your preening Emperor and tell him the true master of mankind comes.
What blinkered fools, to come here! I'll let you live on condition you spread this message: your pitiful Empire will burn!
No, there is only one choice, proclaim Chaos as your true masters, or see your souls… wither.
I suppose it serves the Gods to make pact. But I'd sooner wipe every last stinking Greenskin out!
Yes. For now we have an agreement, Orc beast. But I do hope you betray me, so I may kill your entire tribe!
Good, the Orcs shall ride with Chaos, but then the Greenskins will fall before my blade when I tire of them.
I see an alliance could work, but tell your Boss, Orc, that I expect utter obedience - anything less will lead to your deaths.
Agreed, your Orcs have certain… uses.
I will use your hordes, my Lord Khorne, has a certain affection for you, beasts.
No, Orc, never will I lower myself to work with your insipid kind!
Not this time, Orc. Get this thing from my sight! Feed it to the spawn!
I tire of Greenskins! They are insects that will not die no matter how many times they are stamped upon!
No, Orc, your race interests me less than the bearded troglodytes. And that is saying something!
No, Greenskin, just because you slaughter the humans, do not mistake this for acquiescence on my part.
I doubt there is any need for a pact. Even your base souls belong to Chaos.
NEVER! To even suggest this brings upon a wrath that will see everything you hold dear reduced to ashes!
No, your armies will be obliterated as punishment!
I am Chaos - more powerful than the Gods themselves, you'll see!!!
You seek a deal with forces you do not understand, mortal. For that I must teach you a lesson.
Look upon the Crown of Domination and know that I will soon seek your doom.
No, the Everchosen requires no such alliance!
You vex me… for your soul's sake, that is not wise.
I will let it go this once. The Dark Gods have plans for you.
Ha! You think this matters to me? You are very wrong.
Very well, but I will rip the face off any liche that gets in my way!
So be it, maggot king. But be warned, Father Nurgle knows more about death than you ever will.
So be it. Chaos legions with your rotting puppets. What could possibly go wrong?
I ascent. Do not mistake this for anything but convenience, Vampire.
Very well, my hordes will work with your shambling things… for now.
Yes, that is an accord signed in blood, such things matter to you?
Never! I am noble, enshrined by my crown, but you are nothing - a corpse that doesn't ever realise it has ceased.
The very idea disgusts me. Go back to your minions, puppeteer, and prepare for your doom.
Why would I ally with grave-feeders and their pet liches. I have the full might of the Ruinous Powers at my command!
No, your master is Nagash. I would destroy him with nary a look - so why should I fear your wrath?
While I can admire your limited abilities, I have no use for you.
It is true we share some dark desires, yet you wish to rule the mortals. That will not be, for I desire their obliteration!
Such pointless baubles… put it on the pile with the rest of the plunder.
I'll take your gift, but it's your souls I want!
How gracious… but if you think this trifling thing will appease my masters then you are mistaken…
We have a pact. You will not regret this…
Good, Tzeentch will be pleased!
Praise to the Raven God! We shall sacrifice nine hundred and ninety-nine souls in celebration!
You do not break a pact with Chaos!
To cancel a treaty with Chaos - you are either brave or a fool. I'd wager the latter.
Breaking this agreement is to make an enemy of the Dark Powers. To have your name upon the lips of a God and spoken in hatred… Your soul is doomed.
To reject such an offer is to make sworn enemies of the Dark Powers.
If you are sure… my masters have eternity to make you change your mind.
Ahh, the puppy barks its defiance. Should we put it out of its misery?
Then Khorne will reap your souls!
There will be much blood for the Blood God this day.
Our master, Khorne, rejoices! War is His domain.
There is no profit for my masters in this.
This contract is at an end, we will collect the souls in any case.
This treaty is dead, as are you…
Join us, for we all will reap the benefits!
Do not let your distaste for the north stop you from joining us in battle.
Come, let us make war together and the Blood God will bless us all.
Your tally is due!
We will have payment in valuables, delay any longer and it will be your souls!
I'm sure an accommodation can be reached. After all, our masters have little need for gold and other gimcracks.
Hear me, man. Your water-witch cannot help you now.
Your lands will be ashes, so hear us now!
Come Bretonnian, accept our offer and delay the suffering of your people.
The lands of the Bretons are doomed! You must know that…
Let us drink your wine, mortal, and together we can hammer out a pact.
So, do you wish to know the horrifying truth about your parochial god?
Insignificant Chieftain! Hear me!
Bow before your superior, take my offer and be dominated!
I have an offer for you, champion.
The tribes must unite if the south is to be destroyed. Consider this an offer.
We share the same Gods, so consider this offer.
Take this offer, and Daemonhood awaits.
Stunted fools, hear me now.
The Dwarfs are a dying race - I demand you attend me!
Take the offer and my master shall ensure your Holds will be great again.
If you consider this, then I will ensure all your grudges are paid in kind.
The Dwarfs have worked with Chaos before, ask your kin in the east…
Should the Dawi accept this offer then we will make the Karaz Ankor a force to behold.
Your weakling god cannot save you - hear us!
I demand an audience, or see your cities burn!
Perhaps Sigmar will reappear for this audience?
Your pathetic cult cannot stop us, hear our demands and you may slow the tide.
Now is the time, men of the Empire, to rise up and join us!
The Gods have always had an affection for your nation, pray it doesn't end.
Primitive creatures - the Dark Powers have little use for you, but you will hear our offer anyway.
Impudent Greenskin! You have yet to see true war - but you will!
Our masters have a passing interest in your kind, Greenskin, so hear our offer.
Do you speak the dark tongue, Orc? We have a request.
An offer for you, spawn of Gork, spew of Mork.
Greenskins, you crave war? Then listen to us.
You will take my offer, it is ordained!
Listen! I say this but once.
Bow your heads and listen to the Slayer of Kings!
I have a message from the Changer of Ways, you would do well to take note.
When the Gods make you an offer, do not hesitate to accept.
Rather than have you slain upon that spot, my Masters wish you hear their offer.
Surely you will hear my offer, or risk damnation?
The Gods of Chaos have manifold reasons for making this offer.
Join us by accepting this small offer.
You think to control Chaos, mortals? How twee. Now listen to the real terrors of the world.
We may not have your souls, but we will take what you crave the most - your blood.
Perhaps the north and the Unliving can work together?
Do the von Carsteins fear us? I think they do.
A pact, Vampire, will seal the doom of the mortal lands.
So the destruction of the world may come from an offer between us, liche.
Names are powerful, mortal - if you know mine, then a treaty is possible.
I know the envoys of Tzeentch, mortal - they have a small contract you may wish to sign.
Come, let us sign a pact in the blood of innocents and seal it with the bones of your fathers.
Oh, Bretonnian, we know you crave the greatness that the Empire basks in but alludes your own nation. Sign this pact and the fates can change.
A treaty with us, will keep your nobles safe from the poxes that Father Nurgle has planned for your lands.
A pact amongst the tribes…
We have a pact to offer, does the Kurgan know what goes on here?
Come Dwarfs sign the treaty, just as your eastern kin did so long ago.
The Dwarfs like to write things down… why not sign this treaty?
Will Franz and his allies right the wrongs done to their doomed little nation? They can by signing this treaty.
Come now, Sigmar signed such a document when he ruled. How do you think he attained godhood? I know, I was there.
Put the cross there, Orc, and the treaty will be locked.
Orcs and men of Iron - the lands will tremble!
A pact in blood, Vampire? How fitting.
Nagash allied with our masters before, creature - although that didn't end too well.
Yes, take this wealth - these coins, and relics… if that's what makes you feel safe.
We can gift you riches… but surely it is power you desire?
You know not true power - I can show you the real thing!
The Blood God bids me to join you.
War! We are drawn to it - let the Northmen join you.
Yes! We will link swords, for Khorne cares not whence the blood flows.
When Khorne wanes, his brothers counsel peace to work their own plots.
The Dark Prince demands peace, so he may seek out fresh followers.
We must break from war, so the altars of our masters can be built and the slaves sacrificed.
Come Bretonnians, does your hag-queen not revel in peace?
So Bretonnia, we will stop raiding to concentrate on other prey. I'd suggest accepting the quiet.
Now is not the time for war, champion - let our masters scheme and plot and brew new plagues!
There is no peace - we are of the north, yet there are times to halt the fighting… this is one of them!
Not peace, Dwarf, for your realms will never have that, but a cessation of hostilities… for now.
Go cower in your mountain holes, Dwarf. We tire of you.
We will give you peace, southlanders, but when we return we will come harder than ever before!
Go and lick your wounds, Reiklanders, heal fast for we will come again.
We don't want peace with you, Orc - we just want you to fight SOMETHING ELSE!
Leave us be, Orcs, even Khorne tires of warring with you.
Perhaps a halt in hostilities will allow us to marshal our warriors against the real targets.
Your forces are powered by magic, our Gods create that magic… there will be no more conflict between us, it does not suit Tzeentch's ends.
Ha ha! Khorne demands blood. There is no room for alliances!
Cattle are to be slaughtered, not to be allied with.
Work together? No, you are the quarry, the prey - not the hunter's dog!
There is no peace! Your lands will be obliterated.
Khorne rages! There is only war!
The Chaos Gods demand souls! Forget your notions of peace!
Your lands will burn, Bretonnian.
Your Lady's aspect will shrivel as she is brought before the Chaos Gods. No peace for you, Bretonnia.
We are born to fight! The north and then the southern lands shall drown in blood!
We fight, no peace, only eternal violence!
Your Holds will be filled with your own brackish blood - you will choke on it!
Peace with the Dwarfs? I will see their beards ripped from their chins before we give them peace!
When Volkmar is tied to my banner renouncing the Heldenhammer, when Altdorf chokes with burning smoke, then… then, we will talk about peace.
No peace for your people, Franz, they are doomed - as are all of your generals and allies.
Peace, Orc? You betray your race!
No, Orc, I reject your begging for peace. We will wash the Badlands clean of Orc blood!
The time of the Vampires ends, just as it does for men and Dwarfs. There is no peace, for you are of no consequence.
You think you’re a power? That you can challenge the Dark Gods? Be gone creature and await the judgement of Chaos.
The Gods demand war!
Blood for the Blood God!
Skulls for the Skull Throne!
It is time to cull Bretonnia - to war!
We war with Leoncoeur. Bring me his head!
Do you think you're worthy of the Everchosen? Bring it on!
The Eye of the Gods - war will bring us their gaze!
It is war, Dawi. Prepare to die.
Karaz Ankor will be ashes - we march to war!
This is war! Pray to your pathetic comet - it will do you no good.
Say your last rites, mortals! Pray that Morr takes you before I do!
War then - for Khorne!
Kill the Greenskins, destroy their foolish gods!
Summon your puppets, Vampire, for war is upon you!
War with the dead! It makes no difference whether they breathe or not - all shall suffer our wrath!
A dark pact. I have another to my name, this is no different.
Agreed – but don't think to control me, even the Ruinous Powers cannot.
The Bringer of Darkness agrees to your pathetic terms.
The pact is struck, the mountains bear witness!
We have a deal. Do not disappoint.
The sky darkens; the Gods watch; the offer is struck.
What could you want from the father of Dragon Ogres, little man?
I care nothing for Bretonnian souls!
Your petty nations mean nothing to me, mortal! All of the south is for spoiling!
I'll mangle you in that armour if you speak lies to me, mortal!
What have you to say, mortal man-child?
Make your offer, so I can hear your Lady weep.
You dare summon Kholek!
We may share the same masters, but don't think I am your ally!
I have tasted the flesh you sent as an offering – what do you want?
The Suneater comes, spare me your empty gestures!
Your sacrifices have woken me – is this the End Time?
I am roused, what do you want?
Your words are meaningless, Dwarf!
You stink of mountain ash, Dwarf filth!
Ha! You think you are long-lived, Dwarf?
Child of Grimnir – spit out your demand!
Fellow creatures of the mountains – do you wish something from me?
We have ever-been enemies, Dwarf – why come now?
Sigmar was no god! Behold a true God!
Your Emperor will kiss the earth before me!
I'll crush your skull, human, so make these words count…
Your world is fragile. Let me show you how easily it breaks!
Come, little men, whisper your offer.
It is a brave mortal that comes to my lair.
What do you want, greenskinned mortal?
Orcs taste rancid, yet I'll grind their bones if I have to!
What do these green creatures want with me?
Speak then, Orc – but I will burn you from the sky if you anger me!
What do these green things want?
Orcs. I have squashed many in my time. Now they come to me?
You dare to barter with me? I have brokered deals with gods!
You summon me, little mortal?! I will feast on your sun!
My rage is eternal! There is nothing I want but your obliteration!
You summon the storm?
I am the tempest, what could you offer me?!
You demand to witness the first-born of Krakanrok the Black? Do you wish to die?
I have bathed in lightning – I am energised.
Speak, mortal.
Bow before the Mountain God!
Never, I will crush your bones to powder, that is the only thing I need.
Mortal fool! The tempests will rip your lands to shreds for this outrage!
I will crush your soul to pulp with mine hammer for even asking!
Go now, before I bring Starcrusher to bear.
There is nothing you have I cannot take!
The mountains reject you!
Your offer, liche – be quick!
Say what you must, dead-thing!
What do you propose, corpse-creature?
Why should I ally with you, corpse?
Very well, Vampire, I'll hear you out.
Storms come, Undead one, will you be part of it?
If that is what the Chaos Gods desire, then I am duty-bound to agree… but I will have vengeance!
This is insufferable! When it is done, I shall enjoy flaying the skin from your bones!
I suppose we must strike an agreement, as much as it disgusts me to do so.
We have agreement… but there are certain conditions. Trivialities, really - but we must discuss them all the same…
Very well, there will be consequences of course. The gifts of the Gods are rarely… unobtrusive.
We have an alliance. Do not think to renege. That is not the done thing… at least until I betray you first.
Yes, this works for my Gods. Your desire is irrelevant.
We have a pact. Sign this contract in the blood of your first son and we can begin…
I agree. Now we shall sow the seeds of destruction upon our mutual enemies.
We have terms - extracting ones… But your nobles will turn a blind eye, as they have in the past.
Yes! Sign the contract, and condemn your kingdom to eternal servitude!
Very well - but Epidemus the Tallyman is close, so the terms of this alliance will cost you dear.
Then we have an agreement. Prepare your towns, for my hordes will take their toll this very night!
Yes, we will work together. It serves me for now.
Good, yes, why do you kneel so easily, Bretonnian? No fight left in you?
Even Grandfather Nurgle turns his nose up at your pitiful kingdom - I have no use for you.
No, Bretonnia will fall - it is and ever has been a weak ally. Its fate is sealed.
Fools! Why would I even consider this? Bretonnia is doomed, I don't need your permission to take it!
No, the hag you revere will be the first to fall during the oncoming invasion.
No, tell your king he and his ilk will suffer, along with all mortals.
So, this is what the end of Bretonnia feels like - I’ll savour it!
Yes, the invasion beings! Know that as the strongest of us I dominate the horde!
An alliance is possible, but the Gods demand I control it!
Of course, we should ally - we bring the End Times that much closer if we do.
Yes, but I demand acknowledgement before the Gods for this sacrifice!
Yes, unleash the Warshrines! We bring glory to the Gods.
I will trade you Aurugulass the Slaughterbrute for your favour.
No, this is my time. Archaon's reign is doomed - I'll pick up the crown when he's gone.
Do you think me the Curseling? I am no traitorous dog - I am Lord of Chaos!
No, my horde is mine own to command, and it will fall upon yours with fervour should I order it!
You bring shame upon the Northmen! For that I will have your head!
This is not Tzeentch's will - I don't need to be a sorcerer to tell you that.
No, the Blue Scribes have spoken - this is not meant to be.
I suppose, but should you stunted cretins think to betray me, know that I'll have already considered it!
Very well, Dwarfs, a pact for now. Your time is coming anyway.
Yes, Dwarf, an alliance - for yours is a realm I'll take soon enough anyway.
A pact then. As we destroy your so-called honour, we weaken the soul of every Dawi.
Yes, it cheers me to see you lose your honour. For that we can come to terms.
Agreed - you drive as hard a bargain as your cousins in the Dark Lands. You are closer to them than you care to admit.
No, stunted fools. There is nothing you can offer the Chaos Gods but your inevitably destruction.
Dwarf-scum, the answer is no, but the path to destruction is now clear, the Karaz Ankor will fall.
No, Dwarfs - there is no solace for you here, just the destruction of your faded kingdoms!
My Gods demand that we drink Dwarf blood this night!
No - The Grudgebearer's Age of Reckoning ends here.
I think not, Dawi - your hold over the mountains is at an end.
I'll have hostages to secure my terms! Should you renege they will not just die, but become spawn!
Yes, but this changes nothing! Valten and Franz - both will be dead by my hand!
Yes, we will ally, it matters not - all will fall before Khorne and his brothers in time.
There are those who would shun me for this pact, but a Lord of Change assures me this is the correct path!
Yes, why not! We will destroy our mutual foes before we claim your souls as well.
Agreed, the terms are set. I wonder for your sake if you have made a grave mistake, Empire man?
No, for the Empire's days are numbered - within your lifetimes you will know true hell.
Never! As long as I wear this armour I will not ally with southern filth!
No, the Empire stands on its own, making its fall all the more delicious.
We are enemies, maggot! There will be no pact with men of the Old World.
No, the only offer I'll hear is your Emperor begging for his soul on the steps of the Sigmarite temple!
No, the time of man is at an end! Now, go back to your nation and tell all that Chaos is coming.
Alright! For once I will ally with the Orcs. This way we can channel their aggression and serve Khorne.
Yes, Greenskin, a treaty - if you even understand the concept!
So be it, Greenskins and Northmen - an alliance doomed to fail, but I'll take advantage while I can.
Yes, then when you are finished - we'll take your base souls as well.
Good - the green hordes and the Ruinous Powers shall be as one!
All to the good, Orc. Now which of your mobs will be sacrificed to Khorne?
No - I will make your gods suffer for such insolence!
Your entire green race will soon be at an end. I look forward to that time more than any other!
There is no pact! There never will be, my Gods would turn me to Spawn for even thinking it!
No, I do not work with beasts - unless they're formed in the Gods' image.
You mistake leniency for approval, Orc. That is your last mistake!
A pathetic offer! It is rejected along with all of your sorry race.
You mock me, and for that there will be no mercy! I pledge your murder before the Skull Throne!
You are a fool, more than a fool - an utter wretch, whose soul will know torment for all eternity!
The stupidity of your masters knows no bounds, and for that you'll pay with your derisory life.
Flee if you must - no matter where you run we will find you and harvest your soul!
No, there is no need for subtlety here. Khorne rages! We must have slaughter!
Hahaha! You surely jest? There is no bartering with a Lord of Chaos!
Yours is a poor lot - for I will take your life and all those you hold dearest.
No, there is no deal to be struck here. The Gods have no use for you or your kin.
So it falls to me to provide my Gods with a bountiful harvest, and it is not grain I reap…
Your threats are meaningless, grave-feeder. We will work together for it suits me.
Yes, there is profit for Nurgle in this. The rotting corpses make perfect carriers - I will take command.
Yes, this works. Together we will rid the world of mortals… and death.
Yes, but there are terms. My masters demand recompense for slaying so many potential followers.
Yes, our forces can work together. You take their bodies, I'll claim their souls.
Very well, we will share the plunder, but I have no use for trinkets or bones.
No, you may shun the weakling god, Morr, but my masters are far harder to avoid.
Never! There is no place for you or your rotting ilk. Even Father Nurgle rejects your advances.
Not this time, Vampire. Now go and play with your corpses, let the true Dark Lord go about his business.
This is not your time, Vampire. These are the End Times, and your feeble race plays no part in them!
I think not - all destruction will be in tribute to the Ruinous Powers!
We have no time to hash out any agreement with the Undead, Khorne thirsts for blood and battle!
That is the offer, Ungol!
Take it, southerner!
The tribute is before you.
There is nothing else.
A generous offer.
The Dark Gods smile on this pact.
We will share blood and spoils!
You are fortunate we have agreed to this.
We want peace, for now.
Enough blood has been spilt.
Never, the Hound demands blood!
There is no peace among us!
It must be war!
Pray to your god. War comes!
So, Ungol, we have a blood pact.
We shall share glory!
If this is the only way…
I will not bargain with a mongrel-prince of the south.
We've heard your God-Bear. He whimpers in the wind.
State your demand, Ungol… or do you need your queen’s permission?
You trespass, Ungol. What toll will you pay to avoid punishment?
Do you offer tribute or wergild? There is a cost when you speak with the tribes.
I will listen… I see power in you.
I will not deal with a Kislevite!
Never, my God will devour yours!
Trespassers, be gone!
You forget yourself… I will take this pact, but know that your tribute is the soul of every being you command.
It shall be - my masters will visit you shortly. Guard your dreams.
It is done, my tribes will work with yours. Betray me and you will feel the vengeance of the Norse.
The pact is sealed. We will share many gifts.
Yes, but do not flinch at the sigils I show you - they are the marks of our masters and soon you will sport one yourself!
You have the support of the Vargs and Skaelings - but the Sarls reject you!
Yes, we will take to our longships!
Ha! A tribal moot is called - I shall summon the Skaelings to war!
Good, our Gods visited upon us many blessings this night - a sign that they are in favour of this!
No - your destiny lies on the Altar of the Crimson Harvest!
No, yours is a great sacrifice - one I shall enjoy eeking out of you!
Never - the fleets of Norsca will take to the seas and we will find your realm, cur!
Get from these frozen lands, before the Slaughterbrutes and Ice Drakes catch your fetid scent!
Yours is a fool's treaty - you think you can mock us and not pay with your soul?
No - there is no bargain, no barter without your souls as surety!
No, return to your tribe and tell them that the Norse have no masters but our Gods!
Your tributes are poor - there is no pact!
Get back across the Sea of Claws, southlander, we will follow you soon enough!
So it is. The Eagle calls and persuades me, but I will still see you on a spit!
Yes, that is the will of the Chaos Gods, yet they have promised we can feast on your bones afterwards.
Agreed, but the tribes of Norsca never forget!
Yes, the tribes shall come together - there will be a great feast and much blood spilt!
The Chaos Gods grant me much power and through it I know this offer is good.
The covenant is signed, you forfeit your lives and more if you break it!
There is consensus amongst the north men. They accept.
I have divined an answer from the Gods - they agree.
I look into the fire pit and the flames shape into agreement.
Now is the time the tribes march south - it is too late for your petty treaties!
Fear us - fear the wrath of Chaos and all Northmen!
So like southerners to talk instead of fight - you'll see how Northmen answer!
I have received a Manticore's sting. It provides me with great visions in which I see your traitorous acts!
The tribes gather, but they will not sign any pact with you!
A weakling and a fool, that is what I see before me. Go and tell your masters the Norse come for you all!
Hmm, the tribes are not so easily swayed, it'll take more than that.
I speak for the Norscan tribes, and we deny your petty offer.
A trifling offer - a larger tribute is required.
So it shall be. Now go – your repellence sours my mood.
Agreed, I suppose – tell me, how do you live looking like that?
You make pact with Chaos. A strange choice, idiotic even, but then you are desperate, yes?
Hmm, yes, very well. Maybe we can make the colours work, and will be able to ally.
We have agreement – I just need a little soul we could sacrifice to father, do you have one?
Yes, we have an accord, now please go. Your horrid presence puts me in such a bad mood.
This is fortuitous news, for I would have had to murder you if no agreement was struck.
Excellent, let's us decant the wine, and drink to this accord.
Yes, now, together, let's thank my father – he would appreciate it.
If it pleases my master, which it does – but I don't like this. It angers me… such an ugly emotion.
Very well, I agree but have no doubt, Bretonnian, I'll make your nation suffer for this!
Agreed, but if I see just one filthy peasant the contract is void and I'll kill thousands as penalty.
A good offer, I shall have to ponder it… yes, very well. Bring us wine, let us bless… this union.
I'll accept, but I may have to kill many of you if you get in my way.
You flatter me, sirs – or is that just my reflection in yon armour. Yes, we have a pact.
You mock me? To even ask for such a boon is to sign your death papers!
No, and now you'll pay – Sliverslash will not rest until it is covered in the blood of Bretonnia!
No, take your damsels and Knights and be gone from my presence. The whole thing is depressing me.
By all the Gods of Chaos, no, and thrice, no. I have far too much fun killing all of you.
No, you are a nation of preening fools. I can't have any such competition!
I fear not, while your vainglory suits my own, our thoughts of what chivalry is are quite different.
Yes, we will merge as one, but know that I command, as is my right as the Geld-Prince!
The followers of Chaos have as many fools in them as the southerners! Yet, we must work together.
You have secured the services of the Geld-Prince of Slaanesh. Please, do offer thanks and prayers – it all helps.
Your sycophantic pandering has been noted. We have a pact.
Yes, let us entwine our hordes. You will, of course, submit to my overlordship, I do not have to ask nicely.
Yes, I feel a connection. My fawning servants assure me that killing you would be a bad thing, so I won't.
Get from my presence, spawn! I will not sully my beautiful hands by cowing to your whims!
I reject your offer, and reinforce my will with your head on a silver platter if I must!
I get a bad feeling from you – you wish to kill me? Do you truly wish to test how fast I am?
Go back to your masters and tell them, I'll see them in the seventy-seven hells before I acquiesce to their demands.
Alas not. We would clash – I just know it.
No, my Father-Prince is a jealous God, and I am his alone.
How trying – I must work with the Dwarfs. Father-Prince must hate me!
Gods! Why do you punish this perfect form? I have to make a pact with… Dwarfs!
Yes – the irony of your race, Dwarf, is you make beautiful things with such ugly hands.
Good, we will work together. You have surrendered your honour as I have my standards.
Yes, an accord. But something must be done with this 'grumpy-dour' aesthetic.
Very good, a change of pace to work with such ponderous creatures.
No… not in all my years have I sullied myself, and I do not intend to now. Be gone, Dwarf!
Tell your High-King that he and his filthy race will be scoured from the mountains!
I don't think so, Dwarf. Crawl back to your mountains and spare us all your hideous race.
No, Dwarf, there is no deal to be struck, just the destruction of your precious empire.
No-no, how could I ally with you. I'd hurt my neck looking down all the time.
I apologise I just can't make this work! Better to wipe you out.
So be it! I will ally with Sigmar's bastards. Let the Dark Prince judge if this is wise.
A temporary alliance is all I'm will to ascent to. After all, your realm is not long for the world.
Yes – a treaty – my father seems very keen. But then he expects I'll betray you, and I wouldn't want to disappoint Him.
That will do, Sons of Sigmar, you have made your case – now we talk about the wergild owed.
Very well, this suits my purposes.
Agreed, but let us not get carried away.
Never! I will have this Franz prone at my feet, kissing my boots and praying to be ended!
No, I rarely show anger, for my perfection prevents me – but my rage is close, mortal…
There is little point. That fool, Archaon – even my master has a soft spot for him - plans to decimate your lands.
No, I never liked this Sigmar you all love so much. Seems like a right show off to me.
I know true value when I see it, my own reflection is but one example. So this is not good value.
I may be the acceptable face of the Chaos Legions, but don't mistake me for a soft touch, mortal, others have made that fatal mistake.
A pact then! But only while it serves my interest, then I shall see you all exterminated.
Yes, as much as it galls me! A curse on your filthy race all the same.
So we shall, but I have no patience for your kind. Betray me and you'll all be put to the blade.
Agreed – now get from my presence before I retch!
Why not? After all, the most beautiful thing in the world is spilling blood, and these creatures do it so well.
Yes, very well, as long as your brutes stay out of my sight, we have a pact.
Never, Orcs! Why would I even dream of tainting my hordes with your filth!
Sigvald the Magnificent does not work with Greenskins! That is all you need to know, worm!
No, there is only one solution for a problem like yours, Orc – that’s to cleanse the world of your insufferable taint.
By the Dark Prince, no! Absolutely not! I'd rather ally with those disgusting Dwarf creatures than Orcs!
Ugh, no… just no!
A novel suggestion… but I would rather pull out mine own eyes than have to look at you every day.
No, why would I ally with something so disgusting? I may be forced to kill you.
Fawners! Bring me Sliverslash – I am in a dark mood and need to bathe in the blood of this emissary.
Never, you are vile and I must purge the mortal plane of your unsightliness.
Don't mistake me for a fool just because I mean to look good as I kill every last one of you.
No, I don't need your help. After all, I am divine and you are not, mortal.
Your offer insults me. Don't gawp – I'll cut you down before you can even fashion a response.
Oh, sorry, your armour has a sheen to it, and I caught my reflection in there… There is no deal – my hair is untidy!
No, I could never ally with such ugliness. The aesthetics are just too wrong.
No-no, this won't do. I need utter obsequence, you seem far too unruly for that.
Hmm, I do not like this, but my master instructs me so. It will be a joy to betray you at some point.
I cannot abide this situation, but I cannot ignore circumstances – pray, do not take advantage, creature.
Agreed, but if you displease me, I'll show what preternatural speed truly is.
Yes, an agreement is possible – but keep your rotten servants away from me.
Yes, Vampire and Chaos is an irresistible combination.
I'll accept, on the condition that you don't wear a red cape again – it really clashes with your deathly pallor.
Mannfred goes too far – the Undead have no rights on what is already claimed by the Dark Prince!
No, back to the graves with you, or I'll put you all back myself!
What a ridiculous notion - Undead, as an ally? I'd rather ask a favour from a Plaguebearer!
You test me, Vampire. Very unwise – it'll lead to your permanent death!
No, I'm afraid the lack of mirrors around here really puts me off.
How very droll, but I simply can't get over the stench around you and your… kin. So it's a no.
It is a deal I am not happy with, but the God of Magic demands it so.
Agreed, but keep a Collar of Khorne around your neck!
I have signed your fetid contract, but do not think you can entrap me within its words!
The Grand Manipulator has bought us together - it is best not to fight his will.
Yes, the treaty is signed - ours is a force the world will fear!
The covenant is agreed. Prepare your forces, mortal, as I will mine.
Yes, we have an agreement - one witnessed by the Dark Gods!
There is deep power in what we make this day. I have foreseen it!
Excellent, I'll send word to the Blue Scribes, so they may put it to record.
I accept but only to see the carnage of Bretonnia's destruction up close.
So it will be. For agreeing this I do more to usher obliteration than refusing you, Bretonnian!
I will agree - but the cost to you is great, Bretonnian.
Yes, and I will suck the lifeforce from every place you deem sacred in recompense!
Why not? There is much magic to drain from your lands.
Good, we shall feast, but not on anything as mundane as food. No, power is my sustenance...
I have no time for your stilted backwater realm. It will be consumed and dominated by Chaos!
Never - your king will be my plaything, and I will break every last Knight that comes to challenge me!
No, mortals, you are insignificant. However, your lands hold some eldritch value - I will take them anyway.
I care nothing for the fate of Bretonnia! Prepare your souls - for they are forfeit!
What insipid folk you are - tell your king I am disappointed!
No, not when I can mutate your horses from under you or melt your gleaming armour. I see no reason to treat with you.
Yes - I dominate here! Witness my scintillating fires and bow before your new Lord.
The bargain is struck, you will belong to me, there is no point fighting it, fool!
Very well, we shall work as one. Yet do not forget whose master brought us together.
Yes, I'll will bring the raw might of Chaos magick, in return you must provide a Mutalith Vortex Beast!
Yes! The quivering souls of the southerners just felt icy fingers upon them.
The deal is struck - we will bring misery to hundreds of thousands!
Never - your brutal ways are the methods of a rabid dog who needs putting down!
No, fool, I am the puppet master and you are the doll to be burnt in the fires of seven hells!
I refuse - you're horde does not suit my needs.
No, creature, I have access to the fates. Your destiny is far too mundane.
Alas, no, I sense a great disturbance that would shatter any alliance.
No, mine is not to question why, but this treaty is forbidden by our masters.
Yes, but I'll have every tome of knowledge from your dusty shelves in payment!
So be it, but don't think I'll spare you when the scourging of these Holds truly begins!
Good, Dwarf. It pleases me greatly to see how easily you bend to my will!
I'll take your offer, Dwarf, knowing that you have cursed your family name for generations to come!
Agreed. Your shame is your own to deal with, Dwarf, I care not!
Ha - it is pleasing to see how you cast off your lauded honour to gain the benefits of my lore.
No - Valaya was a withered hag whose prophecies couldn't even alter the fate of a door-slave.
The Dwarfs are already dead. They are just too stubborn to accept it!
No! I don't need your permission to pick the secrets from Valaya's scorched bones!
The Grudgebearer and his kind are forsaken! What you claim to have I will take!
No - I have nothing against such stunted creatures - but the Changer of Fates has decreed their end.
You must accept the inevitable, Dwarf - the Karaz Ankor is forsaken.
My services, yes, for the gifts of mutation, mutilation, putrefaction and the songs of a cacophonic choir.
We have a pact. Now you will see the true power of the Winds - your pitiful lores are nothing in comparison!
The End Times come and nothing you do can change it - so there is little harm in an alliance...
Oh, this is good! Prostrate yourselves, yes. We have a pact, Empire fool!
Good-good, now we can work in harmony for once.
At last you see the light, men of the Empire. Now all you need do is embrace change…
It is the eve of the End Times, Empire scum, there is nothing I cannot take from you.
No - Franz will die choking on his own blood, I have foreseen it!
I think not, I would not deign to any such deal with Sigmar's crippled offspring!
I bring change! Glorious, mutable change! There is no need for such strict pacts anymore.
No, your nation is founded on lies - Sigmar Unberogen was nothing but a tribesman with a hammer!
There is no deal, the Empire is doomed - Tzeentch has promised me so.
Yes, these limited creatures will have some use.
I have my doubts, Orc, but if you disappoint me, I can always twist off your head!
Very well, Orc. See it is done!
The pact is sealed - dance or scream, as you see fit. The screams of other mortals will start soon enough!
Agreed, Orc, but spare me your boasts or yelps of wonder, I have my own words to recite.
Very well, Greenskin, my arcane might be added to your brutish force.
No, beast, there is no pact. Tzeentch places no value on your insignificant kind.
There is no reality - no material plane - where you could be of use to me, Greenskin!
I shan't waste my words on you, Orc - the answer is no!
There is no point, Orc - come the End Times you will be marked for slaughter along with all other things.
A laughable notion! Be gone, before I turn you to spawn, Orc thing!
No, I will not sully my master's vision by working with your ilk!
Now you'll incur my wrath, little mortal, and I do not forgive or forget!
Insufferable! I am surrounded by fools who dare to think they can hire me like some tradesman?
My services are not for you, worm - they are to rid this plane of your ilk!
I have no time for you - this coven will not be!
No, your desires are of little consequence to me.
How could such a deal be brokered? You have nothing I want, mortal!
I saw that you would come, but the fates have only just cleared and I must reject your advance.
You proffer tempting considerations… but the time is not now.
No, I have not the wherewithal to share power with you.
Yes-yes, bring forth the bands of enslavement! I will have you as my own, Vampire!
A blood pact is made and bound with impossible magicks, to break them is to forfeit whatever passes for your soul, creature!
Yes, there is a twisted logic in working together that will please the Dark Gods.
Agreed, we are both puppet masters, although my strings are longer.
Very well, our dread forces shall unite!
I have conversed with a Lord of Change - he thinks it wise to accept.
No, Vampire - take your weak minions and flee my wrath, it will not be to your aristocratic tastes.
You are a still-born abomination, nothing more than a marionette on a string I can cut.
No, Vampire - your kind have had their chance, now you must reap what you sow along with all the rest.
You are naught but an empty vessel - the Chaos Gods have no use for flasks and beakers.
How vexing, but I must decline - Chaos is the only power.
Your offer is pitiful - come back to me when you realise my true potential.
On behalf of the Celestial Emperor, thank you.
May you forever know harmony.
Your respect is noted.
Then we are in harmony.
The Winds have guided you well.
It is an honour.
Only a fool would slight the Celestial Dragon!
You know not what you do.
Why would you incite the wrath of Dragons?
Your crude offence will be remembered.
Xen Yang is watching. He notes this snub.
You are witless indeed to reject Grand Cathay.
So be it. The Celestial Empire shall prevail as always.
We have no fear, for the Emperor watches over us.
Those who pursue disharmony pay a heavy price.
The Celestial Empire has no need of desperate wretches.
You have served your purpose. The Emperor needs you no longer.
This contract brings only disharmony.
Stand with Cathay! Shine Celestial light upon our foes!
The Dragon Emperor calls upon you!
Aid our glorious cause! Restore harmony!
The debt must be paid. Harmony must be restored. Do not dare refuse.
It is time to repay Xen Yang's kindness.
Alas, even the Celestial treasury is not bottomless.
For you to live, the Celestial Empire must grow.
We can seize your lands by force, or you can choose a simpler path.
Surrender this realm and you may know harmony once more.
Our Emperor speaks through me. You know the price of refusing him.
Heed me well, turncoat, or you will suffer Xen Yang's immortal wrath.
Think upon this, for my cause is our beloved Emperor's cause.
For the good of all Cathay, hear me now!
Emperor's blessings upon you. What say you to this?
May we one before Xen Yang. There is much to discuss.
Heed this well, Daemon, or be immolated by the Emperor's light!
You can listen, or you can join the countless others of your kind slain by Cathay.
Hear the voice of harmony, Daemon!
The Great Enemy would be wise to listen.
Of all your hell-sent kind, you alone will understand.
I trust our Great Enemy is in a receptive mood?
Hear Xen Yang's decree or be obliterated, fiend!
You who are disharmony incarnate must accede, or destruction follows.
Will you hear the Dragon's word, Daemon?
There need be no slaughter, merely discussion.
Think upon this, Daemon. It may benefit us both.
May the eight Winds blow in your favour, fiend. What say you to this?
Heed Cathay's decree, little empire of the ice, or your story ends.
Obey the Dragon, or Kislev will become but a whisper upon the snow.
Humans and Dragons are often in accord. Let this be one of those times.
I bring the Emperor's word to the children of Ursun.
May the Motherland know only harmony. Now, what say you?
The Emperor sends warm blessings to cold Kislev, and this decree.
Heed this well, for none can survive the Dragon Emperor's wrath!
Ignore us and know disharmony eternal.
History is littered with the corpses of those who refused Cathay.
This is Xen Yang's decree! Hearken to it, or know obliteration!
The Emperor will not be ignored. I suggest you do not test this.
The Emperor's wisdom is infinite. Heed His words well.
This is the Celestial Dragon's decree.
I speak for all Cathay. We are not accustomed to being refused.
Heed this well, and know harmony.
Hear me now, for the will of the Dragon flows through me.
Accede to Cathay, rotted one, or we shall expunge your stain.
Heed the Emperor's decree, or His light shall cleanse your infection!
Let us discuss what we must, Daemon of rot.
Keep your distance, diseased one, and hear Xen Yang's commandment.
I know you are more receptive than others of your ilk, Daemon.
May you know whatever form harmony takes for your kind. Now, to other matters.
Accede to Cathay, brute, else we shall press you into service.
Xen Yang almost destroyed your kind once. Ignore Him at your peril.
When the Emperor speaks, even the mountain boors must listen.
Stay your fists, Ogre. I bring you the Dragon's decree.
I bring you a selection of finest meats, and the Emperor's divine word.
Greetings, my mighty neighbour. What say you to this?
May you know harmony all your life, friend. Will you hear me?
The Dragon wishes you well, and sends this pronouncement.
Eight Winds guide you always. What think you of this?
Let our minds be as one as we discuss pressing matters.
Cathay values your friendship, and brings this before you.
Degenerate fiend! Accede to Cathay or face oblivion!
Listen well, or this world will suffer the Great Enemy's perversions no longer.
Tear yourself from your perversions and hear the Emperor's word.
Come, gadabout, and know the Dragon's behest.
May you know pleasure through harmony. Now hear this!
We tolerate you as you tolerate us, Daemon, and now must talk.
Chi'an Chi will obey the Emperor, or Chi'an Chi will be eradicated.
Heed Xen Yang or lose your lying tongue, worm.
Offer your answer, and tell no lies.
The Celestial Empire would have words with Chi'an Chi.
Welcome, changer. Perhaps this would suit your design?
Please send Cathay's regards to Chi'an Chi, and this proposal.
