You trespass in the Emperor's domain! Do you crave death?
Cathay is no thoroughfare! Begone, or know the fury of Dragons!
You are unwelcome here. Leave or face armies beyond all imagining.
One may enter the Celestial Empire only with a Dragon's permission.
You tread in the Emperor's kingdom without invitation.
Cathay's ancestors cry out in protest at your presence here.
Align yourselves with us, and know glorious harmony!
Rejoice, for the Emperor has chosen you!
Let us make a pact, for the benefit of all.
An accord between us will earn you the Dragon's favour.
Sign this treaty and you will know Xen Yang's immortal love.
Our Emperor wishes to see us united. We must not disappoint him.
In the name of the great Dragon, we must seek alignment.
Let there be some measure of harmony between us, Daemon.
Will the Great Enemy make this pact with us?
This will benefit us both, blood fiend.
Your murderous god knows this to be a prudent arrangement.
The enemies of Chaos must seek alignment.
Let Dragons and bears seek accord!
The Celestial and the contagious!
The Emperor chooses you, decayed one.
Let there be friendship between us, vast one.
We seek an arrangement with the hungry children of the Maw.
Will you work with us, Daemon of desire?
Co-operate with us, and we need not mention your degeneracy again.
Your dark master of sorcery sees the wisdom in this.
Cathay would co-operate with great Chi'an Chi.
A mark of the Dragon Emperor's respect.
From the Celestial Court's treasury to yours.
Coins of sun and coins of moon, our gift to you.
We would lend our might to yours, for your enemies are Cathay's enemies.
The Emperor would never abandon His allies.
Let harmony fight by your side!
Harmony must be restored.
Further bloodshed aids neither of us.
The Emperor decrees peace!
The Celestial Dragon despises suffering. Let this war end!
Lay down your weapons, and Cathay will trouble you no more.
Our Emperor weeps to see us so divided. Let there be peace!
This war shames our ancestors. I say no more!
The Emperor will forgive His Great Enemy, if it will end this war.
No more of this folly, Daemon!
I cannot bear to see more Cathayan blood spilled.
Let there be a truce, if your brutal god will permit it.
The threat of Chaos is too grave to blunt our blades upon each other.
Let this ill will between us pass, Kislevite. The Emperor will forgive.
Return to your foetid garden. There need be no more death.
We would prefer to be as far from your poxes as possible. No more war!
Our appetite for war is slaked. Is yours, Ogre?
We are not meat for your foul maws. Let this conflict end!
Relent, fiend, and Cathay shall do the same.
I can bear no more of your depravity. There must be peace!
Will Chi'an Chi consider a truce?
You have wisdom as well as cruelty, Daemon. Accept peace!
A fraction of the Celestial Empire is yours, if you will lay down arms.
Grand Cathay will provide, but you must promise peace.
Take it. Cathay has countless lands, countless peoples.
The Dragon will show mercy, if you will show sense.
Pay sufficient tribute to the Celestial Emperor and we will take pity.
Harmony will return only once you have made things right.
This is not the Emperor's will.
I am the authority here! I capitulate to no-one!
The Moon Dragon would weep at such weakness.
It cannot be so. The Emperor requires your obliteration.
Only with your destruction can there be harmony.
To show mercy today would doom Cathay tomorrow.
The Emperor is benevolent, but cannot forgive treachery.
Your actions bring disharmony to Cathay. They cannot go unpunished.
The Great Enemy must be resisted, always.
Denied, for the Emperor will suffer no Daemon to live.
Not until the gates of hell are closed forever!
Monster! There can be no mercy for your kind!
With regret, no. Kislev stands in Xen Yang's way.
No, for malice will soon return to your cold heart.
You are a threat to all that lives. There can be no clemency.
Cathay is the only cure for your disease. We cannot stop now.
As long as you hunger, you remain a threat. I have no choice.
Too many Cathayans have lined your belly. We cannot forgive this.
No peace with sin incarnate!
No! You bring too much suffering!
Chi'an Chi cannot be trusted! Not now, not ever!
We will not be deceived by your dark machinations, Daemon!
The Emperor has long known that war must come. To arms!
Though it means disharmony, Cathay must march to war.
You must die. The Dragon Emperor has spoken.
For blessed harmony to return, your dark reign must end.
Cathay's people rise against you, guided by their ancestors.
You have betrayed the Celestial Empire. The sentence is death.
In the name of immortal Xen Yang, all traitors must die!
The time has come. The Great Enemy must die.
It is my duty to stand against Chaos, no matter the cost.
Prepare yourself, Daemon! Annihilation comes!
Foul destroyer! Your time is at an end!
Prepare yourself for war, Kislevite. It is a sad necessity.
Fool Bear-worshippers! You are the enemies of reason! There must be war!
Not one more infection! That is my pledge!
Nauseating slave to Ruination! Your time has come!
Your barbarism threatens all. Your tribe must be removed.
I will finish the job Xen Yang began centuries ago.
You have consumed your last soul, fiend!
No more sin! No more evil! I will bring harmony!
Chi'an Chi can corrupt no more minds. To arms!
It must be war, wicked one. Your evil cannot remain.
What do the emissaries of that haughty, mewling witch dare to demand?
The lake-hag and her puppet-king deign to treat with me? You best spit out your offer - be quick!
What do you want, Bretonnian? If it's a reprieve for your nation of fools and maggots then you will be disappointed!
Bretonnia and its laughable patrons will be swept away as if the lake-hag had been pulled out to sea.
I have been here before - I slaughtered Baron Lucus, just as I will do you, if it pleases me.
Bretonnia - such a backwater! Yet the Gods degree it must be conquered… Go on, make your plea.
Do you bring the Kurgan, fool? Without their backing you have no bargaining power.
I am the Everchosen, bend the knee or I will take your heart and slaughter your entire retinue.
What do you want, putrid cretin? Don't mistake this parley for anything else - the Gods favour me!
Step before me and pledge your fealty, weakling! Then the Everchosen will deign to hear you.
I welcome your visit, champion, now show your allegiance… before the Everchosen.
You seek the Lord of the End Times - you have my attention.
The Sons of Grungni are indeed weak these days to come snivelling at my boots, begging for favour.
The Dwarfs have ever-been feeble bearded Goblins, stubbornly holding onto a faded Empire.
Speak in your broken tongue, Dwarf, I'll savage you whether it is in Khazalid or Reikspiel.
Stunted creature – I doubt you can offer me anything that I can't take anyway.
Come stunted creature, I gladly accommodate the betrayal of your honour, your clan and Ancestors!
Such desperation for the Dwarfs to visit me. Do they not know the End Times approach?
Ha! You think your pathetic god scares me - I am the Warhammer incarnate!
When the time is right I will gut all of you in full view of your simpering armies - this is my only answer, mortal!
Is this what the Empire sends to parley? The leavings from its little zoo? Return them as Spawn!
Sigmar's Empire interests me less and less. It is the whole world I demand, not his pathetic corner.
Welcome, Lords of a false god. You do realise you worship a lie, don't you?
Ha! I used to be like you! Blinkered. Mayhaps we can work an alliance on this sole occasion.
Simpering Fools! You dare come before me - the Lord of the End Times!
Speak through your meek mouths, mumble your pitiable words so I can use them as a lash to flay your soul!
What could you possibly offer me, mewling spawn - I am Everchosen!
Speak your words, while I still deign to listen, mortal scum!
The Eye of Sheerian has already told me your offer, but I will hear it from your lips all the same.
Bow before the Lord of the End Times, mortal. Only then will I hear you…
Greetings, your abasement pleases me.
Yes, bow down before He who wields the Slayer of Kings!
You catch me in a moment of less rage, creature - I may spare your soul…
Greenskin filth! What is your message, and tell me why I do not reap your disgusting soul where you stand?
Orc insect! Your race refuses to die no matter how hard I stamp on you. Speak then - I may yet have a use for you.
What does the creature want? Get it to speak before I rip its feeble head from its shoulders.
Deliver your message, Greenskin, and then pray to your demented gods I am in a mood to take heed.
Time is short, but I will talk to this green thing - what do you want, creature?
Come then, Greenskin, utter your demand. You have my attention, but I warn you, it is fleeting…
You title yourself Count or Lord but it doesn't make you one, grave-feeder. I am the undisputed Lord of the End Times!
You are irrelevant, Vampire! Nothing but a withered soul clinging to mortal remains. I will dominate you!
The arrogance of the Undead astounds me! You are hollow, and therefore have no value to me.
What do you want, grave-feeder, have you run out of tombs to lurk in?
Vampires! Grave-scum, I have little interest in your petty power games, what is it you want?
Come, counts, abase yourselves before me - bend the knee and we'll talk.
Yours lands, your forest, your castles… all with be ash. So issue your message, it is meaningless.
I despise those who believe in some lake-hag! I don't need to hear your herald. Your time is over!
What does the Bretonnian king want with a Lord of Chaos? Does he beg for his pitiful life?
I'll hear your words, mannish creature. If the message displease me, I'll strangle you with your own tongue.
Bretonnian - how is your pathetic little nation?
That's right, Knight, say your prayers, I hope that wench you worship can hear you, she is doomed too.
You think you'll reach Daemonhood before me? Best pray to our masters that apotheosis happens soon…
Make your offer, and I'll have you bound to it - within a runic shard if I have to!
What do you want? Do not expect me to bow, I only bend the knee to the Dark Gods, not their pretenders.
What does my fellow Lord desire, I wonder? Does the Changer bring you here, or the God of Murder…
My fellow warlords converge here! Do the Kurgan and the Tong come south?
Greetings, let us forgo the usual rituals; straight to business, what is the soul-tally?
Dwarfs! What a putrid race! Your Empire withers, your mountains crumble, what could you offer me?
Bearded wretches – that is what I see before me! Get on your pinguid bellies, Dwarf, and plead!
Dwarf-scum! I knew you would come crawling upon your fat bellies, dragging your beards in filth.
Sons of Grungni – when did you get so weak, so pathetic?
Does the Karaz Ankor struggle so badly that Dwarfs must come begging for leniency?
Dwarfs, know that your crumbling empire holds no interest, that alone, may glean you a tiny advantage.
At last we come to the Empire - poxes, pain, mutation and murder will be my legacy!
Tremble, Empire-man - what the Black-Iron Reaver did to Volganof is nothing compared to my plans.
The Sons of Sigmar Unberogen - you have fallen so far since your first Emperor has been lost…
The time of Franz and all Emperors is at an end, so speak your words, but know that all is Chaos!
Time is short, get of Sigmar - spit out your demand, and the matter of your death shall then be discussed.
You will betray your nation. You will succumb to Chaos, and become my minion - Tzeentch has foreseen it!
I have stepped into the Realm of Chaos and returned - there is nothing you can say that will bring mercy!
All mortals are as significant to me as worms in rotting mud, so why should I listen to you?
The Ruinous Powers demand your utter destruction! What can you possibly say to forestall this?
You can talk at me, mortal, but that will not change anything. Your cities will be razed, claimed by Khorne.
I'll hear you out, but know that you stink of fear. I will use that when we 'negotiate' this pact.
Now, is the crucible of your actions, think hard, mortal - the fate of your soul hangs in the balance.
Welcome, mayhaps we can barter for the souls of those you represent?
You come before me, as a penitent. This tickles me; I may be merciful, and not torture you for as long.
Your life is forfeit. If you accept that, we can make a pact that will see all satisfied.
What Orc? Speak your guttural tones while I consider the many ways I could have you slain.
I will hear you out, Greenskin, but I tire of your species, so this pledge better interest me.
Orcs - that is all I need! What do you want Greenskin? Say something to stop me cutting you down!
Mork and Gork, isn't it? Your feeble gods? Will they save you when I take your head for speaking ill?
Why must I fraternise with Greenskins? They offer little but to wear my patience!
What does the Orc want? What could it possibly offer me?
Come at me, Vampire! Taste my blood if you dare - I promise it will be you that suffers, not me.
You come here proclaiming greatness - you're nothing but a bothersome plague-fly, to be crushed between my fingers.
Once more the Vampires come, seeking a pact and recognition - like a dog trying to please its master…
You Undead are noisome, clogging up the lands with soulless vessels - what do you want?
Greetings, Lords of Night, you come to parley with some hold over me? You will be disappointed.
Vampires, you are the bane of mortals? Haha! Is that what you believe? A curious notion…

Vampires, you are the bane of mortals? Haha! Is that what you believe? A curious notion…
Speak, you craven cur, and pray to whatever thing you dare to call a God, I do not cut your guts out.
You seek a pact with Norscan tribes? Then you are either fool or coward… either way I shall see you dead.
Diseased dogs! Present yourselves so I may put you out of your misery!
You come to Norsca, don't expect to leave!
I do not recognise your foreign garb - are you of the Hung or Kurgan?
We meet at Doomkeep - there you can make your case to the tribes!
Why do you come to the frozen north?
My tribe is open to your offer, do not disappoint them…
Dark blessings upon you - what gifts do you seek in Norsca?
You wish the wrath of the Norse tribes? That is the only reason I find for you to stand before me!
I'm touched by the Eagle and the Crow - I perceive all, and I see you for what you are!
Coward! You come before me pleading a pact the Norse have no need, for us there is just death!
Do not mistake this for anything more that a bid to bring us favour. If the Gods command it, we destroy you.
You seek the Norse: I am their shaman, their mage… their sorcerer. They follow my whim…
The terms of the pact - I'll hear them now!
You prize Norsca, I see - it can be yours but at a great cost!
With what do you bargain?
The Dark Gods look down on your offer with interest, as do the Norse.
The mewling King of Bretonnia sends me envoys - how pitiful! What is your message, worm?
Speak, Bretonnian, but my attention wanes and I have little time for insects…
I hear Bretonnia fairs poorly. I would feel sorry for you, but I do so enjoy slaughtering your population.
Bretonnia: the bastard nation of the Old World – so unloved. Let's change your fortunes – make a pact…
I have a soft spot for folk who go to war with so much soft furnishings…
Bretonnian, you come before me pronouncing such pitiful, sycophantic gestures… Do go on.
What do you want? Does your tribe come to me for succour? You'll find nought but a dried teat!
Do you honestly think you can tempt me away from mine Dark Prince? You and your master are a fool!
Yes, gaze on this pulchritudinous form, and then beg for my favour, warlord…
Slaanesh insists I attend, but do not test my patience with meaningless threats- it gets very dull.
Welcome, Warrior of Chaos. Before you even ask, yes, you may bow before the Geld-Prince!
Greetings, fellow ravager of the mortal realm! What can Sigvald the Magnificent do for you this fine day?
Not these troglodytes again! What could you bearded things possibly offer the Geld-Prince?
Bear in mind, Dwarf, I have seen your mother, and even Nurgle could not manifest such a hideous visage.
Dwarfs! Do you go out willingly with all the disgusting hair drooping from your face?
Come, Dwarf, I need you obsequence, and I have no desire to spend any longer in your stench.
You are some kind of hairy Goblin creatures, yes? How amusing! What do you want?
Dwarfs, I have killed many, so it might be fun to work with you for a change.
The arrogance of the Empire is legendary! How dare they think to approach me, thy humble prince of a loving God!
Do you challenge me, Empire-men? Do you seek to humble me in front of my father? We'll see…
A message from your Emperor? How quaint! I'll hear it... Pardon my chuckles though.
Well, let us hear your offer, envoy, and then you can tell how you wish to be flayed – alive or dead?
Emissaries of Franz, tell me, what helmet  plumes is he affecting this season?
Maybe we can come to some accommodation with the Empire? It would be such a shame to despoil it.
Avert your eyes, grotesquery – I forbid you to look upon this beautiful visage!
Do not test me, repellent fool – this handsome face hides it well, but I'm wiser than you know.
How vexing! Your sycophantic overtures annoy me, so hurry up with your offer!
Yes, you may look upon my beatific features and marvel – many do. When you have finished, pray, tell me your wants?
You have a proposal, yes? Good, I do so hate murderous rage before lunch.
Well, introduce yourself, obsequious creatures, I already bore of this ruse.
Well this is simply marvellous! More playthings to talk to! Tell me your desires.
My true father instructs me to talk to you. It seems we may have common cause.
Yes, I am handsome, but we must forgo the usual flattery - a deal needs to be struck.
What have you to say, vile beast? Speak fast I can already feel my gorge rising!
Greenskins! No wonder I despise that colour, such a noxious tone…
This could be over very quickly, as I'm sworn to kill anything that ugly within sight.
Orcs dare to stand before me! It makes me nauseous. Hand me my sword so I may resolve this!
What a foul beast! Although, being in your presence reinforces mine own beauty, so speak on, Orc!
Orc, you sully my mood just looking at you, best speak your message quickly.
If I must talk to the Undead, let them do it in bright sunlight, so they may take in my comeliness!
Vile, ugly creatures, unfettered from life, why do you seek parley, with 'The Magnificent'!
What is your message, Liche? I have little time for such ugly things.
I've no interest in the Undead, my master wishes to claim more vigorous souls – so speak quickly.
Ahh, Vampires, we share some of the same tastes – I'm sure I could also carry off the 'faded grandeur' look.
Such gloomy surroundings, no wonder you grave-feeders are always in such a sour mood.
What could you tempt me with? Bretonnian, your fey weak, water sprite doesn’t scare me.
I cannot abide your realm, Man-child - even though it is built on a lie that thrills my god!
Bretonnians - the End Times come and I find you in my way.
Tell me, where is your Green Knight? He is Bretonnia incarnate, is he not? He can answer for your sins!
Welcome, Bretonnian - where is my hospitality? Ah, it is lost, with the hopes and dreams of your nation.
We could barter - but you must know, deep in your hearts, that your salvation is a lost cause.
You mistake me for servant, when I am master, fool! Pay your tribute and be done!
What do the emaciated northern tribes want? They wish to leech at me, like some withered lamprey no doubt!
You seek parley… tell me have you read from the Liber Malefic? There are chapters within that tell of this meeting...
Ahh, the subtle threats - I'm quite partial to those myself, for I am in favour with the Great Deceiver.
Greetings friend, the Changer orders us to make peace, to fight common foes, who are we to go against His will?
There is much power to be had, many souls to reap - perhaps we could do it together?
Here come the stunted mewlers – so full of self-importance, yet nothing but Slaughterbrute fodder to me!
Thorgrim is nothing but a cripple in a stone chair still he sends his wittering, decrepit ancients to treat with me?
I'll hear you, Dwarf, but then you must hear my truths – that your kingdom shall be despoiled.
What does the Dwarf thing want? I won't speak to it directly it is – quite literally – below me.
Speak, Dwarf – in Khazalid if you must – it has been a while since I've heard its nauseating vowels.
Greetings, if your Runesmiths are ready to share their secrets, I will share my power.
Greetings, I know the fate of your Man-God - he died screaming, pleading for the Chaos Gods to take his soul…
Aberrations of Sigmar - you come to bargain, but what with? Your cities tumble, your citizens quail…
Scions of Sigmar, speak your message and then I'll share what my master has planned for your kind…
Why do the rabble listen to you? Because the office of Emperor means you hold a golden mallet? Let me show you true power, mortals!
Lords of the Empire, I bring a promise… your lives and those of your people will be saved, if we strike a deal.
Does the Emperor not see the trouble he sows? If only you'd come to a compact - send me souls and so much ruckus could be avoided.
You dare to summon the arcane might of a sorcerous Lord of Chaos?
I can bring the full power of arcane winds to bear, what could you offer me, little mortal?
You wish a covenant? There are many conditions to discuss first, fool! Let us start with your soul…
You stand before a sorcerer blessed by Tzeentch himself… make your case.
Untold power; if that's what you were promised, I can certainly provide it - but there is a cost!
There is no better spell-crafter than me! But I do not give my services willingly, I have requirements.
Hmm… What do the Winds of Magic blow to my portal?
There is a deal to be struck, but first I must know your real name - your true name - yes?
It is fortunate our paths crossed - I have seen your fate, perhaps, we can change it for the better?
Orcs, their horrific forms plague my sight again! What does it want?
Make your offer, Orc, so I may reject it and turn you into rancid pus for my Warhounds to drink!
What is your claim Greenskin? Pray to your bereft gods it impresses me.
There is so much to do, yet I am forced to parley with Greenskin filth!
I've felt the dull minds of Orcs, before! It tests my patience. What is your message, Greenskin?
Come Orc, what do your masters crave? Just this once, I'll see if our interests align.
You come to bargain, grave-feeder, but your arrogance belies the reality - you have nothing I need.
Speak, liche, say your words so I may rip them from this mortal plane and mutate them into sag-flies to crush!
Hush, Vampire! I have no need to heed your threats, my power surpasses yours!
Do not test me, Necromancer, yours is an art I have dominated centuries ago. I am its master!
I admit to mild admiration - the way you confound Morr by eluding death, it amuses me.
What is your offer, liche? I am open to terms.

What is your offer, liche? I am open to terms.
So you recognise the power of Chaos.
You save me the effort of seizing it from you.
These trinkets shall aid my Ruinous crusade.
Thus you acknowledge my immortal superiority.
You make yourself an ally of Ruin.
You are wise not to refuse Chaos.
You invite destruction, little wretch.
With this insult, my dread gaze falls upon your kingdom.
To spurn the mercy of Chaos is an act of madness.
You will regret this folly.
None incite my wrath and live.
The Ruinous Powers will not forget this offence.
Good, good! You accept that I must annihilate you.
I will willingly strip the flesh from your bones, little one
Abject fool! You truly believe you can destroy destruction itself?
I no longer see worth in you. Be grateful I do not obliterate you.
True Chaos has no need of others.
I must tread the path of Ruination alone.
Join destruction's cause and I shall grant mercy once the world is mine.
I promise glory! I promise power! I promise rivers of gore!
Let us bathe in the blood of our enemies! Let us wade knee-deep through their dead!
Sacrifice your wealth, or sacrifice your very being.
Surely a small price to pay for your continued existence?
Make your offering to the Dark Gods. Earn their Ruinous favour!
This land is the price of your continued existence.
What price your soul? A little land, perhaps?
An agonising death or the sacrifice of your realm: you must choose.
The Dragon's children rightly fear the wrath of Chaos. Do not dare spurn us now.
Accede to me, or I shall turn your preposterous wall to ash!
Long have Cathay and Chaos clawed at each other, but you must heed me now.
Put aside the Dragon's futile pride, and harken to the dread voice of Chaos!
The prince of Chaos would have words with the Dragons.
Though an ancient ocean of blood divides us, Cathay and Chaos must now find accord.
Obey me, little princeling, or I shall tear your dark gifts from you!
Accept me as your superior or perish, meagre Daemon.
There can be only one prince of Chaos. Accept now that it is I.
Harken to me. It is what our Dark Gods desire.
Hear me now, brother in darkness!
I am sent by our Gods, brother. Honour them by listening well.
Focus your savage mind upon my words, or I'll wear your skull as a crown.
Obey me or face annihilation, Khornate insect.
The children of blood must heed my call.
Wipe the blood-flecked drool from your muzzle and attend to my call.
I speak in the name of destruction. This is Khorne's cause too.
Greetings, my hell-sent kin. I seek the ear of the Skull Throne.
Though I yearn for Kislev's destruction, heed me and it may be delayed.
Accede to me or I shall scatter your frozen bones across the oblast!
Though I yearn for Kislev's destruction, heed me and I may relent.
Attend to my offer. Even your absurd Bear knows this to be wise.
Grant me audience, children of Ursun.
I retain certain… sympathies for Kislev. This is why you must listen.
Accede to the avatar of annihilation!
Hear me now, or suffer unimaginable torment.
If you value your spine, heed the voice of Chaos!
You will listen, or you will be destroyed.
Obedience or obliteration: choose wisely.
You can see my power. You can see that you must listen.
Show wisdom, and attend to my offer.
I strongly suggest that you accede to my request.
The prince of Ruination would have words with you.
There need be no destruction, if you will only listen.
Obey me, lest I scrub your noxious filth from this land.
You will become but a mouldering smear unless you heed me.
Clean the filth from your ears and hear me!
Open your festering mind to my words.
Hear me now, o champion of decay!
Heed my call, plague child, for it too serves destruction's cause.
Listen now, brute, lest I build my throne from your bones.
Your paltry tribe shall become but a distant memory should you ignore me.
Chaos bears no grievance towards Ogres, but you must listen.
The mountain gluttons would be wise to heed my words.
Hear me now, proud Ogre. It is what your Great Maw desires.
Accede to my request and a great feast is certain.
I bear you no enmity, if you will but listen.
I have a suggestion, born of my immortal wisdom.
I have no desire to annihilate you, but I would have words.
The avatar of Chaos requires your consideration.
I pause from destruction to bring this before you.
Heed me or know suffering beyond even your imagining!
You are nothing, little Slaaneshi, and you will obey me!
I would have words with the Dark Prince's consort.
The pleasure of acceptance or the pain of refusal: you may choose.
This will lead to great excess, I assure you.
The sensation of compliance will bring you endless pleasure.
Refuse me and I shall impale you upon the spires of the Impossible Fortress.
No scheme can save you should you dare to ignore me.
Tzeentch knows what I want, and He knows that I will have it.
Look into the Well Of Eternity, and see that I must be heard.
Let the Raven God's all-seeing eye fall upon me.
Harken, noble changeling, for my suggestion aids the Great Game.
Begone from my immortal kingdom, or know oblivion!
Every moment you trespass on my lands stokes my immortal wrath further.
Leave here now, or I will grant you an eternity of suffering!
You tread where you do not belong.
Cease this trespass!
You come to my blood-soaked realm without invitation. Leave!
Join me on Ruination's path.
Become part of the Dark Gods' design.
This world will soon bow before me. Your co-operation now will be rewarded.
Though peace is anathema to Chaos, I see value in our alignment.
The prince of Chaos treats you as an equal: the rarest of honours.
Perhaps our ancient enmity with the Dragon was… misguided.
Let the Great Bastion no longer divide us.
Together, we can shatter this world, and earn the Gods' favour!
We are avatars of destruction both; thus we must aid each other.
I offer this invitation to the Skull Throne. Carnage is assured.
We should aid each other, for it will bring forth torrents of blood.
I know well what the Motherland needs, and so I offer it assistance.
The children of Ursun would be wise to co-operate with Chaos.
Join with me and this world will know endless decay.
Accept this invitation and the fester shall pour forth!
Align yourselves with Chaos and you shall feast as never before.
Turn your limited mind to co-operation and endless wealth shall be yours.
Alignment with me shall bring you hitherto unimagined sensations.
A treaty between us ensures Excess In All Things.
It is more than a treaty. It is a scheme within a scheme within a scheme.
Join me in this, that we both might wreak devastating Change across the land.
You can surely make use of these trinkets.
Gold is a poor substitute for power, but perhaps it will benefit you.
I trust you will spend this on rampant destruction?
How I hunger for bloodshed! Please, permit me to join you.
There is no war I would not gladly be a part of.
I would fight beside you, harvesting countless souls for my Ruinous masters.
More fulfilling paths to Ruination await me, thus I would leave this one.
I have sated my thirst for your blood. Let us seek fresh victims.
Come now, there is no need for more of your kind to die.
Though they would relish your annihilation, the Ruinous Powers have other plans for me.
I do not call it peace. I call it merely a cessation of carnage.
Let us stain your Great Bastion with no more blood, for I have greater concerns.
The Dragon has earned my dread respect. He need fight me no more.
Our war has been most entertaining, but let us squander no more Daemons.
The Great Game now requires an end to our in-fighting.
Make claim on mortal skulls, not those of fellow Daemons.
Our feud leaves far too many mortals unslaughtered, no?
Enough of this! Chaos cares not about your Motherland.
My talons are steeped in sufficient Kislevite blood.
Let the Fly Lord know I demand armistice.
Waste no more of your poxes on Daemon kin.
Daemon flesh will not nourish you. Seek other prey!
Your brutality has impressed me, Ogre, but this distraction must end.
Entertain the temptation of peace, Slaaneshi.
Let us bestow glorious suffering upon the mortals, not one another.
Move on from this, to the next of Tzeentch's grand schemes.
Our war is a madness even the Raven would disapprove of.
I am prepared to make a sacrifice.
Let this buy an end to distraction from my ambitions.
A piece of my dread kingdom, if you will leave me be.
Show sense, and you need not face obliteration.
Grant me what I ask, or I shall tear it from you.
It is this or your spine. Choose wisely, insect.
The prince of Chaos has no need of others. Not now, not ever!
You are so far beneath me that I am barely aware of you.
Are you truly fool enough to think Daemons play well with others?
Peace is anathema to all that Chaos is!
Absurd! I will not rest until all are slaughtered.
You may know peace when I have torn your head from your shoulders.
Never! For centuries of slights against Chaos, the Dragon must die!
Absolutely not, for Cathay's Great Bastion is a trophy I cannot resist.
We must not deny our Ruinous masters the bloodshed they crave.
I must show you the true face of Chaos, pretender.
Your craven request shames the Murder God!
Preposterous that you would so soon abandon your hunt for skulls.
Never! I crave Kislev's destruction above all others!
Not until the Ice Court is scorched from this land!
Peace? Absurd! You surely succumb to your own Grey Fever.
No peace until your pitiful stain is scrubbed from this realm!
I enjoy slaughtering Ogres far too much to stop now.
Rank cowardice from the mountain brutes? How disappointing.
Peace is beyond tedious, as your Perfect Prince would surely agree.
But I have so much more suffering to grant you…
Even great Tzeentch himself could not turn my mind from war.
I see through your scheme, and I will not fall prey to it!
Destruction shall reign!
The time of your annihilation is nigh!
All that I am burns for slaughter, and you shall be my next victim.
I will tolerate no obstacles to my endless ambition, thus you must die.
My dread throne room requires a rug. Your hide shall suffice.
Chaos will suffer the Dragon's interference no longer!
I wish to see your Great Bastion crumble, then I wish to claim a Dragon's skull.
This realm is not big enough for the both of us.
You must accept annihilation, pretender.
Let there be war between us! Let there be slaughter unbound!
How the Blood God will laugh as I tear you asunder.
No more Ursun. No more Motherland. This is what I desire most!
Kislev must face its long-overdue reckoning, at my immortal hand!
You are the festering sore, and I am its poultice!
Permit me to hasten you on your path to decay...
I have decided that I will feed you to your Great Maw.
Bloated fool! You have impeded Chaos for the last time!
I promise you this – your suffering will be beyond excessive.
I have no more patience for your frivolity. Destruction must come!
The time has come to put an end to your deceptions!
Cower, changeling, for I mean to rip out your lying tongue!
I will wear your skin as a cloak!
Speak, but your words cannot save you!
Our court thrives on plots and schemes! Please, go on.
What dark and callous plans do you wish to lay before me?
My time and temper are short!
The Court of Naggaroth is a dangerous place for unwelcome guests.
The Black Court is no place for the weak!
There is little you can say that will improve my mood.
Make this quick, I have executions to oversee.
Speak quickly, and you may escape with your life.
Approach, but know this; you may never leave!
I have many excellent torture devices, would you care to see them?
You have done well to make it this far, speak!
I am in a black mood, I would advise caution!
The Druchii are malicious and cruel, speak carefully.
The Black Court is a dangerous place.
Do go on, this will be most...enlightening…
In Naggarond, the strong thrive and the weak drown in blood.
Behold the Black Court, few see its splendour and live to tell of it...
Our dread king welcomes you, what do you wish to discuss?
Please, share your inanities with me, I'm listening.
Words have the power to wound, displease me and you will see.
The Black Court waits with bated breath…
I'm sure your little message will be most interesting.
You will pay for the sins of your forefathers!
The Druchii do not forgive and we do not forget!
Have you come to offer the return of Ulthuan?
So, the Asur have seen fit to grace us with their presence.
Speak, Lustrian! My patience grows short!
The wants and needs of your scaly race are no concern of mine!
Your 'powers' do not frighten me, priest!
When did you slither in here?
Bore me with your nonsense, Lizardman.
Children of the Old Ones, how can I be of assistance?
Well, Priest? What do your precious plaques require now?!
I have been looking for something new to hunt and here you are!
Vermin?! In the Black Court?! This had better be good!
So, the ratlords wish to petition the Black Court. Speak, rodent.
What has driven the Skaven from their dark lairs?
I will wear your skin as a cloak!
Speak, but your words cannot save you!
Our court thrives on plots and schemes! Please, go on.
What dark and callous plans do you wish to lay before me?

Speak quickly, and you may escape with your life.

I'm sure your little message will be most interesting.
You will pay for the sins of your forefathers!

So, the Asur have seen fit to grace us with their presence.

The wants and needs of your scaly race are no concern of mine!

When did you slither in here?
Bore me with your nonsense, Lizardman.
Children of the Old Ones, how can I be of assistance?
Well, Priest? What do you precious plaques require now?!
I have been looking for something new to hunt and here you are!
Vermin?! In the Black Court?! This had better be good!
So, the ratlords wish to petition the Black Court. Speak, rodent.
What has driven the Skaven from their dark lairs?
Our only common cause is your destruction!
You shall fail, and the true Druchii shall rise!
Come, fellow Druchii. Let us speak.
What motive brings you to treat with us, Druchii?
Filth! The Black Court has no time for you!
Prostrate yourself before me! I MAY show clemency.
You try my patience; do you wish death!?
I will inflict such horrors upon you…
You will meet your doom if you do not speak now!
The Black Court would think nothing of me killing you…
I find you tiresome. Tiresome things die here.
Speak. Speak quickly! Do you wish to die!?
Your flesh will roast if I am not satisfied!
You have precious little time before I kill you!
Welcome. The Black Court will hear you now.
You have business before the Black Court? Let us hear it.
How can the Black Court aid you this day? Aheh…
Speak, guest, and we shall listen…
You have entered the Black Court. Your business?
We must ask you to be quick, we do not tolerate … failure.
We will at least hear you, before deciding your fate.
Your fate looms before the Black Court. Good luck…
Acquit yourself well, and you might survive this.
We will listen, but do not make promises you cannot keep.
The sins of Ulthuan will ripple through the ages!
Your forebears were curs, just like you!
Your coming here was a risk. Why brave such danger?
Ulthuan wishes to treat? Remarkable. Curious…
For all your brains, you achieve nothing. So you come here…
Roar, if you will, you deserve nothing but my scorn.
When will we be rid of your rotten kind?
Lustria sends warriors to talk with us? Then talk.
What do the Lustrians want of the Black Court?
You are powerful, yes, but less than mobile? An amusement…
Speak, vermin. Your time here is short.
The Dhar will scourge your pathetic hides, unless you speak!
A curious oddity, the Skaven. What brings you here?
Pestilential beings; I suppose that is a compliment to you?
What do traitors wish to discuss with true Druchii?
You are surely doomed to die. I would speak quickly.
Speak, kin, and I will gladly hear your request.
We share common purpose. Let us be about it.
Speak! Before I change my mind.
I could cut you down in an instant, so speak with grace.
A thousand cruel curses greet you - say your piece!
I would enjoy killing you, but I suppose I cannot. Yet.
Pathetic creatures, be brief. I care not for your ramblings.
Speak, or die!
Am I supposed to listen!? Very well…
I do not like your presence, so be quick! Quicker!
I'm losing interest in this already…
You are tiresome thing, should I kill you?
Welcome to the Black Court. Choose your words carefully.
You are welcome here, but do not think you are safe.
Welcome. Speak, if you would.
The Witch King welcomes you. I will treat on his behalf.
You stand before the Black Court. What would you request?
Come now, time is precious. Speak speak!
Speak, whilst you still can. We will hear you.
What plight do you bring before the Black Court?
Words are crucial, don't you think? Pick yours carefully.
You shall speak, and I shall listen. Then we shall see.
Ulthuan sends DOGS to treat with me? Pitiful!
You're out of your depth. Run back to your island.
Do the Asur come to make peace? Hah. Speak.
Ancient enemies, come to treat with the Black Court. How choice.
Hiss and snap, paltry fools! Or did you come with purpose?
What can you possibly offer the Black Court?
Your minds have rotted over the centuries, useless fools.
Ancient and savage, the Lizardmen. Speak… can you speak?
The Black Court will listen to your plea, cold-blooded ones.
All knowing, if not all-moving. What can we do for you?
I smelled you before I saw you. Speak, filthy creature.
Disgusting vermin, your time is short. Do not waste it.
I barely tolerate your verminous presence, so be quick with your words.
You are curious, quaint creatures. What business brings you hence?
You will die. But it will be slow and I will enjoy it.
Bow before the one true King of the Druchii!
So, you think you can lead the Druchii?
The Druchii are mad, bloodthirsty killers and you seek to rule them?
Tremble before the Witch King!
Stand, sit, kneel, it matters not.
Diplomacy is so tedious. I would sooner skin you than hear your drivel.
We are long past words, you know that.
The Druchii have no friends, only victims.
Death lurks behind every syllable, speak!
I have never been much of a diplomat.
I am not known for my ability to forgive.
Your destruction will bring me untold pleasure.
Your people will suffer for your clumsy attempts at diplomacy.
I am Malekith, Lord of the Black Tower and King of Naggaroth!
I am King of the Druchii, leader of the Merciless Host!
The Witch King of Naggarond will hear your words.
Who seeks the counsel of the Witch King?
You may speak your words, but they will change nothing.
You are either very brave or very foolish...
You stand before the supreme ruler of Naggaroth, speak.
Words have great power. The power over life and death, for example.
Choose your words carefully, I most certainly will.
What brings you before the Lord of the Black Tower?
I will walk over your shattered corpse to reclaim what is mine!
Long have I been denied my birthright, but no longer!
Look, my council! A brave Asur warrior comes seeking our aid…
The Asur look so different when they're not mangled corpses.
I will bleed you dry and wear your shrivelled husk as a cape!
Your faith will not shield you from my wrath!
I will tear your temples down with my bare hands!
The Old Ones cannot save you from my ire!
My mother has a fondness for the denizens of Lustria…
Swamp creature of Lustria, what do you want?
There is much I would like to do to you, Lizardman…
Your dedication to the Old Ones is touching; foolish, but touching.
I will pile your pestilential bodies high!
I will drive you back beneath the earth where you belong!
I find myself deeply intrigued by you…
Do you know what we do to vermin in Naggaroth…
Your ambition belies your treachery, so be quick with your desires.
Speak your piece, Druchii. I have little time for it.
Make plain your ambition, Druchii, as I make plain mine.
We Druchii all want something, so speak!
I have no time, so make it quick!
I should cut you down for wasting my time. Speak!
I am disinclined to listen, but I must, so speak with haste!
I am contemplating killing you, so time is of the essence.
I am bidden not to destroy you. Consider yourself lucky.
Speak quickly, or die!
What do you want?
I grow impatient of these constant interruptions.
Be quick about it!
What!? What is it!?
Morathi will hear your insignificant plight…
Yes? What do you bring before the Hag Sorceress?
The Mother of the Druchii will hear your request.
Do not presume my patience, but speak all the same.
I have a great many things to see to, so be quick.
Morathi will listen to your plea.
What is it you seek? I am most intrigued to hear.
I speak for the Druchii; what is it you desire?
Your time with me is precious, so make known your request.
Enter, and speak, for time is a luxury of which you have little.
Accursed Asur - I should cut you down.
Only etiquette stays my fury, so speak. Speak!
What business has Ulthuan in Naggaroth? I am intrigued to know.
How can I, humble Morathi, aid the mighty Phoenix King?
You display scant intelligence. What could you possibly want?
Curious creatures, savage and degenerated. Speak, if you can.
Time has rotted your minds, laughable creatures.
Abandoned by your gods, you come to me. Poor things.
Such fury and power! How may Morathi aid you?
What can Morathi do for the cold-blooded warriors today?
Surely you can read my thoughts and desires already?
What brings the denizens of Lustria to my door?
For what possible reason do you filthy vermin come before me?
Blighted, insignificant vermin; what do you want?
Ohh the Skaven! How delightful…
Holding court for vermin; there is no greater… joy.
What is this trifle you lay before me? Urgh, very well.
The blood of the innocent would have been a more appropriate gift.
We have no need of your gifts, but we accept them none the less.
I accept. Now leave and take your stench with you!
Child of Chaos?! The Ruinous Powers must be bitterly disappointed in their offspring!
I accept, but I would prefer to hunt you and spread your pelt upon my floor.
I accept your terms, creature of Chaos.
You cast a long shadow... I like shadows.
Very well, Beastman. I accept your terms.
Oh, for the fabled days of the Age of Glorious Torment! Instead, I must accept your offer!
I accept your offer, but I would sooner bathe in your blood!
I accept this offer, insect.
I accept your offer, Bretonnian.
Very well, mayfly, I will accept your terms.
You are more capable than I anticipated. Very well.
You have what you came for, but tell your dark masters we do not fear them!
The Ruinous Powers pull your strings and mine it would seem. I accept!
I accept, servant of Chaos.
This benefits the Druchii. Very well.
Chaos is a glorious thing! I accept your offer.
We must work together against the weak and the foolish. I accept!
I accept your offer, but I have called for a Crusade of Blood!
You have your terms traitor, but I will have your head for this!
You are ruthless, well done.
A softly spoken word often conceals a sharp blade... I accept.
I see you are blessed with a silver tongue. I accept these terms.
You are a skilled diplomatist. I accept.
May the Knives of Khaine kill you in your sleep!
You have your terms, Dwarf. Leave, before I add your beard to the tapestries!
I am forced to accept your offer, but this is not over!
Have your terms, foolish as they are!
Greed is an admirable quality, Dwarf, I accept.
I accept your offer, mountain-dweller.
I accept. Now, get out before I mount your head upon the Black Tower!
You barbaric ape! I am forced to agree to your terms but I will have my vengeance!
Fine. I agree to your terms, human.
We have reached an agreement, child of the Empire.
You have my acceptance, your feeble attempt at diplomacy has been most amusing!
You are not as stupid as you look, human. I accept.
I agree to your terms, now remove your hulking carcass from my presence!
This has been beyond painful. I accept your offer!
You have your terms, Greenskin.
I may live to regret this, but you won't.
I admire your commitment to war. I accept your offer.
Your depravity does you credit, I accept!
I would sooner walk over the corpses of your weak people, but I must accept.
I agree to your terms, but you will pay for this in blood!
We have traded words and come to an agreement.
Have your terms, weakling.
Your offer is acceptable, Asur.
Our talks are at an end, I agree to your terms.
By the Lord of Murder, you will suffer for this insult, Lizardman!
Have your terms and drag yourself back to your foul Lustrian swamps!
Since you appear devoid of all emotion you bore me, I accept.
Agreed, now remove yourself from my halls!
You shall have your terms, you strange creatures.
I agree to your terms, Lizardman.
You have my acceptance, now, run!
Your weakness disgusts me, but I accept.
You have your terms. Leave, before I eviscerate you!
You have what you came for.
Very well, we have an accord.
If acceptance will end your drivel, then yes.
I appreciate a well reasoned argument. I accept.
Statecraft is a dying art. For that reason alone, I agree to your terms.
You have a way with words, I accept.
I will have your head for this insult, Skaven!
Scurry off with my acceptance, but know this... I will remember this day…
You have your agreement, Skaven, now leave!
Despite your infernal twitching, we have an agreement!
I long to know more of your malignant race, so I agree.
Very well, outsized rodent, you have your terms!
Flee, Vampire! You have my acceptance and my eternal hatred!
I agree to your terms. Now, remove your cadaverous face from my sight!
The dead strike a hard bargain, very well.
Forced to agree terms with a corpse, this is a low point for me.
I accept. Now, tell me about this 'Dark Kiss'...
Ahh the fabled charisma of the Vampires. Very well, I accept.
I am forced to accept! May Drakira grant me vengeance for this travesty!
I accept, but you would be wise to sleep with one eye open...
I agree to your terms, for now.
How predictably dull... very well, I accept.
There are many dark deeds we could enjoy together.
Khaine be praised! He has brought you to your senses, I accept.
Very wise. A rejection would have meant your life.
What choice did you have, weak as you are?
Better to accept than feed the Cauldrons of Blood!
Very well. Mark my words, I will wear your entrails as a hat.
The Druchii are not known for their willingness to forgive.
Ohh there will be suffering and much agony, that I promise you.
Your death will be slow and painful!
I do not forgive easily…
You will not live to regret your rash decision!
Your people will feed the endless thirst of Khaine!
Ahh! Glorious war!
Let there be war and suffering for all!
We no longer require your 'help'.
Our treaty is at an end, you are fair game once more!
We are free to do anything we desire!
Let us bathe in their blood together!
War is glorious! Let us share in its delights!
Join us or be trampled with the others!
Give me the gold, or I will pluck the eyes from everyone you hold dear!
Blood or gold; a simple request for a simple people.
You have two choices. Give me what I want or I take it...
Khaine, grant me the strength to destroy this beast should it displease me!
Cease your infernal braying and listen!
When I speak you will listen! Do you understand, Beastman?
What impressive horns you have! Point them elsewhere while we talk.
You smell of blood and death. Excellent, Let's talk!
The children of Chaos! I have important matters to discuss.
Quiet, or I will sew your mouth shut!
Mayflies! Your fragile bodies offer little pleasure, let us talk instead.
If you are wise, which I doubt, you will listen to what I have to say.
Well, Bretonnian, I am here to make you an offer you cannot refuse...
It is polite to hold one's tongue in the presence of your betters.
What does your code of chivalry say of avarice?
You are unfit to serve the Ruinous Powers! Still your wagging tongue and listen!
I don't care who your masters are, displease me and I will flay you!
I have despicable plans to discuss with your dark masters!
Let us sit together and discuss plans for the destruction of the weak!
We will spread chaos across the world and revel in the madness that follows!
Let us share in nightmarish deeds and acts of pure cruelty!
Traitors! You are lucky you still draw breath! Do not anger me further!
You will hear me or feed the Cauldrons of Blood, your choice!
An offer is better than a dagger in the eye, wouldn't you agree?
You know the depths of my malice and the lengths I will go to for revenge...
The pain of others is glorious! Do you not agree?
Give in to Atharti and the many pleasures she can offer her loyal followers...
Still your stunted tongue, Dwarf! You will hear what I have to say!
Cower before me! If I am displeased by our talks I will pluck out your eyes!
The illustrious Druchii have seen fit to honour you with their presence.
Well, mountain-dweller, I would say it's a pleasure, but we both know I'd be lying.
Listen carefully, Dwarf. I never repeat myself.
Clean out your dirt-filled ears, Dwarf. I have matters to discuss with you.
Those that turn their back on the Druchii often find a blade between their shoulders!
Are you frightened, mayfly? Well you should be!
I know statecraft is little practiced in your puny Empire, but do try.
You have little to offer me that I could not take at knifepoint, so listen carefully.
Do not fear sin, child of the Empire, it can set you free...
We have things to discuss, at least try and comport yourself in a manner befitting a diplomat.
Close your maw or you may find a blade in it!
I will stake you to the ground, if that's what it takes to get you to listen!
Take your finger out of that orifice when I'm talking to you, you disgusting creature!
Put down the chopper and listen.
You like war; we like war. I think you see where I'm going...
Diplomacy with Greenskins is like pulling teeth... strangely enjoyable.
Usurpers! You will hear my words or perish in flame!
Silence! When the Druchii speak, the weak tremble!
Elves of Ulthuan, we need to talk.
We, the outcast children of Ulthuan, have matters we wish to discuss.
Come, sit, share a drink with me while we have a mutually-beneficial discussion.
A diplomat must cast aside all his feelings and deal with the matter at hand.
Displease me and I shall see your temples raised to the ground, Lizardman!
Your Old Ones are long dead. It is time you followed a new path!
You seek to spread your Cold Order to every corner of the world? Let's talk.
The pain of lesser races is delicious, you really must try it!
We share a love of blood sacrifice! Perhaps there is more we could share?
Creatures of Lustria, I have matters I wish to discuss with you.
Shut your mouth and listen or I will shut it for you!
My first impulse is always to maim! Consider yourself lucky I am in control of my impulses today!
Accept my offer or accept the demise of your entire race!
Shut up and listen, I have much to say and little time.
I will give you instructions, fail to follow them and you will suffer.
My patience is limited and my temper quick.
The Naggarothi make generous friends and deadly enemies...
I come before you to discuss a proposition from the Black Tower.
I demand a moment of your time!
Stand still, before I cut off your tail and beat you with it!
We will find you and kill every last one of your pathetic race! Now listen!
You, rat creature! I am speaking, so you should be listening!
A little twitchy, aren't we? Do you have something to hide?
Greetings, spreaders of plague! Let us talk awhile.
Hello Skaven, there are things you need to hear.
You know nothing of the darkness! Shut up and listen!
Pretenders to the true dark, hear my words and tremble!
Pull the maggots from your ears and listen to what I have to say.
Dead creature, I have an offer from the Black Tower.
You would be unwise to turn the Druchii from your door, Vampire.
Well, let us see what we can do for one another.
Your Deepwood cannot stand against the flaming rage of the Druchii!
You fools! You cannot hide yourselves away from the world, or me!
You would do well to listen to my words, Asrai.
You call us evil, but you simply lack imagination. Let me enlighten you.
There is much we could achieve if you embrace your inner malice!
Cast aside your 'humanity' and I'll show you the pleasures you've been missing!
Sadly a blade in the ribs cannot fix everything... I have an offer to discuss with you.
Occasionally we are forced to lower ourselves to your level.
The Druchii have much to offer.
You should be snapping my hand off... Not literally!
Children of Chaos, we seek to share in your depravity!
You would be unwise to cast my offer aside, Bretonnian.
Do you recall the fate of Bastintaal of L’Anguille? Then listen carefully.
I have an offer for the Ruinous Powers.
Your masters will honour you with many fine deformities when you present them with my offer.

It is a rare thing, to see the words of a slave move a king, but I accept.
Apparently the desolate north is not completely deprived of sense. Very well.
Your words have moved me, Bretonnian. I accept.
I have gleaned a hint of wisdom in amongst your foolish words. I agree to your terms.
It is a dark day when the mountain must bow to the howling wind! I accept, daemon of darkness!
Have your terms! But know this, our gods drove your twisted daemons back once before and they will do it again!
Servant of Chaos, I must accept the dark will of your masters.
I do not like your terms, servant of Chaos, but you leave me little choice...
Creatures from the black, you have your terms.
Your masters will be most pleased - I agree to their terms.
These are not terms! Yet I am compelled to accept them, you dark-hearted villain!
May your dark heart fester within your chest, you deceitful creature!
Have your little request, it means nothing to me.
I will grant your request, Druchii, but I will remember this day.
Though I am sure you have used your dark arts to bewitch me, I accept your terms.
I'm sure this little accord is terribly important to the Druchii, I have found the whole thing rather dull.
May your homeland be infested by desert scorpions! Have your terms, Dwarf!
A thousand curses be upon you! You will have your terms, but your people will pay for them in blood!
Return to your dark halls. You have what you came for.
You drive a hard bargain, Dwarf. I accept your terms.
I'm sure you will tell your beardlings of this day in years to come. I accept.
You may return to your elders. Be proud of what you have achieved this day.
Have your terms, savage cretin! You will pay for this insolence!
You may have your way this time, but there will be consequences for your little Empire!
Have your ceased your blathering? Excellent, I accept your terms.
Your mortal desires are nothing to me. Thus, I accept.
Even barbarians are capable of a low sort of cunning. Very well, I accept.
Child of the Empire, it seems we have an agreement.
I weary of your drivel! I accept this offer, but you will pay for the insolent manner in which it was made!
May khepra beetles burrow in to your brain and eat the diseased contents! Have your inane terms!
I have made myself a craftsman in speech, but it would seem ignorance has prevailed. I accept your terms.
Gods, grant me the strength to bear this indignity… I accept.
If agreement is what it takes to remove you from my sight, then agreement you shall have!
As you have refrained from desecrating a single tomb during your time here, I accept.
I accept, but it is my fondest wish that you be torn limb from limb by Hierotitans!
I will have your soul added to the Casket of Souls for this insolence, Elf!
I will accept this offer, but only as it's been a slow decade.
You may tell yourself that all you do is 'for the greater good', but I have seen lust for power before. I agree to your terms, Elf.
You have proven yourselves trustworthy in the past. I accept this offer.
Your offer was courteous and well made. I accept.
Cretinous lizard of the southern wastes! You will rue the day you crossed a king! I accept.
As you say, but I am displeased. Most displeased…
Very well, I accept your little offer. Now return to your swamps and leave me in peace.
As I fear you will never leave until you have my agreement, I accept your offer.
This offer is acceptable, Lizardman.
You are as implacable as the desert sun, I accept your offer.
You may have the dark desires of your heart this day, but you will pay for them in the fullness of time!
May you die a thousand deaths for your part in this travesty! Have your terms and be gone!
You have my acceptance, along with my eternal hatred and a promise that I will stand over your rotting corpse!
For every joy there is a price to be paid. You would do well to remember that.
I will accept your offer, for the plots and schemes of your little land are nothing to me.
Your little offer is acceptable; meagre and uninteresting, but acceptable.
The Tomb Kings are always happy to come to the assistance of the lesser races.
The art of diplomacy is beautiful and complicated; those who master it can paint a masterpiece with a handful of words. I accept.
A well-made offer is pleasing to the ears of men and gods!
I would sooner see your flesh stripped from your bones by khepra beetles, but I accept.
You treacherous craven! You have contrived this whole situation! Have my grudging acceptance!
Though you are unfit to discuss terms with a king, I will accept them none the less.
Have the desires of your little rodent heart, I care not.
Very well, Skaven, I will accept this offer, despite the fact that I do not trust you in the slightest.
Your incessant plotting and scheming has paid off. I accept.
May your soul live a tortured existence out in the desert wastes for bringing this travesty to my door!
By the Scales of Kalandrithir, you will pay for this! I accept.
The greed of lesser kings has torn our kingdom apart on several occasions, but if you insist...
The gods will not smile upon this accord, but I accept.
May the gods stand between you and harm in all the dark places you must walk. I accept!
When two great minds meet in council they will always come to an understanding, as we have this day.
What fell sorcery has brought me to this pass? Forced to agree terms with a creature of Nagash!
May a thousand suns shine forever upon you! Have your terms, creature!
Have what you came for, Lahmian monster. I could not care less for your petty intrigues.
I am sure this seems like a victory to you, Vampire, but your affairs are as the buzzing of a fly to the mighty Tomb Kings!
Words come easily to your kind. Very well, I accept your terms.
You will have what you seek, Vampire.
May the sands of Nehekhara consume all you hold dear! Have your terms, Elf!
I will see your Deepwood destroyed for this outrage. Have my acceptance and my eternal hatred!
The desire to protect ones homeland is something I understand well, I accept.
The follies of the Elves have long since lost their savour, I accept your offer.
It would seem we have an accord, Elf.
Strange creature of the woodland realm, I accept your offer.
I see the gods have guided you down the path of wisdom.
Wisdom is a gift granted to few. You are lucky.
Wisdom is seldom found beyond the boundaries of Nehekhara - this is most pleasing.
It seems you have taken leave of your senses. Very well, but the friendship of a king is not so easily cast aside…
So, you wish to cancel our treaty? So be it…
You are making a terrible mistake, one your people will pay for in generations to come.
Your rejection is not worthy of Nehekhara.
Do you think this actually matters to my eternal plans?
Very well, you’ll be lost to the sands before I.
Djaf shall remember this… and come lurking.
Your refusal dishonours your race, and offends my majesty.
Curse you! Curse all your rancid lot!
The shining legions of Nehekhara are ready to end your pitiful race and erase you from history!
Call upon your gods, you will need their help in the battles to come.
So you have chosen death, very well. I will toast your destruction.
I am here to inform you that our treaty is at an end.
The mighty Tomb Kings of Nehekhara no longer view your friendship as profitable.
Our treaty is at an end. May the gods of your homeland watch over you in these dark times.
Come! Join the mighty legions of Nehekhara upon the field of battle and witness true martial brilliance!
The very earth shakes at the advance of my mighty legions! Will you stand with me?
The Tomb Kings march to war, will you bask in our reflected glory?
When a king asks for tribute a wise man gives it without question!
I require a little token of your esteem…
A generous and open-handed leader will find himself with many strong and valuable allies.
How I long to watch desert scorpions devour your eyes! Instead, I must bandy words with you!
Stinking monstrosity of Chaos, you will hear my words and tremble!
I will not waste fine words and pleasantries on you, let us talk.
The twisted children of Chaos… you are more hideous than I ever imagined…
I will do my best to make you understand my words, Beastman.
I am unsure if you can follow civilised speech, so I will speak slowly and loudly.
When a king stands before you, you kneel, peasant!
Many a crusading Knight has lost his life in the Charnel Valley… you would do well to remember that during our talks.
Peasants of Bretonnia, the mighty Tomb Kings of Nehekhara have matters they wish to discuss with you.
It would seem you are not as backward as I first imagined, let us talk awhile.
I have come to bring light to your darkened little corner of the world, Bretonnian.
Behold! The fabled glory of Nehekhara and its mighty kings. You are fortunate indeed.
Cease your noise, puppet! It is your masters I wish to speak with, not their lackey!
Kings do not discuss their plans with minions, tell your masters I am here!
You weak-willed fool! It pains me to speak to a creature who has no control over their own mind.
Though it is utterly beneath me to share words with a servant, I am forced to waste my time on you, creature of the Ruinous Powers!
Servant of the dark lords of Chaos, I have matters I wish to put before your masters.
Minions of Chaos, I am here to discuss terms with you.
Would that I could feed you to the sand sharks! But for the good of my people, I must share words with you instead!
Your dark arts destroyed my homeland! Yet here I am to parlay with you!
I do not doubt that your malice will destroy you in time, but until then, I have matters I wish to discuss with you.
The strength and power of the Tomb Kings is known the world over! So, let us speak of matters of great import.
Your cruelty and wickedness are far famed, Druchii. Let us talk together awhile.
Well then, here I am to discuss terms with the Dark Elves of Naggarond, wonderful.
You dare to raise an axe in the presence of the king?! You will pay for this insolence, but first you will hear my words!
I have lowered myself to bring you this message and you will hear it or die, Dwarf!
If you have finished grubbing beneath the earth… I seek a word with you.
Are Dwarfs capable of civility? I suppose we will find out…
Lords of the mountains, the glorious Tomb Kings of Nehekhara have an offer to lay before you.
Greetings, Dwarf, I have a proposition that may appeal to the natural greed that is so prevalent in your race.
While your kind was scratching in the mud I had already built monuments fit for the gods! You will hear my words, in silence!
The words of a king should carry weight, even in this forsaken land! Silence, I am talking!
Do try to curb your barbaric tendencies while I am speaking.
I will give you the honour of my company while I lay out my proposal.
I will keep this simple, as I fear you may struggle with complex ideas… I need to speak with you.
Child of the Empire, I wish to discuss a proposal with you.
You will be still and listen! Or I will have your bones crushed by Necrosphinxes!
Quiet! The noise you creatures make is unbearable! I can feel it rattling round my skull!
The way of knowledge is narrow, perhaps too narrow for a Greenskin…
A wise King knows that even a blunt instrument has its uses from time to time.
The fine art of diplomacy is clearly wasted on you, so I shall simply get to the point.
I will keep this short, Greenskin. For your sake and mine.
I grow tired of your meddling, Elf! You will hear what I have to say, in silence!
Ohh how I hate the Elves of Ulthuan! Yet, here I am…
Despite your holier-than-thou demeanour I am here to make you an offer.
Though your incessant babbling about the 'greater good' is beyond tedious, I have an offer to put to you.
No discussion can throw light when it wanders away from the point. Don't you agree?
Greetings, Elves of Ulthuan. I have an offer I wish to discuss with you.
Slithering, sneaking reptiles, how I despise you! You will hear my words, or the consequences will be dire!
Creatures of the southern wastes, how I tire of you!
Though your swamps have little to offer, I still have matters I wish to discuss with you.
Creatures of the fetid swamps of Lustria, we have much to discuss.
The Lizardmen of Lustria, let us talk.
Children of the Old Ones, we have much to discuss.
Silence, fool! My time is precious and you are far from worthy of it!
We Tomb Kings are not known for our patience, so listen carefully!
I would sooner bathe in a sea of khepra beetles than converse with you, yet here I am!
It is customary to kneel before a king. Especially one bearing generous offers.
I have much to tell you, listen carefully.
A wise man is silent before his betters.
Few are granted the opportunity to hear the words of a king, so enjoy it while you can.
I am here to discuss matters of a mutually beneficial nature.
I come with word from the great land of Nehekhara!
I have an offer for you, but don't think for a moment that I have forgotten who and what you are, rodent!
Bestill your pestilential flesh, I have an offer to put to you.
Cease that infernal chittering and listen!
These are strange times indeed, when a king stands before a rodent with important matters to discuss.
I have matters to discuss with you that will appeal to your scheming nature, Skaven.
Well, Skaven, let us speak of matters that are beneficial to all.
I will watch your bones burn in righteous fire, but first, we must talk.
Quiet, traitor! The gods will see you suffer for your crimes and I will be there to watch!
For now, we must put aside our differences and discuss matters of great import.
I shall rise above your petty intrigues so we may discuss the future of Nehekhara.
It is always a pleasure to talk with one who understands the fine art of diplomacy.
Let us sit together and discuss matters of a mutually beneficial nature.
Though I want nothing more than to wipe your vile taint from this earth, I have a proposition to put to you!
Creature of darkness, my hatred for you burns brighter than the midday sun, yet I must speak with you.
Lahmian monster! You would do well to hold your tongue until I have finished speaking!
May the light of the gods cleanse your tortured soul, Vampire. I have a proposition for you.
Your silvered tongue may fool mortals, but I am as old as the sands of my homeland and with age, comes wisdom.
Do not attempt to beguile me, Vampire, you will fail! Just listen.
You will hear what I have to say! Fail to do so and you may find your homeland rather… changed.
If you fail to heed my words, elf, I will destroy your precious Deepwood with a wave of my hand!
Strange creatures of the woodland realm, I have matters I wish to discuss with you.
Come, bask in my reflected glory awhile, we have much to talk about.
Greetings, Asrai. We have much to discuss.
Elf of the Deepwood, I wish to speak with you on a matter of great importance.
Which kind of Elf are you? The tree ones? The Vortex worshippers? Or the deviants?
I am long dead, Elf – you cannot intimidate me, I do not feel pain.
Bow before a king – revel in my Undying majesty.
My Undying legions are eager to spill blood – are you their next prey?
Defy me and my curse shall haunt you for the rest of your existence.
Sand and stone… these elements are everything – they will be your epitaph.
You dare challenge an ever-living Priest King of Nehekhara?
My sarcophagus is currently empty, do you wish to fill it?
Keep your head bowed. Show me your reverence, thrall.
When threatened, a jackal, shows its belly; an act of submission. You are the jackal.
Like Ptra, I am divine – worship me and we may strike a pact.
Usirian warns against a pact with you, so speak now.
I have little time for such fey, living things. Approach if you must.
What do you want, High Elf? Do all living things whittle so much?
I lose patience with your cold-blooded kind.
I know of your insidious mindgames, reptile. It will not work on me.
Vermin filth, do not approach a being of such majesty!
Your council is weak, rat-man, only in death will you find strength.
The Liche Priests whisper to me that you lack… majesty.
I am a true ruler of Nehekhara, what do you offer?
I hold the mantle of king, of royalty; you are nothing but a husk.
Yours is a petty realm; a minor fiefdom, nothing more…
Come, Tomb King – or is it robber baron? What relics or legions do you offer?
The jackal-headed god wishes us to talk, dark one. So speak.
How is your icy kingdom, Druchii? You need sand not snow.
Don't be aghast, for I still have a mortal's appetites. More wine? Drink, then we talk treaties.
The convention is to bow, I suggest you do to stay in my good graces.
Welcome - behold my greatness, it is beatific, is it not?
Look upon my eternal form, know that you broker with great power.
You are in the court of a king, you may marvel.
I am a gracious host, how can I make you comfortable? I forget mortal pleasures.
What do you desire, if it is within my vast power, I shall make it so.
Ptra smiles – the creator god blesses this conference.
My Liche advisers bid that we should make amends.
Tell me, creature, how will negotiation aid me in restoring my glory?
I see you, High Elf, even if my eyes are lost. What tributes do you bring?
I have been to Ulthuan – to your capital – when I lived. I was unimpressed.
Reptiles, look upon my magnificence, and submit.
Scaled creatures, do not stand in the way of my restoration.
You hold little interest to me, Lizardmen. Be quick.
Do I confound you, reptile? My existence is against your limited view of this world.
Very well, I will hear your inane squeaking, rodent.
What do you want, creature of Sakhmet?
Our dynasties are compatible, maybe our tomb-cities should unite?
Together we may be as mighty as Khemri. What are your terms?
The gods of Nehekhara deign that we speak. It is a fool that ignores their will.
The Great Creator himself sent omens that we should speak…
Come, fellow sovereign of Undeath, let us weave our desires.
The Tomb Kings of Nehekhara have much to offer their allies…
My wealth and power know no bounds and I am generous to those who treat me with the respect I deserve…
May the light of the gods shine on our talks this day!
You will hear my words, Beastman! Or you will taste my blade!
Silence! I have important matters to lay before you, creature of Chaos!
Even the lowliest peasant has his uses from time to time. I have an offer I wish to discuss with you.
Though your homes are little more than hovels and your gods are strange to me, I have an offer to put to you.
Tell your dark masters that the mighty Tomb Kings of Nehekhara have matters they wish to discuss.
I have an offer that will be most pleasing to your Ruinous Powers.
Though I know you are nothing but a viper, I am here to make you an offer.
Greetings, Elf of darkness. Let us sit together and discuss mutually beneficial matters.
Sometimes the lion is forced to work with lamb…
I have heard much of the greed of your kind, perhaps we could come to some arrangement that is pleasing to both sides?
Only a fool would turn aside an offer as generous as this…
I will do my best to make this simple for you, barbarian.
May the honoured dead forgive me… I have a proposition for you, Greenskin.
Though the stain of this will be upon my soul for eternity… I have an offer for you.
Remove that haughty look from your face and listen carefully, Elf, we have important matters to discuss.
What I have to say is of the upmost importance, you would be wise to heed my every word.
I have a generous offer to lay before you, Lizardman of Lustria.
I am sure my offer will please your strange and barbaric gods!
Stand still when I'm talking to you, rodent! You sway like a palm in a sandstorm!
Let me lay out my proposal before you attempt to twist it to your benefit, Skaven!
Though you are a lowly servant of Sokth, I have an offer to put before you.
By the Scales of Kalandrithir! You will hear my words, traitor!
My patience does not extend to your kind, creature of Lahmia! So still your tongue and listen!
You would be unwise to risk my ire, Vampire. So listen carefully.
Consider your words carefully, Elf. The Tomb Kings are not lightly cast aside…
Wood land creature, I am here to make you a generous offer.
The land of Nehekhara is filled with treasures beyond counting…
The rulers of Nehekhara are rich beyond your wildest dreams; we wish to share this vast wealth with you.
The many wonders of Nehekhara are a sight to behold. Today though, I offer you this gift.
The glorious armies of the Tomb Kings stand ready to aid you!
The might of Nehekhara will wash over your enemies like a spring flood!
We will sweep away your enemies like a sandstorm!
The rulers of Nehekhara weary of your war-mongering, let there be peace.
There is no glory in fighting an inferior foe. Therefore, we offer you peace.
Neither side profits from this war, let there be peace.
You hold no lands, have no great treasures – why would the rulers of Nehekhara waste their precious time on you?
You are as relentless as a sandstorm and just as implacable! I am here to offer you peace.
Your mortal lives are short. Better to spend them in peace.
You cannot hope to win this war, mortal. I am here to offer you a way out…
Tell your 'Ruinous Powers' that the Tomb Kings call for peace.
Take a message to your masters: The time for bloodshed is at an end.
The Elves of Naggarond have little to offer the mighty Tomb Kings, we weary of stilling your black hearts.
I am here to offer you peace, creature of Naggarond. Not that I imagine for one second that you will accept.
Set aside your Book of Grudges and your axes for a moment, I am here to discuss peace.
Listen carefully, Dwarf. I grow tired of fighting your inferior warriors.
My people were building great monuments when yours were still scratching in the mud! I cannot waste my time warring with you.
We have taken all we need from your little Empire. Now we call for peace.
Only a fool is obstinate in the face of defeat. I am no fool, I offer you peace.
I seek to offer you peace, though all I see in your eyes is bloodlust.
Your battle with us no longer serves the greater good.
The shores of Ulthuan no longer interest me. It is time for peace.
There is nothing of interest to the mighty Tomb Kings in your fetid homeland. Thus, we call for peace.
I care little for the will of your strange gods. I demand a cessation of hostilities.
Killing vermin is not the work of kings. I am ready to end the fighting.
Your pestilential corpses taint the ground they lie on. Let us have peace now.
Come! Are we not civilised men? Let us have peace and mend the tears in our broken kingdom.
Djaf has had his fill. Let us return peace to our war-torn realm.
Though I would like nothing more than to wipe your vile taint from this earth, once and for all, I am here to offer you peace.
We have decided it is foolish to fight the dead. We offer you peace.
I may have a use for you yet. Let us have peace.
Your woodland realm is a strange and terrible place… I am here to offer you peace.
The mighty legions of Nehekhara are the envy of the known world. I can see why you beg for help, but we cannot give it.
When the lion and the lamb stand side by side, it can only end one way.
A wise man seeks shelter while the storm rages. We cannot be your shelter.
I see you cower before me! There shall be no peace!
The ancient armies of Nehekhara are vast beyond counting – there will be no peace!
I will see your remains scattered to the four winds! Now is not the time for peace!
When I have hunted you to extinction, then we will have peace.
The great Tomb Kings of Nehekhara do not make peace with the creatures of Chaos!
Your weakness disgusts me! I will glory in your utter destruction!
Those who wish to live in peace should prepare for war, Bretonnian!
Our all-powerful gods drove you from our lands before and we will do it again!
