Your dark masters will never hold sway in Nehekhara! There can be no peace with the minions of Chaos!
Your dark arts shall not avail you, death is coming for you.
No fine words can save you now – now you shall pay!
Leave me, Dwarf! There will be no peace!
My victory over your pathetic people will be writ large in the histories of Nehekhara!
Your barbaric attempts at diplomacy are laughable – there can be no peace!
My people were building great monuments when your people were still scratching in the mud!
You will have your peace when all your kind are dead!
What do Greenskins know of peace?! No, a thousand times, no!
Your wagging tongue has proved your undoing. I see no need for peace!
Djaf has not been sated, there can be no peace!
Slither back to your swamps, the glorious legions of Nehekhara are coming for you!
I cannot grant you the peace you seek, Lizardman.
Prince Lamhirakh sends his regards, Skaven!
Your treachery has not been forgotten, there can be no peace!
Sokth take you for his own! There will be no peace!
By Asaph, I will have my vengeance and you will pay for your treachery!
There can be no peace with the creatures of Nagash!
I will not rest until your vile taint has been wiped from this earth, once and for all!
You shall be entombed beneath the sands for all eternity!
You shall have your peace, when your Deepwood has been swallowed by the desert!
Twisted monster of Chaos, the rulers of Nehekhara do not bow to the likes of you!
You are little more than a wandering band of monsters. You have nothing to offer me!
Your braying has left me with a headache and no desire to hear from your disgusting race in the future!
Your bestial terms do not interest me, creature of Chaos.
Though I understood little of what you said, I am confident my answer is no.
Now that your bellowing has ceased, my answer is no.
This is not the offer of a race that prides itself on honour, leave me!
Kings do not bow to the wishes of peasants!
Remove yourself from my sight, peasant!
Your petty plots and intrigues are of little interest to me, mortal.
You will not find what you seek beneath the sands of Nehekhara, Bretonnian.
The Tomb Kings of Nehekhara are unwilling to help your cause.
You forget yourself, servant of Chaos! I am a king, not some peasant you can command!
Tell your masters they have nothing to offer me!
Take your offer and take your accursed form from my halls and never darken them again!
It would appear you have failed your masters, this will not go well for you…
I reject your terms, servant of the Ruinous Powers.
It is difficult to come to terms with a madman, so no.
Take your dark heart and your dark offer and leave my kingdom before I have you pulled apart by Necrolith Colossi!
Your dark arts have failed you! I reject this offer and you!
I have looked deep within your soul, Elf, and found only madness! I reject your offer!
There can be no agreement, not with the Druchii.
You may have beguiled many a great leader with your silvered words, but not I, not I!
I find it difficult to trust your kind, Elf. As such, I reject this offer.
Do not waste my time with your drivel, Dwarf!
Have you already forgotten the Hammer of Algrim?! I have not!
Your offer is almost as ridiculous as your beard! Never, Dwarf!
Your curt demands may pass for an offer in your homeland, but in Nehekhara we respect the art of diplomacy!
It does not surprise me that I am unable to accept your terms, Dwarf.
Come back to me when you have a better grasp on the art of diplomacy.
I will feed your rotting corpse to the sand-sharks!
I reject your offer, you drooling barbarian!
The men of the Empire have nothing to offer the great kings of Nehekhara!
What could you possibly offer the king of kings? Nothing – now go!
Despite your barbaric upbringing you have done well this day, but my answer is still no.
I am unable to accept your offer at this time, despite the clarity of your words.
All you care for is destruction! I shall never come to terms with you or any of your pernicious race!
Vile monster! There is nothing you could offer me that would erase your foul deeds! Be gone!
The mountain does not bow to the howling wind!
Though your speech is nigh-unintelligible, I understood enough to know that the answer is no.
I will put this in terms you can understand: no!
To put it simply: no.
I am tired of meddlesome elves! I want nothing from you!
You have overstepped, Elf!
The rulers of Nehekhara need nothing from the Elves of Ulthuan.
You are a skilled diplomat, but I will not accept this offer.
All the proper rites have been observed, but I cannot accept this offer.
Master-diplomat though you are, Elf, I cannot agree to these terms.
The mighty Tomb Kings do not accept offers from the denizens of Lustria!
I will tear your golden pyramids down, brick by brick, and use the remains to build glorious monuments to the gods of Nehekhara!
I care not for the will of your strange gods, Lizardman, my answer is no.
The denizens of Lustria have little to offer the great kings of Nehekhara.
I am afraid I cannot indulge the desires of your little plaques, Lizardman.
Devotion to ones gods is an admirable trait, but it does not compel me to accept this offer.
May your corpse be devoured by a thousand khepra beetles! Never!
You jackal, how dare you come before a ruler of Nehekhara with an offer such as this?
I will throw you in to a pit of skull vipers for this insolence!
The Tomb Kings of Nehekhara have no need of you.
Your clumsy words have failed to move me, I reject your offer.
I see no point in continuing our talks.
You held my attention well, but I cannot agree to your terms.
It is always pleasing to find others, outside Nehekhara, who appreciate the fine art of diplomacy, but I am afraid I cannot accept.
You have acquitted yourself well, but I cannot accept these terms.
I have not forgotten your meddling, Skaven! I will never agree to your terms!
You have nothing to offer me. Now leave, before I call a Necrosphinx to see you out!
The Tomb Kings of Nehekhara do not agree terms with rodents!
Your chittering has bored me to the very gates of the underworld! The answer is no.
I do not trust you. I reject your offer.
No, Skaven, I cannot accept this offer.
Your soul will languish in torment for your part in this! I reject your offer, utterly!
May the Curse of Lahmia be upon you for this treachery!
Servant of Sokth! How dare you ask this?
Kings do not bandy words with the servants of Sokth!
Though the gods smile upon your offer, I cannot accept it.
It is always a pleasure to converse with one who has the wisdom of the ages, but I cannot accept your offer.
I will not rest until your vile taint has been wiped from this earth. Now, get out!
Accursed Lahmian, I reject your offer!
You will not ensnare me with your dark arts, Vampire! I reject your offer!
Remove your accursed corpse from my sight, our talks are at an end!
I had heard much of the silvered tongues of the Vampire Counts. I was not disappointed, but our talks are at an end.
Slink back to whatever dark hole you came from! I want nothing from you, Vampire!
I will burn your hovels to the ground for this!
Your Deepwood shall become a barren wasteland for this insolence!
Your paltry offer is of no interest to me, Elf.
The wants and desires of your strange race are of no interest to the mighty Tomb Kings.
I cannot agree to these terms, Elf of the woodland realm.
Your words have been wise and your manner courteous, but I must reject your offer.
We shall come forth from the sands and our numbers will be beyond counting!
I will shatter your bones beneath the golden wheels of my chariots!
You will gaze upon the fabled glory of the armies of Nehekhara!
It is time to slay the beasts! To war!
Let the hunt begin!
Your people will taste of the waters of the Great Mortis River!
The might of Nehekhara comes for you, Bretonnian!
Gaze upon the Necrotect of your destruction, servant of Chaos!
Tell your Ruinous Powers that the rulers of Nehekhara are coming for them!
The destruction of your people will bring me untold joy!
Dark Magic will not save you, Elf! We are at war!
Let there be war between the Tomb Kings of Nehekhara and the Dwarfs of the mountains!
War is upon you, Dwarf!
Your so called 'Empire' will be crushed by the might of Nehekhara!
Your barbaric gods cannot save you now! War is upon you!
I will watch your corpse turn to dust, Greenskin! To war!
It is time you were culled, like the beasts you are!
Elves of Ulthuan, war is upon you!
You have meddled in the affairs of others for the last time! Now your people shall die!
War is upon you, Lizardman!
My armies will see to the complete destruction of your reptilian race!
Your schemes are at an end, Skaven! You will burn in the fires of war!
I will not rest until your entire pestilential race has been wiped from this earth!
So, we have entered the Time of Kings again. Very well!
Those that oppose my will shall be cleansed in the fires of war!
Lahmian monster! Your doom is here at last!
War is upon you, creature of Nagash!
Your end is nigh, Elf!
You shall watch as the sands of Nehekhara consume your precious Deepwood!
My Goddess of Vengeance is more powerful than yours.
Your rage is impotent next to mine, Elf.
You are keeping me from my purpose – speak quickly!
Careful how you tread, there are snakes in the sand.
Asaph is the Goddess of Vengeance – do not incur my wrath.
You dare engage with me!
Challenge me, and witness vengeance!
You reek of weakness, thrall.
Bow before a queen, and I might consider mercy.
Do not enrage me further, fool.
A snake will strike if angered. Do you risk that?
I have no interest in you, creature.
The affairs of Elves hold no interest to me.
Do not trespass, Elf, or we'll see just how quick you are.
Reptiles should skulk in the jungle, not intrude on my sands.
Do not waste my time, reptile, I see an enemy not an ally.
You have nothing to offer me but your death, reptile.
Your age is irrelevant, creature, your span is over if I deign it.
The asps will feast on vermin this day.
Vermin filth! I have no desire to bargain with you.
You are frail, my king. The stink of rot upon you.
I have no use for kings, especially your decrepit corpse.
Do drone on with all your dynastic titles, it is so impressive.
Get your bandages out of your mouth and speak!
A fool in life and a fool in death, what do you want?
Vampire! You dare approach me!
From the sands I shall strike at you and Neferata!
Attend me, Elf, but do not mistake my welcome for infinite patience.
I know of you, Dark Elf, what do you want?
You come to speak to the Voice of the Vengeful?
An audience? Very well - have you spoken to my cousin?
What do want of the warrior-queen?
As long as this serves Lybaras, I will hear your plea.
Do not let my deathmask unnerve you - approach and talk to me.
Asaph deigns that I parley with you.
What would you have of me?
Make your offer, but beware my venom - there is no antidote!
You have my attention, mortal.
Hush! When I sit upon my throne, you can begin.
Welcome, you fragile things.
I have no strife with the wanderers of Ulthuan.
You engage with a warrior-queen, warrior-reptile.
Reptiles and serpents share ancestry - maybe we have common cause?
Greetings, ancient one, do not outstay your welcome.
Cold-blooded? I have no blood.
You are brave to come here, vermin… for snakes eat rats.
Your offer better be worth my time, vermin. Asaph hungers.
A 'king' comes, should I be intimidated?
The royalty of Nehekhara attends; be warned… I bite!
Do not approach me with loose bandages!
Speak then, if you can. I assume your jaw is still attached?
I will not bow to a dead king – I am a queen.
You dare approach me, Vampire!
You are no youthful Elf! On the inside you are as withered as me!
I know a king when I see one, and your king has no majesty.
Careful what you desire, stranger, you have no idea what waits in the desert.
You come in ignorance – a bargain will be challenging…
Your petty plights do not interest me.
Why should I aid you? You radiate ignorance.
Do not threaten me, you have no idea of my power!
I could crush you with a single incantation – steady your tongue!
That is not polite – let me teach you some manners!
Do you wish to visit the Realm of Souls? I doubt you'd return!
Do not bother me, you are not welcome on the Day of Awakening!
Let me explain your doom, for I have foreseen it!
Your race shall diminish, and I will take any lore you leave behind.
Do not be coy, for I am too old. Tell me what you want.
Your claim that we break the natural order of the world is false!
What do the cold-blooded want from the Liche Lord?
Lizardmen, you have failed to adapt. You still believe in living…
Do not accuse me of stealing secrets, reptile, I toiled long to uncover them!
The pests rise and demand tribute! Oh, what a time to exist!
I see no reason to barter with such verminous filth.
You play a dangerous game; the Mortuary Cult is not your pawn.
We are here to serve the kings of Nehekhara, but do not mock us.
Careful, I could cast you back into the Realm of Souls for eternity.
Show respect for the Grand Hierophant or I’ll reduce your legions to bones!
We are the Mortuary Cult. Our power exceeds your reign, your highness.
We have much in common, Druchii, it makes sense to share our findings.
Have you discovered the darkest secrets to your power? I have…
I am the Grand Hierophant. It intrigues me to barter with you.
I seek only to bring greatness to Khemri. Do not frustrate my plans.
Welcome stranger. I need lore – you may have what I desire.
You seek immortality? I have what your soul longs for.
Do not underestimate me, I have been here a long time.
Serve me well and I might be able to bestow the Great King's favour unto you.
I know many secrets, including yours. Now, shall we bargain?
You are wise indeed to approach me – maybe a deal can be brokered?
Good, come to the Liche Lord, we have matters to discuss, yes?
I am troubled, do you have the answers I seek?
Maybe an accord? I would so like a visit to your White Tower
I have high hopes for an agreement, Elf.
I bring sand and heat, reptile, all for a small boon.
We are both worldly – an exchange of knowledge seems fair.
Where are your Old Ones, reptile?
Your jungles will be safe, Lizardman, simply make the pact.
You are vermin, but I may have a use for you.
What does your council propose, creature? I may have a counter-pledge.
Ah, your majesty, how may the Mortuary Cult serve?
I have sent Liche Priests to your side at once. Let them serve.
The resources of the Mortuary Cult are at your disposal… for a price.
The rebirth of Nehekhara comes, we share the same goals.
The desert gods talk to me – they encourage a pact.
Go back to your frozen wastes, dark one.
I have had enough of your doomed bloodline, Elf.
Prostrate yourself before a immortal god-king… then we shall speak!
My Liches advise caution, should I consider you a threat?
I note your bow borders on disrespect for my dynasty. It is noted.
Why do you not approach in the proper position of deference?
I care not for your mortal concerns, only what is right for my reign.
I am a vessel of Ptra - the Ever-living! Fear me, creature.
Your presence here, angers the god Khsar, and I am his follower.
You scheme like Sakhmet and, like that goddess, are nothing more than a concubine!
You have relics that belong to me – hand them over, creature!
What are you? Some fleshy thing that comes making demands!
My patience with Elves is at an end.
Does my existence offend you, reptile? Good.
The secrets you hoard are nothing next to those I have learnt and forgotten, reptile.
You dare summon me, Lizardman? The wrath of Khemri falls upon you!
What could you possibly offer a king, reptile?
Your filth is not wanted in my kingdom.
The Skaven are still a force in the world? How disappointing.
I note you are yet to bow… I expect you to show reverence first.
Nehekhara is mine - I am its Great King.
When I lived I was supreme. Death has not changed that.
The Realm of Souls has changed you – you disappoint me.
Your petty living desires bore me, let us discuss more important matters.
Well then, dark one, what could you offer a king?
Welcome to my realm. I have had eternity to gather my resources, what do you need?
The scarabs swarm… a fortuitous omen. We should take advantage.
So mortal creature, I have many trinkets – what is your still-beating heart's desire?
You come before a king, one that has reigned for aeons.
I chafe in my wrappings, do not put me in an even darker mood.
Who disturbs my slumber? Who dares wake a Tomb King?
Welcome to my kingdom. Offer proper tribute and a pact may be forthcoming.
You find me in an accepting mood – I have them every thousand years.
Greetings, creature, what manner of thing are you?
Do the sons of Ulthuan enter my kingdom of sand?
So much flesh on show, Elf, do you mock the Unliving?
What do the reptiles need with a king of Nehekhara?
Reptiles here? Should they not be basking on the banks of the Great Mortis?
Welcome, cold-blooded, we share many common desires.
Maybe we have common cause after all, Lizardman.
I shall suffer vermin if they can provide me with what I need.
Have you something to tempt me, Skaven? What has your gnawing uncovered?
We find ourselves in regal company – the great pacts of old are possible.
Together we could make Nehekhara great again. Let the restoration commence!
My dynasty has hosted you before. I cannot remember when.
Fellow crypt sovereign, I believe my pyramid is larger, but let us not get into that contest…
Come, let our Liche Priests compare demands. Meantime, we shall hunt the living!
Your petty tortures are nothing to my whims, Dark Elf. Do not test Settra!
Your magic is why I have this unpalatable form, do not anger me further!
You dare approach the Imperishable!
Bow, thrall, grovel before Settra, only then will I listen!
Prostrate yourself, and pray that I do not order your obliteration!
You invite the ire of the Great King – unwise and fatal for you.
Even Ptra gave me his sword, what will you offer, thrall?
What tribute could you possibly offer, other than an abject subservience?
Take in my majesty and quail, creature. Settra speaks.
Your petition has reached the Great King and is found wanting…
I am Settra – Blessed of Ptra, Lord of the Great Mortis River – who are you again?
Bury your head in the sands, but know that the desert is mine!
Back to your little island, little Elf, Nehekhara is no place for you.
I have killed so many of your Elf-kind, it bores me to prattle with you.
I have no time for primitive creatures. It easier just to annihilate them.
What does it say? Order it to speak our royal language!
You're race may have created this world, but *I* rule it!
I see no 'wise' ancient here. Just a feeble reptile, that dares address mighty Settra!
There is no place for vermin in my kingdoms.
There is nothing you could offer Settra, vermin, only your immediate deaths.
I have conquered your city-state before, should I do so again?
Your titles hit me like grains of sand in a storm. They are insignificant.
Bow to the Great King – beg for my grace – and I may spare your dynasty.
Who are you? I forget the names of thrall-kings, for they are so insignificant.
You are a vassal, do not forget your station when you commune with Settra!
Impress me with your cruelty, Dark Elf. I dare you.
Approach, Druchii, yes, I know your Eltharin name - Settra knows all!
Kneel before Settra! Only then may you petition me.
You have the attention of the Imperishable, do not squander it.
What tribute do you offer the Great King of Nehekhara?
I am Settra! You should bow before greatness.
Marvel at my pyramid, know that you will never achieve such majesty!
Do not invoke the gods around Settra - they bow to me!
You come before greatness, it is normal to feel overwhelmed.
Keep your head bowed, do not look upon my bandaged majesty!
You speak with Settra, King of Kings, know that you are not worthy.
Your tribute, thrall, for it is a privilege to be in my presence.
Think your arrogance can match mine, Elf? I am Settra!
You will bow to me Elf! I am your better! I am king!
Must I deal with this creature? Where is your handler?
What brings you from your moist jungle to these dry sands?
Your grasp of Nehekharan is impressive, creature, I shall hear your offer.
What happened in my long absence, that I must now parley with lizards?
Skaven, I have use for vermin, you may deign to be in my majesty.
Ruled by a council? How inferior. No one rules Settra!
Approach the Great King of Nehekhara, I may be merciful.
Come, vassal, what tribute do you pay Settra the All-king?
I have conquered your city-state before, should I do so again?
Perhaps an alliance? Although you WILL address me as sire.
Behold my pyramid, and know that mine will always be larger, as befits the Great King.
You should know better…
You will feed my cauldron of blood!
Why are you here? What web do you spin?
The blessings of Khaine be upon you!
Speak while you can, my wrath is terrible to behold!
My hatred for your kind boils my blood!
A misplaced word will mean your death, pray, speak.
Words cannot move me!
My blades are poised, enter at your peril!
Your words will seal the fate of your people.
I have a mind to slaughter you, convince me otherwise.
The Lord of Murder whispers his will to me.
Flee, while you still have the legs to do so!
Your blood will drench the earth this night!
Speak, but choose your words with care.
What foolish errand brings you before me?
I have little time, or love, for diplomacy.
Don't waste my time with petty intrigues.
Actions speak louder than words.
Bandying words with you will not please my Lord.
Who seeks the mistress of Har Ganeth?
Khaine abhors diplomacy, unless it leads to war…
Make haste, I have rites to lead.
Your timing is poor.
Hatred for you fills my soul and pleases my Lord!
You walk on the blade's edge, Asur!
Don't look down your nose at me, Asur!
Your weakness sickens me, cousin.
Cold blood is most pleasing to the Lord of Murder!
I will bathe in Lustrian blood and glory in your demise!
Your gods will not save you from my fury!
You would make a fitting tribute to my Lord!
Do not trifle with me, denizen of Lustria.
Speak, swamp creature, I have slaves to sacrifice!
Well, puppet of the Old Ones, what do you want?
What brings you from your false temples?
Your noxious blood is of no use to me!
My time is far more valuable than your life, rodent!
Vermin do not last long in the halls of Har Ganeth.
What can you possibly offer me, rodent?
I do not fear the dead! Speak, false King!
I do not recognise your right to rule, so called 'King'!
What arid winds have blown you hence?
The many ways of murder are wasted on you, Tomb King.
Your entrails will decorate the towers of Ghrond!
You are not fit to call yourself Druchii!
What little corner of Naggaroth have you crawled from?
You know of my powers and still you come?
I could kill you with a single word…
If your words displease me, I will cut out your tongue!
Those who cross me, do not live to tell!
I have such plans for the destruction of your people!
You dare to seek me?!
Dark omens follow you hence!
I will sear the meat from your bones!
Do not waste your last breath begging for mercy!
My heart is filled with hate for you and yours!
I have seen your death and it is gruesome!
Who seeks the Dark Convent?
What could you possibly have to offer me?!
You cannot begin to comprehend my power!
Do not appeal to my better nature, I don't have one!
If I must bandy words with you, at least make it quick!
The Supreme sorceresses of Ghrond are not known for their patience…
You would do well to kneel before me!
Try not to bore me, it won't end well for you.
Very well, I will hear your petition.
Ohh how your petty struggles bore me!
I will not rest until your whole race is destroyed!
My hatred for you is all consuming, Asur!
Weak Asur fools! You know nothing of the Winds of Magic!
I have power you wouldn't dare to dream of!
Your presence here affects the minds of my people like a fever!
The fall of your people is here, Lizardman!
Your jungles will burn, by my hand!
I have plans for your scaly corpse!
I struggle to follow your barbaric speech, lizard-thing!
Approach with caution, Lustrian. I am in a black mood…
You have found me, lizardman. Now, speak.
What brings the denizens of Lustria to the Dark Convent?
Speak, but know this. I will garrotte you with your own tail!
You have squeaked your last, Skaven!
Red eyes in the darkness, is that you Skaven?
Cease that infernal chittering and get to the point!
I enjoy an underhanded deed, but never at my expense, rodent!
My patience for your race is limited, Skaven!
I will lead you to your final rest, Tomb King!
Your liche priests are no match for me!
Long dead Kings of the sand, what do you seek?
Necromancy is a fascinating art, you, not so much!
Your hatred and malice will be your destruction, Druchii.
Lust for revenge consumes you utterly, dark one.
The hatred in your heart is noxious, Druchii.
You cast a long shadow over my homeland, dark one.
I see the truth hidden behind your words.
You cannot hide your heart from me.
Do not attempt to lie to me, I will know.
If you wish to see dawn, leave now.
Your intentions are clear to me, but speak your lies.
I expect naught but lies from you.
Your continued existence hangs in the balance.
Words cannot conceal the truth you hide.
Do not waste your breath, I already know what you seek.
You have a liars heart and a hateful gaze.
I bid you welcome, what do you wish to discuss?
Welcome to the court of the Everqueen.
You have my undivided attention.
All are welcome in my court.
Those who speak the truth are always welcome here.
We have much to discuss, come, join me.
I am the bright flower of the goddess, chosen of Isha.
You stand before the mistress of the undying forest.
The true of heart always find a warm welcome in my court.
What matters do you wish to lay before the Everqueen?
Those who forsake their own people face a terrible fate.
There is only one rightful ruler of Ulthuan.
Faithful servant of Ulthuan, what brings you here?
Child of Isha, what do you seek?
Choose your words with care, Lustrian.
My goddess stands with me, where are your gods?
Deliver your message, Lizardman.
Your blind faith is pitiful to look upon.
Children of the Old Ones, you are most welcome.
It is always a pleasure to welcome the denizens of Lustria.
Welcome, Lizardman. We have much to discuss.
Greetings, Lustrian. What brings you to the court of the Everqueen?
I read your intentions quite plainly, Skaven.
Squeak all you like, I already see your next move.
There is a terrible darkness upon your tiny heart, Skaven.
You think yourselves 'cunning'?
There is always a price to pay for necromancy, Tomb King.
The twisted magic that animates your withered corpse will consume you.
Kings of Nehekhara, I bid you welcome.
What is it you wish to discuss, Tomb King?
I will not entertain Druchii scum in my presence!
Nagarythe is not yours, filth, it never was or will be.
I have nothing to say to Druchii scum.
Don't expect a welcome in the Shadowlands Druchii.
I am eternal, nevertheless, my patience wears thin.
Do not mock me, my Shadow Warriors have only one answer to jests.
You dare interrupt my eternal vengeance?
Keep your demands short, I weary of mortal concerns.
My only concern is spilling the blood of traitors, and you are in my way.
Don't presume to stride where I patrol, that will be a fatal error.
If you are not of Nagarythe, you are the enemy.
Approach me if you must, I make no promises about drawing my bow.
You have the stench of Druchii on you, why should I not strike you down?
I despise weakness, and yet you are surrounded by it.
I will hear your plea, mortal.
You summon the Shadow King, do you serve with the warriors of Nagarythe?
Do  not look for me in the light, I lurk in shadow.
Greetings, I sway to Loec's tune, for whom do you dance?
The shadows come, the day wanes, are you prepared for dusk?
The Shadow Crown weighs heavily on my head, do not increase its burden.
You approach a dark throne, I pray you bring only light.
I kneel before Eothlir's tomb, will you bow beside me?
Yours is a short span, so why do you seek me out?
Come in peace, perhaps you may even leave Nagarythe that way too.
The hour grows late, what do you want southerner?
Your realms exist due to the Shadow Warriors, respect is due.
How are the realms of milk and honey? Their lustre protected by my folk.
You forget yourself. You speak to a King not a mere prince.
I welcome my southern kin… if I must.
How fares your soft southern realm, my kin?
Welcome to Nagarythe, kin, I hope it's not too shocking…
Tell your sleeping masters, that a pact with the Shadow King is unlikely.
This is a waste of time, the Lizards hold no hope for Nagarythe.
I rarely see Lizardmen where I roam, but I'm told we have common cause.
Very well, what are your conditions, Lizardmen, maybe a pact is possible.
Vermin should be purged, not bargained with.
Do not threaten me, rodent, you may lurk in the dark but I am the shadow.
Say your filth vermin, then be gone before I send my warriors your way.
You dare approach the Anar, Skaven, that is uncharacteristically brave… or lethal.
This world is for those whose soul remains free, not forgotten corpse kings.
Your position is weak, dead thing, don't think challenge me.
What do you want corpse? I make them, not negotiate with them.
I maybe a king of shadow, but you are a king of darkness - intriguing.
These seas are mine and my father's, not yours.
Go back to the Maelstrom, you do not belong on the open sea.
A Vampire Coast… I haven't heard anything so ridiculous in all my days at sea.
Sartosa claims these domains and I am her queen!
Before we begin, know that the treasure is mine.
You don't impress me, Druchii, I've killed your kind before.
I have asked the Seafather to rid the world of Dark Elves, but you're still here.
Shall we cut a deal? Or shall I cut your throat?
You come at me, lubber, but I am the daughter of the sea!
Harm me or my ship and risk the wrath of Manann!
I will parley with you, but if I don't like what I hear you'll be on your way to Stromfels' Lair!
The Seafather tasks me to destroy you… Why shouldn't I?
Salt and blood, fool, salt and blood - that's all you'll taste soon enough.
Choose your next words carefully; the Swordfysh has dry powder and is ready to fire.
My anger rises like the tide - don't test it.
A storm comes and you are in the eye.
Call me a mermaid… I dare you.
You can stick your pointy ears and your pristine sheets!
Skip the chatter, I just need to know about the plunder.
Come, frog-bastard, what have you got to bargain with?
I'll listen, reptile, but whether I care to act on your words is another matter.
Address me as captain, and I'll call you... toad-scum.
Stay in your dank holes, vermin, the sea is mine.
I have sunk the Skabrus. You do not threaten me, rat.
I'll seal you back in those tombs, bone-king.
I know what you are, desert king. Do you know my father, the God of Salt an' Sea?
Can you cross running water, Vampire? Some tales reckon not.
There's nought but saltwater in my veins, count.
This is all we need, another undead tyrant plying the waves. What do you want?
The next tide comes, as you should well know. So speak, ghoul.
I have already sunk one Dreadfleet, do you think yours intimidates me?
Perhaps we can parley like true pirates of Sartosa, even if I'm the only one who breathes.
The Seafather bequeaths me to listen, doesn't mean I have to like it.
Be warned, Naggarothi, I am as merciless as the ocean.
Think yourself cruel, Elf? A few cracks of my cat will change your mind.
You speak, Aranessa listens… for now.
Let us hope what you have to say pleases the mighty Seafather.
The Swordfysh is ready to sail, what do you want?
Do you wish to join us on this voyage?
I'm ready to cast off; this best be quick.
Ignore my crew, they're hungry - I usually sail with living ones, but Father commands…
I'm a pirate, of course you can trust me an' my crew - let's barter.
Fair winds and fairer tides, thanks to Manann… Now, what to barter?
Come on board, I'll guarantee your safety… as long as you bring good tidings.
Look port, then starboard... All you see is mine. Now you are informed, we can parley.
Tell me, have you seen Prince Yrellian recently? Is he still a daddy's boy?
How many masts does the Seadrake have? Answer correctly and we'll talk.
Do you come to trade some of that precious Slann gold of yours?
Talk to me Lizardman, if you can with that tongue in the way.
My scurvy crew tell me you come to offer things, rodent-man.
You don't scare me, Skaven. You're no Skretch Half-dead.
Let's hear what you have to say rag-man and I'll decide what's best for me.
I hear you keep a more than a few gems and a good bit of gold in those dusty tombs of yours…
What do you want, Vampire? My blood is too salty for you, I'll wager!
Just because I've started using crew past their prime, doesn't mean I'll take lessons from you.
You will find no plunder here admiral, only your annihilation.
Bow down to my hegemony over the seas and you will die quickly.
The sea has only one overlord, the rest of you are ants to be trampled.
The Druchii! Nothing but a deluded race of cattle.
Take in Noctilus' majesty and prostrate yourself, Dark Elf!
Do you offer anything more than just your vessel of a body for my crew?
The Galleon's Graveyard only offers death to your kind!
Your end shall be swift, but there will be much pain beforehand.
The cursed deeps shall be your watery grave!
I will profit from your stupidity in coming here today.
The decks of the Reaver have not tasted blood in a while…
Death comes to those who trespass into my midst.
Beg for your life, wretch, for you are at the mercy of Noctilus.
I shall hear you out before death lends you to my ranks.
Once you die, your body shall be another husk for my crew.
The decadent paradise of Ulthuan shall burn... along with the rest of the world!
For crossing me, the Asur shall meet their end. It is inevitable.
Not even the Old Ones can prevent your doom now!
Slann spells are cheap conjurings next to the power of the Maelstrom!
I will drown you like the pestilent vermin that you are.
Few creatures are more deserving to be put out of their misery.
A welcome a war between Undead cabals.
Your pathetic, Undying forms are no threat to my Necromantic prowess!
I have no qualms about taking the von Carsteins down once and for all!
We may share a bloodline, but you too shall be a slave to my will.
If I saw you as genuine competition, you would already be dead.
Sea-scrounger of the Undead, you surely come to join my darkling crew?
Which forsaken backwater did you float out of?
Your Black Arks may inhabit the seas, but the Bloody Reaver rules them.
Do you offer condemned slaves for me to turn into crewmen?
I'll always find profit in my dealings… even if it means murder.
Choose your words, for you stand before supreme power.
What petty offerings do you bring the great Noctilus?
In the business of despoilment, there's no time for games.
Pay tribute, or make war - it matters little, for either is desirable.
I will listen to the grovelling peon.
What do you want, thrall?
What compels you to be foolish enough to enter my realm?
Deliver your message, lamb. Or my servants may think you are for slaughtering.
I can smell your fear… I always can when your kind approaches.
You may be long-lived, but death is eternal.
Speak, then pray to your pitiful Elven gods that your words ring true!
An Undead Lizardman would indeed make for an interesting minion!
Your ancient games do not interest me in the slightest.
I have no taste for plague-ridden blood, ratman!
I may be immortal, but I have no time for your snivelling tones.
The darkness embraces all creatures of the dead, but I reserve judgement.
Like every good soldier of the dead, you should be serving me.
The von Carsteins’ petty dealings are of no interest to me any longer - they are weak.
Do not involve me in your Sylvanian squabbles, such insignificances bore me.
Don't compete with me for spoils, I've battled storms and won!
Vampires and pirate scum - I do not mix or interact with such things.
I have witnessed the currents of eternity; you pose no threat.
Pirate?' Don't tarnish me with that inane label, I am so much *MORE*!
Stromfels warned me about your crews - I am prepared.
Will Stromfels spare me from Elves! Light or dark - I'll drown them all!
Should I sing your death song in Druk-Eltharin, wretch?
Stromfels empowers me, and there is nothing you can do!
The performance will start… WHEN I SAY!
I am Madame Direfin, and your doom is nigh!
The arcane currents flow strong, there is nothing you can do!
Don't test me, ingrate, the power of Stromfels' wrath flows through me!
Can you match my voice…? I think not, fool.
Prepare to have your heart soar in ecstasy, and your soul taken!
I have brokered with storms! Bargained with gods! What are you?
You are nothing to the tides, so why should I care for your desires?
You poor fool, having to deal with me in this mood.
You had your chance, Elf. I would have sung a beautiful song for your king! Now I will end you!
No more Elves! I will sing to you when Ulthuan is drowning!
Stromfels despises you, reptile, as do I!
I see only scaly vermin before me.
Are you some kind of eel? I prefer lampreys…
A pointless audience. Why should I sing for a race that merely hisses?
There is a need for pest control I see.
What value does a songstress such as I have in dealing with a rat?
As I dominate the sands and the sea, your tombs shall echo with MY voice.
I shall sing to you, Tomb King, and you'll bow to my majesty for a change!
Your time is at an end, blood-sucker, the siren of the storms is here!
Don't threaten me, Vampire, my voice can shatter your skull!
Another wave-wanderer. Do you wish to parley with moi?
Oh, another with a vigorous crew! Do they like entertainments?
I hate pirates. Filthy, greedy creatures… yet, there may be an opportunity here.
Unlike you, I am not dead... just between bodies.
Welcome to the Lamprey, pirate. Let me sing for you.
Your kind has had such a tragedy - I can do tragic...
What do you bargain, Dark Elf, I have no use for living slaves…
You address the greatest songstress, living or dead - why are you worthy of my time?
You stand before me - to what do I owe such an ovation?
At last, an audience! We shall speak in the intermission.
Your plaudits I'll take… your criticism isn't needed.
Should I sing for you?
Come, we shall talk, then I shall sing, then you will do as I say…
Approach the Madame-Captain… what do you offer?
The Lady blessed me with this voice, superior even to her own… and now you get to hear it.
What souls will you give? For the rest of you to live?
I have performed to royalty, sung for the greatest kings… why must I entertain you?
You are not the Phoenix King! I shall only sing for the Elf sovereign and that tune will signal his drowning!
At last, a truly appreciative crowd. I will sing for you, Elf, and you will be amazed.
Reptile, do you have ears? Can you even fathom beautiful music?
The Lizardmen of Lustria! Owners of many pretty, sparkly baubles…
Come my cold-blooded friend, let me sing to you of a pact.
See the reptile, pull its tail, make it roar, make it crave bloody war…
I hate vermin, especially talking vermin. Speak if you must!
What do you want, ratman?
Such ugly things. May I bring beauty to your existence with my voice?
Do you appreciate art? Can your bandaged ears hear me sing? If so, we may talk.
I've encountered your kind before, Vampire. Will you also be a patron of the arts?
The next performance is due, Vampire. I expect a rapturous applause.
The galleon always has space for more booty!
Free wealth is always welcome, though the crew may have preferred to plunder for it!
Don’t expect such generosity to be reciprocated.
You have my agreement… but if this is a trick, Druchii scum, it will not end well for you.
A typically hollow offer from your treacherous kind, but one I cannot decline.
The Dark Ones drive a hard bargain, but we have a deal.
Dealings with Naggaroth rarely end well, but let us see where this takes us.
From one sea-reaver to another, I accept.
Perhaps it is your Dark Arts at work here, but we have reached an accord.
I would sooner see those long limbs of yours torn from your body... but you have my acceptance.
I accept the Asur’s pathetic terms. Now be gone, before you are made to walk the plank!
The sea can often be fickle with what it provides us, Elf, so I must accept.
As long as 'the greater good' you claim to work towards also benefits me, we can do business.
The time of the Asur may have passed, but I can see the advantage in agreement.
I would usually not care about such things, but you have me convinced today.
I agree, but your slithering, scaly kind will soon lament this day!
I will exercise restraint and accept, instead of spilling your cold blood.
I’ll accept, if only to get your foul kind out of my sight.
I am unsure about you estranged reptiles... but your offer is acceptable.
You jungle-dwellers rarely offer such intriguing options. I accept.
Your ends are a mystery, Lizardman, but I feel there is advantage in this agreement.
You may have your way this day, but this acceptance does not rule out your future death!
I had planned on killing you today, but circumstances dictate that I must accept. Next time, perhaps…
You are fortunate, there are just enough reasons for me to accept this offer instead of killing you.
The deal is done, but know that I would sooner cut you than be double-crossed.
I know not what you are plotting, but I will play along for now.
Such a satisfactory offer will be regarded with suspicion… but is accepted.
We accept. We may be brigands, but we do not stab our business partners – not in the back, at least.
Good! If it pleases you, help yourself to my admirals' supplies of rum on your way out.
Only a fool would turn this down.
As with most vermin, I’d usually not waste my time on you, but on this occasion I must agree.
I have no choice – typical of you stinking Skaven to manipulate circumstances to your own ends!
The rodent’s proposal cannot be overlooked.
I’m not a gambler, but I will take any advantage presented to me, even if it did come from a rat!
No mere scavengers, are you? Enough bargaining – I accept.
A compelling offer – your scurrying rat-claws have certainly done the legwork.
We will do this your way, but let it be known – you and your Undead minions will soon serve me!
This deal will only delay your inevitable destruction, sand-zombie! The Tomb Kings are not imperishable!
I did not think the desert could offer anything useful to me, but I was clearly mistaken.
I care not for the schemes of long-dead priests, but I can do business with them.
The Undying kind certainly know a good deal - I would know.
We have a deal, Nehekharan.
May your ships be scuppered for forcing me into this position!
Have your way this time, pretender, but the ocean will never be big enough for the two of us!
A deal made without spilt blood is proof that sometimes there *is* honour amongst thieves.
A tactful offer. I am accustomed to profiting from more incompetent pirates.
The sea fosters understanding!
It is fortunate that we see eye to eye, for piracy is a cutthroat business.
Sylvanian treachery never ceases to amaze! You leave me no choice!
Have your terms, you pathetic excuse for a creature of the night!
I know the Vampires of the land love to squabble, but you have no disagreement with me.
Though I care very little for your petty affairs, I am not averse to doing things your way.
Of course, it is more favourable to do business with ones closer to my kind.
It is easier to come to terms with those who see things from a similar perspective.
Good! It seems you are not as stupid as you appear.
A wise choice. If you’d declined, I’d have to kill you.
Whichever god it is you pray to has guided you well!
Very well, but death always comes sooner to those who betray the sea's children.
We had an understanding! This will not end well!
You will pay for this. Mark my words!
Take heed, for you will live to regret this… or die for it.
You must have a good reason to turn this down. Is it stupidity?
The arrogance! Be grateful that these terms were not offered at the edge of a cutlass!
Finally! The deckhands thirst for murder and plunder!
There shall be all the more slaves for my ranks!
I will enjoy destroying you and your weak followers!
The treaty is off. We do not need your favour!
Did you actually think a pact with a pirate would last?
Friendship is a landlubber’s concept!
Your money or your life!
A little gold goes a long way.
You’d do well to stay on my good side. The sea can be a perilous place.
Sail with us to blood-soaked glory!
The wind fills our sails and blows us towards war! Let’s crush these wretches!
Your murderous ranks would be useful to us in the coming fight.
I’m not averse to feeding you to the Prometheans, Druchii! Alas, I come for business, not pleasure.
I’d sooner obliterate every one of your pathetic Black Arks, Elf-dog! But today I shall throw you a bone.
Consider these demands, and you might even end up with something to take back to your bleak shores.
Do the deluded Dark Ones know a good deal when they see one?
Many see us both as pirates, Naggarothi, but that should not prevent us from profiteering together.
We both know how to reap the profits of the sea, so you will surely see the benefit in this deal.
Elves do love the sound of their own voices, don’t they? Now shut up and listen!
Although I’m here to negotiate, we both know I’d rather be burning Ulthuan’s cities to the ground!
Contain your ego for just a moment, Asur, and hear these terms.
Though are vocations differ, that is no reason not to do business…
Surely there are some things that even the affluent Elves would want?
I have something that might interest you. I’m sure the Phoenix King would agree.
Cease your unintelligible reptilian babble for just one moment and listen!
Though I would rather see those flapping, forked tongues cut out of your misshapen heads, there are matters to discuss.
I care little for your incomprehensible motives, but we must talk.
Compose yourselves, Lizardmen. I come to offer a deal, not a fight.
Is there time in your strange schemes for a little business with us?
I know the children of the Old Ones are no fools, so I trust we can see eye to eye.
Hold your tongue and listen, or I'll feed it to one of the Scurvy Dogs!
These are our terms. Accept them and you might get out of this alive.
Be warned, rejection of our terms is often followed by a brisk walk off the plank!
I’ve sailed far to get here, so listen carefully.
I bring terms. What say you?
Do we have a deal? I haven’t got all day!
There is a way to further both our causes.
There’s no reason why we can’t both have our way, would you not say?
I assure you, we can both gain an advantage from this…
Any day I am forced to do business with a rat is to be lamented!
Even you virulent, flea-ridden, wretches must see the benefit in this.
I’m told that the giant rodents have a bit of business acumen, and are not just brainless parasites…
Take it or leave it. I do not want to spend a second longer than necessary in your pestilential presence.
There is a greater scheme at work here, and I know the Skaven like a good scheme…
We are both unwholesome creatures, so I think we can find a way to benefit one another.
I’d happily test how imperishable you really are, but there are more important matters at hand.
Though I despise the Tomb Kings, one can’t always choose their business partners.
Come now, what kind of a 'king' would turn down such an offer?
To say your time has passed would be an understatement, Nehekharan, yet this may still interest you.
You are as old as the sands of your homelands, Priest King, but has time has granted you wisdom?
The Unliving do their best business with the Unliving, I'm sure you'll agree.
I would send your minions back down to their watery graves if I did not have to offer you this!
The ocean only sustains you because I allow it to! Now hear these terms!
Put away your cutlasses and listen. I wouldn’t want to have to kill you prematurely.
I do not usually tolerate those who challenge my rule over the waves, but I am willing to make a business exception.
A pirate knows what a pirate wants.
We both know the ocean is unforgiving, but perhaps we can help one another?
Hear my terms, or I will force you to walk the plank in the midday sun!
If I did not have this deal to put to you, I would show you the true extent of my power!
Keep your cheap conjurings to yourself, Sylvanian. I bring a proposition, not a fight.
Halt your petty preoccupations for just a second, and listen.
You may not be sailors, but you are Vampires, so I think we can see eye to eye.
The landlubbers of Sylvania are not above a deal, are they?
The ocean could be a much less perilous for you, if you would only consider this pact.
You could do no wrong by being on our good side.
Only an unwise leader would not see the sense in accepting these terms.
There is much to gain for you here, Druchii, but do not bite off more than you can chew.
The Dark Ones aren’t so foolish to turn down a pact with us, I hope.
You High Elves love to talk, but if you care for your kind, you would do well to listen.
You’ll be glad to know that I am not here to wage war, Elf.
A treaty with us is worth its weight in Slann Gold!
This will surely please your inscrutable gods.
Twitchy you may be, rodent, but even you must understand the value of a treaty.
You may see this as gaining an advantage, but it is no more than circumstances force me to offer.
The passage of time might not affect the either of us, Nehekharan, but I haven’t got forever to wait for an answer.
Has your immortality given you the wisdom to make the right choice here?
It’s not in my nature to offer a treaty to a freebooting rival, but ends justify these means.
An agreement between us has the potential to be as destructive as an ocean tempest.
I know the pettiness of Vampires, but I also know you are smart enough to see the sense in a treaty.
A treaty between the forces of Undeath will instil fear in the living!
Though we are not typically ones to share, the ship’s hold bursts with loot.
Let us share the successes of our despoilments.
A gift of booty!
Our pistols and broadsides are ready. We only need someone to kill!
The deckhands are eager to fight, and your enemies will make good cannon-fodder.
I love the smell of black powder in the morning!
The admirals grow weary of this conflict.
We tire of picking on lesser foes, so are willing to broker a peace.
We’ve had our fill of booty from you! There are other shores to pillage…
You offer us nothing, Naggarothi – we even tire of killing you.
The Dark Ones may never know peace, but your futures will be bleaker if you do not accept this.
Lucky for you, we’ve decided our attentions are better directed towards others.
I assume Ulthuan would prefer to exist in peace?
We have decided that you and your fetid homelands are no longer of interest to us.
The sea offers us other opportunities – we have little time for this war.
I’m not averse to exterminating vermin, but this fight has run its course.
Even when you drown, you infect the waters around you! Enough of this conflict!
Since many of us are immortal, it may be best to end this conflict, lest it never ends at all…
A good king, living or dead, does what is best for his followers, tomb-dweller.
Just because we are both despoilers of the sea does not mean we must be enemies.
The sea craves to be still once more, at least for the time being.
This war is a waste of our Undead minions.
I am familiar enough with the Sylvanian Vampires to know they prefer peace to subservience.
This is laughable! We answer to no-one, least of all you!
Our pistols, cutlasses, and broadsides are for our purposes, and no-one else’s!
I can see why you would want our help, but we are not in the business of fighting for others.
I enjoy the overwhelming stench of your fear far too much to consider a peace.
I would not want to disappoint the fleet with a cease-fire, there are still many of you to kill!
No! This will not end until your rotting corpses are fish food!
I did not know the Naggarothi were quitters. This war will not end that easily!
Your words of peace are as futile as your pathetic Dark Arts!
You can’t talk yourself out of war with us, Elf, no matter how good with words you are!
Never! Ulthuan’s beaches shall be drenched red with your blood!
We will burn your jungle realms to the ground! There will be no escape!
Beg for mercy, lizard. Though your forked tongues offer peace, I see it for the pathetic grovelling that it is!
The desperation of the Skaven shows their weakness. This war shall continue until their destruction!
Peace with us is a fruitless endeavour, rat!
You cannot rid yourself of our ire that easily, Nehekharan!
Whether at sea or in your forsaken desert realm, there is nowhere you are safe from us!
There can be no peace between us until your fleets lie wrecked on the ocean floor!
Your waters are our waters! Do not attempt to claim legitimacy, you cannot escape your destruction!
You will not be spared... Sylvania will fall!
We shall not relent until the pathetic Vampires of the land are no more!
Take your pathetic offer back to your frozen hovels!
Not even your Dark Arts could convince me that this paltry offer is worthwhile!
The Witch King can do better than that!
Maybe if you threw in one of those Black Arks of yours?
Your silver tongue may be able to convince me of much, Naggarothi, but not this.
While I distrust your kind least of all the Elven races, I cannot accept this offer.
I have no time for you scheming Elves, your offers only serve your meddlesome ways!
The Phoenix King must think me an idiot!
No deal, Elf. My fleet will profit little from this.
Even the most skilled orators of Ulthuan could not convince me to accept this.
With all your eloquence, it is a pity your offer really does not interest me.
We may be on good terms with the Asur, but I would be a fool to accept.
The denizens of the sea do not mix with lizard-freaks!
This offer is as much a joke as those useless pyramids of yours!
Whatever your mysterious ends, I care not for them.
Come now, I know Lustria has better things to offer.
I cannot agree to your terms today, Lizardman.
The will of your strange gods will not be carried out today.
Until the sea swallows you whole and never spits you out, never!
You’ll walk the plank for this insult!
You call this an offer? Get out of my sight, before I feed you to the Scurvy Dogs!
We have no need for your business.
You may be brave for coming here, but you are also witless for thinking I would accept your offer.
A nice thought, but the barnacles on my galleon are worth more than this.
An interesting proposal, but I cannot accept.
A better offer might be worth negotiating, but not this.
I can tolerate your company, yes, but I can’t agree to your terms.
The only thing that’s going to happen here is the Scurvy Dogs getting the taste for rat-meat!
I’d sooner see you all drown, as is befitting of all pestilent rodents!
We shall not be tricked into dealings with the Skaven!
Your barely coherent chittering has only confirmed that this was a waste of my time.
Tempting as this offer may be, I am wary of deals with the Skaven.
It is just too difficult to trust the word of a rat.
It would bring me much greater joy to put you deluded Undead 'kings' out of your misery!
I will only consider terms that involve your annihilation, Nehekharan!
I do not accept this offer, nor your legitimacy as king.
It is laughable that you think I would accept an offer from a walking relic.
Though I admire that little Undead empire of yours, I cannot accept.
There’s just not enough in this for me, Tomb King.
I would sooner destroy you and the putrid souls that serve you on your wretched fleets!
A pathetic excuse for a fleet, and a pathetic excuse for an offer to boot!
You must have had a little too much rum if you think I’d accept this.
The ocean realms have witnessed few more audacious offers than this!
As much as I like to do a deal with a fellow denizen of the sea, I cannot accept.
We have sufficient booty, and have no need for anything more.
I would rather give my Vampire Admirals the pleasure of purging their weak Sylvanian cousins!
The days of the land Vampires are numbered, there is no use in trying to bargain your way out!
You Sylvanians reek of desperation and fear, as does this pitiful offer!
The selfish and conniving von Carsteins will not get their way.
What a pity, I thought Sylvania could offer me more.
I can just about tolerate you landlubbing Vampires, but this is not a deal I can accept.
Our broadsides have you in their sights and they bring your destruction!
My Undead crew shall revel in burning your hovels to the ground! Your souls are booty!
We shall bring a tide of death from the sea to sweep over your entire race!
Your Black Arks have meddled in our dominion for the last time!
Dark Magic cannot overcome the power of black powder, Naggarothi!
Ulthuan’s shores shall be stained red with High Elf blood!
Our cutlasses and guns shall be idle no more, Asur!
War is upon you, Lizardman!
My fleets shall bring death and despoilment to your entire race, puny reptile!
I look forward to hearing the anguished screeching of you and your burning brethren, ratman!
Time to exterminate your verminous race once and for all!
I shall pulverise your ancient civilisation back into the sands once and for all, desert-dog!
A war of the Unliving it is, then!
Ready your scurvy crews, for they’ll soon either be dead or dead and serving me!
As it is on land, it is at sea – the weak succumb to the poor, and succumb you will!
I’ve always wanted to end Sylvania’s hegemony over the creatures of the night, and so it shall be!
The old order of Vampire Counts has had its day, I shall see to that!
Better captains than you have met their end trying to best me!
Have you come to grovel before your Pirate King?
All the sea is mine! All of it!
You think yourself sadists, but I can show you true pain, Naggarothi!
My cutlass has felled many Dark Elves, and can easily kill one more.
One part of me wants to hear you speak, another wants to kill you.
I might kill you, but worry not - an empty vessel still has a purpose!
The Winds may shun me, but I am still a master at inflicting pain.
More cattle for the slaughter!
Your timing could not be better! The Scurvy Dogs are due a feed.
You must be eager to become fish food.
Watch your words, they will likely be your last.
I’m happy to fulfil your death wish. Is that not why you have come?
The Pirate King is no pawn! I will end you!
You are a problem. I solve problems by killing them.
Let’s see if the Asur can dodge bullets!
Your time has long passed, you white-garbed fools! Bow to me now!
Your Lustrian strongholds shall never be safe until I find what I seek!
I will beat the secrets of the Slann out of you if I must!
Stinking rats! Nothing but plague-blooded vermin!
Filth always comes to the surface.
I will put you right back in the sand, Nehekharan!
The only Unliving king round here is me, dune-dweller!
Cheap conjurings are no match for black powder, Vampire lord!
There is no more pathetic a Vampire than a Sylvanian.
Tread carefully, sailor – we both know there is little honour between pirates.
What pact do you offer, fellow admiral of the night?
You are a long way from your waters, freebooter.
Do you come to trade the plunder of your Corsairs, Druchii?
Those Black Arks of yours are quite the galleons.
Don't waste my time, or I shall have you walk the plank!
I'm not sure if I want to cut a deal with you… or just cut you.
I've decided not to kill you, but my minds can be fickle…
Know that my deckhands' rotten eyes watch you closely.
I cannot guarantee your safety. Especially from me…
Speak up, I may not hear you over the voices.
Can I offer you some blood-infused rum?
Wealth for my coffers or souls for my crew?
Request what you will, but I answer to no-one except my selves!
What message do you bring for the Vampire Coast?
I hope you bring trinkets of your pompous civilisation.
What does Ulthuan want of Harkon?
We sensed your cold blood in the air, Lizardman.
Are you here to trade? I will pay handsomely for Slann artefacts!
You Skaven are a scourge on this world… a bit like me.
I usually only see rats jumping off sinking ships.
You smell worse than my decomposing deckhands, tomb-thing.
The Unliving has-beens of Nehekhara grace us with their presence.
Urgh… land-Vampires… the most pitiful of all.
Tell us, is Sylvania still under the petty von Carsteins' yolk?
Back to the Maelstrom with you and your inferior dead!
You have risen from Stromfels' clutches, but I'll send you back to the depths!
There is no sea or coast where you are welcome.
Don't think to fool me, pirate, I have been on the waves far too long.
Get back on Neferata's leash! There is only one power upon the ocean.
You do not frighten me, Elf. Your kind only feign piracy - we have it in our blood!
Do the minions of Mathlann claim the waves? The sea is ours, for we harness the ghoulwinds!
Straight to the plank with you!
The pistols aimed at you may be rusty but they can still kill.
Enough prevaricating! I'll see a pact or you'll be zombies before the next tide!
The sea despises you - I can feel her anger.
Make your offer quickly - I wish to be off by the next tide.
I am a pirate of the Great Ocean! What could you possibly offer me?
Morrslieb hangs low and the tides are shifting in my favour. Do not defy me.
I have the sea and the beasts within, what can you claim?
I'll make this easy - give me your treasure or I'll consume you all.
My fangs are as sharp as your wits are dull.
Let the High Elf talk. If their words displease us we'll simply string them up by their ears.
So pure and gleaming! How I long to despoil your white gowns with blood and salt.
Do not test me, reptile, your kind should already be extinct!
Another lost race that shall quickly be forgotten. What are your terms, lizard?
If the Skaven moves one jittery inch, kill it and throw its carcass back to its own hungry followers.
I have no patience for the vermin - send them back to Captain Skretch.
You come from sand, Tomb King, but the sea is not afraid of the beach!
How are those dusty tombs? Still full of MY treasure?
Greetings, von Carstein, should I dilute your bloodline with saltwater?
You land-Vampires are all the same, obsessed with status. Out here only blood and spoils matter.
An impressive ship, no doubt, but I'd wager we can still outgun you.
I invoke the code: let no blood be taken before a deal is struck.
Like you, we have no use for breathers. Perhaps we have common cause?
Let us talk treasure and blood, the only things that matter.
Best you secede this tide to us. It'll work out best for all involved.
Dark Elves - I've heard there is ice in your blood.
Give me a moment of your time, Naggarothi.
Ah, there you are. Let's barter.
Consider this a chance to impress me.
Now, are we all ship-shape and ready to parley?
Don't worry, I won't curse you - I'll just damn you to my service.
I hope you're prepared to suck lemons. Don't want scurvy dogs in my fleet.
I'm all for it, it's just the crew that aren't best pleased…
Come aboard. We'll drink port... nice, ruby-red port…
The sea's Undead are always open to profitable opportunities.
Don't let my appearance fool you, I'm as bloodthirsty as any on this ship.
Welcome aboard, but don't get comfy, or your stay may be indefinite!
Join us on my deck... I have a fondness for Elf blood.
Don't flatter yourself, Elf, I've been to Ulthuan and found it wanting…
The cold-blooded - let's see what you have to offer.
Don't even think about shattering my mind, as you did with Harkon.
I've drained Skaven before - it's vile.
You have no power on the sea, vermin, why should I listen to you?
You look a bit dry, your highness. Nothing a bit of saltwater can't solve.
Are your organs pickled in brine? Did they pickle that brain of yours too?
I have little time for aristocrats… especially the dead ones.
Don't compare me to Isabella, I'm much more lethal…
Back to the Maelstrom with you and your inferior dead!
You have risen from Stromfels' clutches, but I'll send you back to the depths!
There is no sea or coast where you are welcome.
Don't think to fool me, pirate, I have been on the waves far too long.
Get back on Neferata's leash! There is only one power upon the ocean.
You do not frighten me, Elf. Your kind only feign piracy - we have it in our blood!
Do the minions of Mathlann claim the waves? The sea is ours, for we harness the ghoulwinds!
Straight to the plank with you!
The pistols aimed at you may be rusty, but they can still kill.
Enough prevaricating! I'll see a pact or you'll be zombies before the next tide!
The sea despises you - I can feel her anger.
Make your offer quickly - I wish to be off by the next tide.
I am a pirate of the Great Ocean! What could you possibly offer me?
Morrslieb hangs low and the tides are shifting in my favour. Do not defy me.
I have the sea and the beasts within, what can you claim?
I'll make this easy - give me your treasure or I'll consume you all.
Salt, blood and plunder - a pirates life for me! As for you…
Let the High Elf talk. If their words displease us we'll simply string them up by their ears.
So pure and gleaming! How I long to despoil your white gowns with blood and salt.
Do not test me, reptile, your kind should already be extinct!
Another lost race that shall quickly be forgotten. What are your terms, lizard?
If the Skaven moves one jittery inch, kill it and throw its carcass back to its own hungry followers.
I have no patience for the vermin - send them back to Captain Skretch.
You come from sand, Tomb King, but the sea is not afraid of the beach!
How are those dusty tombs? Still full of MY treasure?
Greetings, von Carstein, should I dilute your bloodline with saltwater?
You land-Vampires are all the same, obsessed with status. Out here, only blood and spoils matter.
An impressive ship, no doubt, but I'd wager we'd still outgun you.
I invoke the code: let no blood be taken before a deal is struck.
Like you, we have no use for breathers. Perhaps we have common cause?
Let us talk treasure and blood, the only things that matter.
Best you secede this tide to us, it'll work out best for all involved.
Dark Elves - I've heard there is ice in your blood.
Give me a moment of your time, Naggarothi.
Ah, there you are. Let's barter.
Consider this a chance to impress me.
Now, are we all ship-shape and ready to parley?
Don't worry, I won't curse you - I'll just damn you to my service.
I hope you're prepared to suck lemons. Don't want scurvy dogs in my fleet.
I'm all for it, it's just the crew who aren't best pleased…
Come aboard. Let's discourse - we'll drink port... nice, ruby-red port…
The sea's Undead are always open to profitable opportunities.
Make your tribute - will it be to Stromfels, Shyish or Nagash?
You'd look worse for wear too after plying the seas for centuries.
Join us on my deck - I have a fondness for Elf blood.
Don't flatter yourself, Elf, I've been to Ulthuan and found it wanting…
The cold-blooded - let's see what you have to offer.
Don't even think about shattering my mind, as you did with Harkon.
I've drained Skaven before; it's vile.
You have no power on the sea, vermin, so why should I listen to you?
You look a bit dry, your highness; nothing a bit of saltwater can't solve!
Are your organs pickled in brine? Did they pickle that brain of yours too?
I have little time for aristocrats… especially the dead ones.
Ah, the dusty land-locked nobles of the last age - do come aboard.
I am the true lord of the sea. You lifeless scum do not impress me.
Your plunder is my plunder, pirate, so make your petty offer.
Your ship does not intimidate me, corpse-captain, I am Lord of the Blessed Dread!
So it is the pirates of the grave-seas come before the Kraken? Do not threaten what you cannot defeat.
Will Mathlann spare me from these zombie pirates littering the seas!
Do not challenge me, kin, I rule the waves and Mathlann's reach is long.
I see you Druchii, but do you see me? Do you witness what I wear? Then bow.
Hush, fool, a simple whispered order from me will see you dead, so tread lightly.
Come, kin, impress me, or the slave decks will have another to fill its cages.
While on my deck, you will do as I command.
Tell me why I shouldn't have you sent to my slave decks?
I raid and enslave… Tell me, why should I not include you in the latter?
Whatever bargain or parley you expect, know that the Krakenlord always gets the spoils!
If you board the Tower of Blessed Dread you must expect the hospitality of Karond Kar.
I have sacked the Temple of Gilgadresh and slaughtered the tigers of Ind. You think me intimidated by you?
I am the Kraken, scion of Mathlann, master of the seas; you'd best bow.
My crew thirsts to spill your blood; tell me why I shouldn't let them?
I come with the might of the Blessed Dread. You cannot stop me.
The Krakenlord comes, and all you may do is beg for mercy!
There is nothing you can say, Asur. Your sires will spend their lives in my slave holds.
I will take everything from you, hated kin. Squeak your pitiful terms.
The lizards are a dying race. Just give yourselves to me, it will save a lot of bother.
Do the reptiles come to plead with me - is that part of their 'Great Plan'?
Come, reptile. Let us hope you speak druhir, creature.
You prophesise my death, reptile, but it is only yours I see.
Do not try my patience, rat. I will skin and feed your carcass to the beasts under my ark.
Cower, vermin, for you have my attention.
Vex me and I'll strip whatever skin remains from your bones, liche-captain.
Why do the dead plague me so? Now the desert-walkers hound the Krakenlord.
The dry dead always leave me parched… for murder.
Your kind - living or dead - have no place upon Mathlann's ocean.
Put your fangs away! I dominate here.
Greetings, sea-rival; why has Mathlann altered the currents to ensure we meet?
The sea-dead come to me, but the Krakenlord is far from impressed…
What do you seek, ghoul? My deference? Let us see what you offer first.
Call yourself a pirate? Because you puppet a few drowned corpses? I am not impressed.
The Vampires, hags and ghosts of the sea - playing pirate… how risible.
Welcome. You are a guest upon my ark… do not displease me.
Fellow Druchii, will you join my crew? Do you believe you have a choice?
This is my domain, Druchii, for I am King of the Blessed Dread. What do you seek?
I will hear you, Elf-kin, but do not mistake my patience for predisposition.
Welcome to the Blessed Dread, will you be staying?
The Krakenlord cometh; your obedience is required!
You are about to experience the hospitality of Karond Kar…
Bow before the Kraken and I may hold a sliver of mercy.
Make your entreaty quickly, there are mortals to enslave.
Every skull that decorates this deck adds to my legend. Why should I not take yours?
Call me 'Lord Fellheart'. I am much more than a mere captain.
You have my attention. The question is what will you do with it?
Don't be scared by my helm, as intimidating as it is… fear the being that wears it!
Amuse the Krakenlord of Karond Kar… or suffer my displeasure.
You are prey, Asur. Should the eagle listen to the mouse's plea?
Oh, Asur child, the fun I can have with you and yours.
Why should I talk to you, traitor, when I can enslave you?
Prostrate yourself all you want, Ulthuan's coasts are mine to scour.
I'll hear you, lizard, but the Krakenlord makes no oaths or pacts.
I have slain many of your kind, ancient one. Do you offer me more?
Lizardmen is what mankind calls you. How like them to name you after themselves.
You send an envoy to my vessel, but for what purpose? In the hope I will cease despoiling your temple-cities?
Why should the Kraken speak to the rodent?
Vermin? On my deck? This isn't a sinking ship!
Come, bone-clanker, creature of Nethu, what do you propose?
Speak, dead-thing, but know that I only have use for the living on my ark - even the slaves must breathe.
What do you want, ghoul?
Say what you must, dead-thing.
Ahh, Gorl! I like its shine. Many thanks.
If you think to bribe us with valuables, it won't work. These are gifts and will be treated as such – with our gratitude – but that is where the matter ends.
We have many words for gold, for nothing gleams like it. This will be placed in the vaults with our thanks!
Good, we shall strike out a grudge in the Dammaz Kron in acknowledgement.
A wise move from a race so prone to blunders…
Very well, there may be hope for you yet.
I might have known, oathbreakers!
An oath means nothing to you! We'll have our vengeance!
Into the Great Book of Grudges you go, treaty-breakers!
Careful now, that was an honourable offer. You do not want to offend the Dawi.
Reject us!? Just what kind of unbaraki scum are you?
I'd have taken the offer and been grateful to boot, but I expected nothing less.
By Grimnir's Axe, you'll rue the day for this outrage!
War it is! Be careful what you wish for, urk!
You are due a reckoning. Soon, it will come.
As you have broken many clauses in said treaty, it is void – our honour remains intact.
The Reckoners have studied the treaty, and found it wanting. Consider it cancelled.
There is no treaty, no union between us! This was a mistake that might see me take the Slayer Oath yet.
Take up your az and join us, surely your honour demands it?
Do not sully your ancestors with cowardice, the time for war is now!
War calls! Answer its summons and become mighty under your god's scrutiny!
You owe us. Pay up or make ready for war.
The account is due, see that the settlement is sent.
I present a bill, it will need paying – not a coin more or less.
I have no time for your fripperies, umgi – this is our demand.
You have tested our patience long enough, if you wish to tread near the Grey Mountains again you'll hear us out.
Let Valaya and the Lady talk through us, manling, and know that profit for both can follow.
Maybe there is time for one last alliance between men and Dawi?
We both worship great rinn gods of beauty worthy of our ancestors; there is much to bind us, umgi.
We'll drink your grape-water, manling, but insist that you take a pint of Grimbold's Firecracker as well. Then we can talk about other dull things...
Hear us, Chaos grobitz – our demands are simple!
The Karaz Ankor is far from done yet, Chaos scum – hear us!
It leaves a bitter taste upon my tongue and a stink in my whiskers, but I must make a request.
Even you must break from killing, Northmen. When you do, we have an offer.
Will the Chaos-kin, not listen? Doesn't your vile God trade in promises and pacts?
We may have to take your tainted gorl, and hope that Valaya is not listening when such a promise is made.
Are you from Karak Zorn? Do you not speak Khazalid? We demand an audience!
You shame us all with your actions. In the name of the High King, hear us!
We must unite as the Karaz Ankor of old – so receive our offer.
Do we not all ask for Grimnir's strength when we wield our axes? Then let us talk.
Fellow Dawi, let us share a tankard of Bugman's and put the world to rights!
Eventually, all must bow before the Throne of Power. Why not do so now?
You have disappointed us, and to think you share the same blood of Sigmar – now there was a manling we could trust!
No, umgi, you will listen to us!
Perhaps the men of the Empire are ready to talk with their old allies?
Will the men of Sigmar be great again? Will they hear us out?
Come, men, let us drink your watery brews and talk of offers and trade.
We are impressed by the Emperor, he recalls in us the great Lords of your race. The End Times approach, now is the time for the alliances of old to be renewed.
Listen, grobi filth, before I take your ears myself!
I demand your Warboss hears us now or we will wipe your stinking tribe from above and below!
We have demands, Greenskin. Ones you would be wise to act upon!
By Grungni's anvil, I despise what I must do here – yet we have an offer to make.
Come Orc, maybe there is a profit in these talks…
For once we may be able to resolve our differences without spilling blood… although, I doubt it.
Hear us, or my axe will speak in our stead.
By my beard, I'll make my demands clear and you'd best hear them.
Do you think we will suffer this outrage? Our demands are plain…
We have an offer, but one that must be answered quickly.
The Dawi rarely make requests, so you'd best take note before we change our minds.
By Morgrim's hammer, will you not hear our offer?
Come now, the Clans promise there is profit to be made by being open to this offer.
Do you wish to hear our offer or not? The Guilds press upon me to make it.
Listen to my request and then we will drink good, Dwarfish ale until our beards curl!
I'll have your head, Zangunaz, but first here is a list of demands.
What fell things the umgi created with you, Vampire – I demand you listen or we will crack open every one of your tombs.
I detest the Undead as much as the grobi, but still I must make this offer.
We have requests, Vampire. You would be wise to heed them.
You think yourselves long-lived and even knowledgeable, but you know nothing of the mountain realms. Perhaps you would like to learn?
We have a request, Uzkular, will you consider it?
We have a contract ready to sign and be done.
Ready to fight with the Dawi, lad?
A treaty to enshrine our alliance and consider it a great honour, no doubt!
Come mangling, bring your nags and I'll bring good, honest, Dwarfen axes.
Let us sign a treaty, Bretonnian.
There's nothing good that will come of this, but a Dwarf's word is his bond.
Creatures of Dum – you are used to signing pacts, yes? So sign this one.
Hail, Dawi. Now is the time to unite and begin the Age of Reckoning!
Sign the treaty and pledge to the High King, Clans-kin!
A new alliance is needed, manling.
Will the Empire sign a treaty and bring about an age long-thought past?
I spit on you, Greenskin, but a treaty must be signed.
It may not be important to you, grobi, but I'll see that parchment signed and a treaty ratified!
Sign the treaty, Uzkular, so you can get from my sight!
We'll have a treaty but if I see one Dwarf corpse rise up, the accord will end and you shall taste vengeance!
Come and share in the riches of the Karaz Ankor, friend.
A gift for you from the Clans.
Best accept the gift of my people, friend, or offence might be caused.
We come to your aid, for the Dwarfs are an honourable folk.
The Dawi join this fight, for the enemy has wronged us also!
Grudges will be settled – we come to battle!
Peace is difficult to come by, but now is the time for trade-talk, and beer, to flow.
A respite from war is a healthy thing.
Good! Battle is no fun if there is little time to drink and tell stories in-between the slaying!
Peace be with you, umgi. The Grey Mountains will be safe again.
We will trade and be at peace, manling.
Can there be peace with the followers of Dum? If they hold to their vows…
No Daemon-spawn or their warped followers shall enter our realm! Agree and we will have respite.
The High King desires peace between the Holds. We should abide.
Peace – there is no glory in our kin fighting, not with so many urks to fight!
We wish to have peace with the manlings of Empire.
Now we shall have peace, umgi. Let's have a few tankards of "One-finger's Tar Drop" until you fall over drunk due to your weak constitutions.
Peace with Orcs! I doubt it, but we offer it anyway, despite our ancestors' scorn!
We offer peace, not that we expect Greenskin scum to keep it!
Be gone, Vampires – back to your fetid realm and leave the Dawi be!
We offer peace, now back to the graves with you!
Ha! The Dammaz Kron is full of your sins, we shall never ally!
No alliance – not in this Age of Reckoning!
