You'll find no friends here – only hatred!
Peace, ha! Not while The Great Book of Grudges remains full!
Our beards bristle at peace, urks – the thirst for war is too strong.
We reject this notion! There is no peace while Grimnir sharpens his az!
There are scores to settle and grudges to be righted with you, Bretonnian.
You have lessons to learn, manling. Lessons that cannot be taught through peace.
There cannot be peace with your Gods – we must fight until there is no breath in our bodies.
Grungni give me strength! Do you mock us, Chaos scum? Of course we cannot have peace with your kind!
The grudge is in the Great Book, there will never be peace until it is settled.
No, the war must continue until the penance is paid in full!
You have wronged us, umgi, now you must pay the price.
Foolish manling – you think peace is that easy?
Do not violate your gods' tenets, or ours, by offering peace, Greenskin!
There will not – cannot – be peace with the urki and the grobi scum!
You are an enemy of Valaya, Zangunaz – peace is impossible.
Get back to your tombs, Vampire, and stay there. Then we will have peace but not until!
Yes, Kazak!
We declare war!
It is war! Khazukan Kazakit-ha!
War on Bretonnia – the manlings must be punished!
Kazak! That is war in Khazalid, boy. Best strap on your armour and prepare to die!
We go to war with the Chaos Gods, we will make Grimnir proud!
It is war with Chaos – Gotrek will surely join us!
Shame on your Clan! War is the only answer!
War it is, kins-Dwarf – you'd best be ready.
Axe versus sword, I like those odds, manling! To war!
War then! To think we fought beside you in eons past! Never trust umgi, their memories are as short as their lives.
Now the urki and grobi will pay! Kazak!
A great day indeed, let us battle with the urk scum until Grimnir himself joins us!
We'll have this Undead plague cleaned up soon enough – to war!
We declare war with the Zangunaz! You'll wished you had stayed dead soon enough!
Your umgak armour won't protect you from my axe!
I don't forgive and I definitely don't forget, Bretonnian!
You carry a heavy load, umgi, I can see that plainly.
I don't give my help to just anyone, Bretonnian…
Greetings, Knights of Bretonnia!
Bretonnians! What can I do you for?
Dumal! Deliver your message and get out of my sight!
Tell your masters the White Dwarf refuses to bow before them!
Come, Northman, spit it out, we haven't got all day!
I'll bandy words with you, Chaos scum, but I don't like it!
What do your dark masters want from me?
Alright, servant of Chaos. What brings you here?
I've got nothing for you, son of Sigmar, keep walking.
I'm in no mood for a rorkaz, umgi, let's get this over with!
Well, manling, what can the White Dwarf do for you?
Why do the men of the Empire seek me?
What word from the Empire?
Sons of Sigmar, you are a welcome sight.
I'm not much for words, but I'm pretty nifty with an axe!
Talk if you must, it won't change your fate!
I don't have time for words, the Dawi need me.
My axe yearns to be plunged into your skull!
Your death will be remembered in another of my glorious sagas!
I'm here, you're here, lets talk.
I'll listen to what you have to say.
Who seeks the counsel of Grombrindal?
What business have you with the White Dwarf?
The Ancestors bow to no-one!
Words bore me. Throw in some ale and you're talking!
Greetings! I am Grombrindal, but you knew that!
You are welcome. Tell me, what do you need?
There'll be plenty of time for talk. First, we drink!
Can I offer you a prophecy?
Choose your words, Greenskin, or you'll find me standing on your neck!
Why don't you take a little stroll off that there cliff and stop botherin' me?
Count yourself lucky you still have all your limbs!
Don't expect much from these 'talks', Greenskin.
Go on then, have a go at diplomacy, ha!
I'm surprised to see you here, Greenskin!
Unbaraki! How dare you come here?!
You are a disgrace! Gazul take you!
Come on then, lad, grab a tankard and let's talk.
Sit you down and tell me what it is you need.
Khazukan! Welcome!
Always happy to drink with a fellow Dawi!
Zangunaz! My axe longs to be embedded in your skull!
You know nothing of azazmar, you Undead fool!
You Undead lot make my skin crawl!
I can't promise you safe passage... My axe has a will of its own.
The Undead is it? Go on then, speak.
I'm not wasting good ale on you, let's make this quick.
I must have gold-sickness, as I agree!
We have an accord, but I curse your ancestors all the same.
Dongliz! I cannot abide the notion, but we have no choice.
Ip. That is "yes" in our tongue.
Keep to your side, or this will be recorded in the Great Book.
We will drink to this accord. Hail the brewmaster!
We have an agreement.
I have seen worse trades.
Sign this contract, and we'll have a pact.
The umgi are desperate if they send this excuse for an envoy.
I have no patience for this. Say what you will, servant of Leoncoeur, and be done with it!
Greetings, Bretonnian, shed yourself of that Umgak armour and we can talk.
Ahh, the Bretons come to parley, their realm must be in trouble.
Well met, Knights of Bretonnia.
Hail, Bretonnians, what can the Dawi do for you?
I do this, against the wishes of the Longbeards, I might add.
Agreed, but your treatment of the Grey Mountains will never be forgiven, umgi!
It is a fair treaty. I accept.
The terms are favourable, so we will work with the umgi on this cause.
Ai, we accept. Get your horses ready and your commonfolk armed.
We have always fought along side the umgi of both nations. Let us do so again.
These umgi are even worse and more treacherous than that Empire lot!
No, you are unbaraki, and I shall not treat with you, Knight!
I think not, umgi, pray to that woman in the water you are so keen on instead.
Unacceptable terms and a bad attitude in general. We will not work with you!
Nuf, we cannot hammer out terms.
No, this time you go it alone, umgi.
Nothing good can come of this, but I have little choice…
I debase myself in front of my ancestors by agreeing to this vile pact!
Bring me the Book of Grudges! I must write mine own name in it, for I accept the Chaos thing's terms.
Alas, I agree, but let it be known I do this for the Karaz Ankor, and not for any promises of power whispered by this… creature.
An alliance then, a temporary pact at best.
I agree, even if it means shaving off my beard in disgust afterwards.
Chaos-kin, you dare come here and challenge me in front of mine throng!
You are a pawn of vile powers, give me your message so I may reject it!
I see before me Northmen, you speak for your vile Gods no doubt…
I will hear you speak, pawn of Chaos, if only to deny your desire!
Chaos comes, should we welcome you with open arms, spawn?
Are you here to personally deliver news of the End Times? We got that message…
Northman, you are slime not worthy of any respect. I should kill you where you stand!
Bring my axe! I have a Chaos-puppet to slice into a thousand strands!
Get out of my sight, Chaos-kin, before I have the Drengi hunt you down!
The mere thought of working with them gives me the rutz.
A foolish hope, sworn over gorl as tainted as your masters.
Back to the north with you, fiend!
Very well, but this is Guild business.
Agreed – why then does this taste like sour beer?
This will enrich us all.
A fair deal and I'd expect nothing else from mine kin.
Of course, together we are stronger!
Send away the Reckoners, we are done! An agreement is in place.
Not for all the Oathgold under your mountain!
Wazzock! Get out of my sight!
I'm afraid Clan politics will put us at odds on this occasion.
Come back when your beard has grown a fair few feet, Clans-Dwarf.
My blood boils like magma at the thought of it, but ni!
Valaya weeps for I cannot help my kin this day.
What is your message, Clans-Dwarf?
I do not trust your Clan, so speak and be done.
Welcome, Dawi, do you bring a gift of Gromril to aid in negotiations?
Greetings kin of another Hold, what can I do for you?
Come, come, kin, let us feast and drink!
Dawi from another Hold arrive, tis a great day!
Times grow dark, and here come the umgi to lay their troubles at my feet!
I'm not in a good mood, manling, say your piece…
Greetings, umgi. How fares the Empire in these dark times?
Manlings come – they only do when they want something…
Welcome, men of the Empire.
Hail to your Emperor, manlings.
Ai, we'll help you out. You cannot trust the umgi to sort anything out themselves.
My Longbeards tell me not to trust you and with just cause. Nevertheless, I accept.
Our kin share history, let us hope we will share the joy of battle together.
We have a treaty then, manling!
Of course, how could we not aid our most-trusted of allies?
Dawi and menfolk will work together again.
You are too short-lived and untrustworthy, Empire man. Now go.
I have no stomach for allying with the umgi, they always let us down…
Nai, my warriors grow restless, I have no time for the Empire.
I cannot, but I wish your Empire well all the same.
Nai, not this time, umgi.
No doubt we will bring order, but not at this juncture.
I will take the Slayer Oath in recompense, but for now, the Orc speaks sense.
We must ally with the grobi, even if it marks us as unbaraki…
I find nothing to fault here… other than working with grobi scum!
It is a tacit agreement. Betray me, urks, and I will find every last one of you…
Ai, we have a pact. Do not betray us, urk.
I cannot tell if the ancestors laugh or are shamed, yet we accept, Orc.
Never! I will not rest until every last Goblin is a stain upon the ground!
Ni, Orc, you shall never have such satisfaction!
Do you take me for some beardling? Get out!
The whole notion reeks of Skrati thinking. I'll never work with the Greenskins.
We are enemies, urk, no matter what you may wish.
Back to your mobs, Greenskin, tell them no Dawi will treat with you!
You dare approach a Lord of the Dawi in such a manner?
Talk at me in your crude language if you must, I make no promises as to the outcome.
Come then, messenger, spit out your words so I can be done with them!
My throng stands ready, do not disappoint me.
Make your proposal, my Longbeards grumble, so make it quick!
You may speak before my shieldbearers and on the oath stone.
Honour to your ancestors!
And what can the Dawi do for you on this fine day?
Ai, let's hear what you have to say, we'll hear it before oathgold.
You have seconds to live, Orc, speak quickly before you die in agony!
Ugh! The Greenskins come. Their stench precedes them…
Come then, grobi, let us hear your message.
Orcs come seeking parley! Have the mountains tuned on their sides?
Ha, in all my days I never thought to see a grobi come begging for favours!
The Orcs bring forth an envoy! Grimnir's blessings on such wonders!
This was a fool's errand. Be gone!
Nai! You shame your ancestors, not mine.
Do you take me for some beardling high on fool's gold?
Nai, nai, and thrice nai…
I do not like the terms, go back to your masters and try again.
I serve the High King, not your masters.
Alas, our ideals differ greatly.
Unfortunately, that would not be in the best interests of the Karaz Ankor.
I refuse. My reasons are my own.
The days are dark, the end times come, and here is proof – Zangunaz come to treat with me.
As long as I am Lord, this thing will receive no hospitality from me!
It is a brave or stupid Necromancer that approaches me unarmed.
Very well, say what you must, Vampire, but I make no promises.
A strange day – I find disgusting envoys of Vampires approaching me.
What do you want, blood drinker?
A grave time for the Karaz Ankor, and yet I must say yes.
We have a deal, Uzkular, but don’t mistake this for leniency when it comes to battle.
The whole thing tastes like ash in my mouth but ai, it will be done.
Agreed, now get out. Your form sickens me!
I will do anything to bring glory to the Hold. If that means working with Uzkular, so be it.
Many would mither at such a pact, but it is for the best.
Nai, nuf – whatever language you wish it in, Vampire… NO!
Vile creature! I should strike you down with my axe where you stand!
I cannot in good conscience submit my throng to that.
No, I will not sully the sons and daughters of this Hold by allying with Zangunaz.
A ridiculous notion. Now be gone, Undead.
I think not!
The umgi are desperate if they send this excuse for an envoy.
I have no patience for this. Say what you will, servant of Leoncoeur, and be done with it!
Greetings, Bretonnian, shed yourself of that Umgak armour and we can talk.
Ahh, the Bretons come to parley, their realm must be in trouble.
Well met, Knights of Bretonnia.
Hail, Bretonnians, what can the Dawi do for you?
Chaos-kin, you dare come here and challenge me in front of mine throng!
You are a pawn of vile powers, give me your message so I may reject it!
I see before me Northmen, you speak for your vile Gods no doubt…
I will hear you speak, pawn of Chaos, if only to deny your desire!
Chaos comes, should we welcome you with open arms, spawn?
Are you here to personally deliver news of the End Times? We got that message…
What is your message, Clans-Dwarf?
I do not trust your Clan, so speak and be done.
Welcome, Dawi, do you bring a gift of Gromril to aid in negotiations?
Greetings kin of another Hold, what can I do for you?
Come, come, kin, let us feast and drink!
Dawi from another Hold arrive, tis a great day!
Times grow dark, and here come the umgi to lay their troubles at my feet!
I'm not in a good mood, manling, say your piece…
Greetings, umgi. How fares the Empire in these dark times?
Manlings come – they only do when they want something…
Welcome, men of the Empire.
Hail to your Emperor, manlings.
You dare approach a Lord of the Dawi in such a manner?
Talk at me in your crude language if you must, I make no promises as to the outcome.
Come then, messenger, spit out your words so I can be done with them!
My throng stands ready, do not disappoint me.
Make your proposal, my Longbeards grumble, so make it quick!
You may speak before my shieldbearers and on the oath stone.
Honour to your ancestors!
And what can the Dawi do for you on this fine day?
Ai, let's hear what you have to say, we'll hear it before oathgold.
You have seconds to live, Orc, speak quickly before you die in agony!
Ugh! The Greenskins come. Their stench precedes them…
Come then, grobi, let us hear your message.
Orcs come seeking parley! Have the mountains tuned on their sides?
Ha, in all my days I never thought to see a grobi come begging for favours!
The Orcs bring forth an envoy! Grimnir's blessings on such wonders!
The days are dark, the end times come, and here is proof – Zangunaz come to treat with me.
As long as I am Lord, this thing will receive no hospitality from me!
It is a brave or stupid Necromancer that approaches me unarmed.
Very well, say what you must, Vampire, but I make no promises.
A strange day – I find disgusting envoys of Vampires approaching me.
What do you want, blood drinker?
I hate the notion above every other and yet we agree to the accord.
Kruti! We will agree, for now.
I do so under duress, for your names are in the Great Book of Grudges!
I accept, have the Reckoners witness and record the price.
I do this only for the betterment of the Karaz Ankor.
Ai, it shall be, mark it in Aldrhun for all to see.
Agreed, my court as witness.
It shall be set in stone!
Anad, the deal is struck!
Speak, umgi, and pray to your ancestors it is something I want to hear.
You are listed in the Great Book of Grudges many times, umgi, why should I listen to you?
Ai, come then, Bretonnian, I'll hear what you have to say.
Go on then, speak your words, umgi...
Send your king my regards, Umgi. Now, what can the Karaz Ankor do for you?
Welcome, Knights of Bretonnia.
We agree, but the shame of your actions in the Grey Mountains makes you untrustworthy, manling.
Ai, it is an accord, but betray us and you'll all pay, Bretonnian.
I accept. Tell your ruler that the High King agrees.
Very well. It is in the interests of both kings to work together.
An agreement it is then – I realise you drink that Elven muck, wine, but today we toast with Dwarfish ale!
Ai, Bretonnian, it is an accord.
Get out! Another entry in the Dammaz Kron!
Foolish manlings! The Dawi will never reach accord with the likes of you!
Nuf! That's Khazalid for no, Bretonnian!
Not this time, umgi.
I have to say nai, on this occasion.
We may work together in the future, but not now, umgi.
It will be, but make no mistake, dumal-scum, I despise this as much as your fell Gods.
So be it, but do not cross me, Dum-kin. I swear on my oath stone you will regret it!
Just because our interests align this once do not mistake it as an alliance, spawn!
I do this for the greater good of the Karaz Ankor!
Ai, may Grimnir forgive me.
It is an accord, but my Reckoners will be watching, Chaos scum.
I will not sully the High King's mantle by speaking to Chaos things!
Chaos, how dare you entreat me! Filth! Spawn! Thagi-Kin!
Chaos! Even saying it burns my throat. Speak, scum, and be quick!
I will not parley with thralls of Dark Gods, so choose your words carefully.
I will listen, spawn, but don't expect me to act on anything your vile masters request.
Say what you must, puppet of Chaos…
Never, vile filth! To even suggest such a thing will bring your death!
Take this message back to your unbaraki masters. The Dawi will scour the mountains of you!
The next we see each other it will be in battle and Grimnir's axe will taste your blood!
By the Dragon Crown, the Dawi will never side with Chaos!
Ha! To think... to dare such a thing! Be gone!
No, as I breath, there will be no accord with Chaos filth.
Very well then Skruff-kin, but I don't like it.
An accord then, but your ledgers are marked!
An alliance of our Clans!
Ai, our Holds will unite.
By the Ancestor Gods, yes!
This is a grand day!
You are banished from my halls. Never show your beards again!!!
You shame your ancestors! Get out of my sight!
No, my kin, my orders stand. This will not be.
You have been appraised by my Reckoners and found wanting.
I cannot, the Great Reckoning begins.
It saddens my heart, but no.
Bow before your High King!!!
You dare! There is no greater authority!
Welcome, my bearded-kin.
Bow to the Throne of Power!
Welcome kin! How may the High King serve thee?
Fellow Dawi, it is an honour.
I have no time, for you foolish, manlings, spit out your demands!
The old alliance is dead, so don't come here asking favours!
Hail to your Emperor! What can I do for you?
Don't mumble, manling, I can't stand mumblers…
Now then, manling, what brings you here this day?
Greetings, Sigmar's chosen!
We have an accord, but don't cross me, manling!
I agree, but I'll be keeping a close eye. I don't trust umgi anymore – you are too fickle.
Very well, the Dawi and umgi will work together.
The runes favour it, so we shall ally again.
We shall strike an alliance, just as our ancestors did!
The old alliance remains alive!
I think not. Get out, and tell Franz I'll have him!
Ni, your Empire is no match for mine.
No, the Dammaz Kron is too full of manling grudges!
I'm afraid not, tell Franz it is a nai!
Alas, I cannot agree, you're on your own this time, umgi.
No, we walk different roads on this occasion, manling.
For this moment and this thrice-cursed moment only, we side with urk-scum.
I will take the Slayer Oath myself, but we must work with these vile creatures!
Although it causes me to gag to even say it, we agree with the Greenskins.
Then we work with the grobi, pray to the ancestors it is not for long!
Let the chroniclers record this – Dawi and urks working together!
Ai, I'll work with the Greenskins if it means the Reckoning will prevail.
Ni! I would rather hug an elgi than work with Orc-spawn.
Bring me my axe, so I may slay this wretched grobi filth for even suggesting such a thing!
I will not shame the Royal Clan by agreeing to anything with urks.
Get out of my presence, Orc, before my Hammerers smash you in twain.
Ha! Work with the grobi! You must think I'm a wattock!
Stop wasting my time, Greenskin.
Do not sully my presence any longer than you must!
I am the High King, I will hear you beg now!
Talk then, but I make no oath for the surety of your life…
What brings you to the halls of my ancestors?
Greetings… what do you require of the Karaz Ankor?
Ask your favour and I will check with the Dammaz Kron that you are worthy…
Welcome, friends of the Dawi.
All here are honoured Dwarf-kin!
Greetings, honourable ally.
Why is there grobi scum in my presence?
I thought I smelt urk stench!
Orc scum! Here? Speak, then, in your bestial tongue…
You bring urks before the High King?!
Urks, here!? I didn't even realise they could talk let alone reason…
You catch me in good humour, Greenskin, I'll hear your proposal.
Ha-Ha! Never! Now, be gone from my halls, my realm, my kingdom!
Nai, you have made a grave mistake coming here. One that shall be marked in the Dammaz Kron.
Get out of my halls!!!
It seems you have wronged us! We cannot do business.
We will not strike any deals with you this day or ever!
Walk away…
It is with regret, but nai!
Not this time, have your sires return in several generations.
I cannot accept on this occasion.
Get my axe! Why should I hear you speak, Zangunaz!
Vampire! …why do you darken my halls with your foul presence?
Now then, Blood Drinker, this had better be good…
I despise the Unliving, so state your case while I'm still inclined to listen.
Speak, Zangunaz, then I will decide if you keep your head.
I will hear you, Vampire, this once.
Cover the eyes of the ancestor statues… I agree.
Curse all Uzkular! For the good of the realm I accept.
Very well, Zangunaz. To the eternal shame of the Karaz Ankor, I agree.
I do this because I must…
It is an accord, be it one I find repellent.
A dark day for the Dawi, but we shall ally.
Never! Get ye gone, Undead thing!
The High King would never deign to parley with the likes of you, creature!
Get out Uzkular! Never darken my presence again!
I will not sully my ancestors by talking to the likes of you!
I will not parley with the Undead.
Blood drinkers and tomb robbers, be gone!
I am used to taking conflicting oaths, so I will accept your offer while despising you!
I do not break oaths so I accept, but don't mistake that for liking it.
My axe thirsts for your blood… but we have an agreement.
We have an oath of agreement, pray you don't break it.
My Drengi would rather fight you… but this time I'll accept.
I am the last Slayer King. There is an accord in place, do not betray it.
Let us drink to this. Break out the Bugman's!
Then it is done. We will celebrate by matching blades!
Ai, Grimnir smiles on us!
Very well, manling, I hope your nags are up to the job.
Very well, Bretonnian, but my Slayers will take convincing.
A tacit agreement it is. Keep your side, umgi.
Let us toast to an accord, but not with that donkey drek you consider drink.
Our Ancestors will sing about this for many generations!
Ai, men and Dwarfs will ally again with the Slayer throng!
So, Bretonnian, you come all this way. Your message better have more substance than the wine you drink!
Deliver the message from your king, manling, but your view of chivalry differs from mine.
The men of Bretonnia, what brings your noble behinds to Kadrin?
I see horse lords of the Bretons approach me. What could they want?
Bring forth the beer, the Bretonnians have arrived to save the day!
Come forth, men of fair Bretonnia, Kadrin welcomes you.
We don't need your help, Bretonnian. We are the Slayers of Karak Kadrin!
I think not, manling, tell Leoncoeur he is on his own.
No umgi, nai, take your armoured nags and do one!
If I was purely Drengi, then it would be yes, alas, I'm also king, so the answer is no.
No, manling, what you propose is no benefit to my Slayer-kin.
As king, I must make tough choices. This is one, Bretonnian, I decline.
I do not like it! Working with Chaos... Grimnir will shun me for this!
A dark day, but it must be done.
It is something I must consider, but it galls me!
This has to be…
The Slayers will work with Chaos scum but this is one day I wish to forget.
The Throng agrees, for Kadrin and the Karaz Ankor. May our sires forgive us!
I thought it stank of skruti – what do you want, pawn of Chaos?
Vile creature, do not dare to enter my halls – do not dare to even talk to me!
Say what you have to say, spawn-kin, but do not taint Khazalid, I'll hear you in the common tongue.
My axe yearns for your throat, dumal-umgi, so you'd better speak quickly.
Stay where you are, servant of Chaos. Take not one further step, I'll hear you there.
I will hear you out, but I warn you, my blood runs hot for your death!
I would rather lop off my dongliz than work with this scum!
By all the Slayers of Karak Kadrin, nai!
Get thee gone, Dumal Kruti!
Never will the Dawi ally with Chaos!
It is a fine and foolish thing you suggest, Spawn. One I gladly decline.
Ni – you take me for a fool instead of a king, Chaos filth?
Ani, we have an accord, but your clan is not one I take pleasure in working with.
Your clan has never been a friend of Kadrin, but I accept on this occasion.
Ai, for the Karaz Ankor!
We will join our throngs and the Urks will quail!
It is an honour!
Khazukan Kazakit-ha!
Speak then, clans-Dwarf, but don't expect my response to be to your liking.
Your beard is short, Dawi; it makes you untrustworthy in my eyes.
Hail to the Holds! How may I aid your clan this day?
The Slayers of Karak Kadrin, greet you, clans-Dwarf.
My kin, the throng of Kadrin welcomes you.
Our kin have come. Fetch the Brewmaster, we drink!
Nai, you are kin, but your actions have the ilk of an oath-splitter to me.
No, this cannot be. Now take your gold and leave my presence, clans-Dwarf.
Alas, our aims differ here.
Nai, serve your clan as you must, the way I will serve mine.
I decline your fair offer, kin, but not out of spite – never out of that.
The Holds will stand – that is a certainty, but this offer is not.
Very well.
An agreement – but not one that best serves my subjects.
An accord then.
As the King of Karak Kadrin let it be recorded in the Hold's records: I agree.
Very well, Empire-men.
A binding contract?! Send in the reckoners!
You come at a difficult time, umgi… speak quickly.
I have little patience so this better be of import.
What brings you to the halls of my Ancestors?
Come then, let's hear what Franz wants.
Greetings, manlings, are you ready to slaughter the enemy?
Will you join me, men of the Empire, in finding death in glorious battle?
I think not, manling. Be gone!
Do not approach a Slayer with such meek-minded foolery!
No, manling, this won't do.
Has the Empire lost its mind since I was last there?
Your words are foolish, manling, nai!
Not this time. Come back when your pitiful mannish beards have grown.
Come then, Grobi, the Slayers and Orcs will work together but when this is done, I kill every last one of you…
Urk scum! We have an accord, but a temporary alliance at best!
It is mutually agreeable, but this is a one-off, urk.
Grungni won't be happy; nevertheless, we have a deal with the Greenskins.
An alliance with the Greenskins?! Valaya will be laughing at me!
Very well, we will treat with the Grobi for now.
Grobi scum! Do you expect us to break stone bread and drink your watery grog?
Urk, I have slain so many of your kin, what do you have to say to me!
What have we here, the urks come before the king of the Slayers?
Speak, Orc, but I reserve the right sever your foul head from your neck if I think you lie.
Let the Orc speak, if it can. Usually I never let them live long enough to find out.
This is novel – urks here in my presence, and still breathing!
Nai, urk, nai, now the Axe of Dargo will have its say!
No, my Dawi will never agree to your terms as long as I live, and the halls of Karak Kadrin still stand!
The grobi are enemies, and we shall never ally with their ilk!
You dare approach the Ironfist with such a notion? Get out of my sight, grobi scum!
Haha, to even suggest it would have the longbeards draining their flagons.
No, grobi, but I am in a sporting mood... you have a few minutes to get away…
Urks! Talk fast, for you are my enemy…
You are not welcome, so I won't pretend otherwise. Now spit out your proposal!
My Slayer Oath would have me kill you where you stand, but I am also a king, so I'll hear you out…
Hail! Do not be intimidated by the throng of Drengi, they wish only to die in battle…
Greetings. Let us speak quickly, for I wish to fight.
Ai, I'll have yer words, before you take my ale.
Welcome to my throng!
I am Ironfist. Some call me a king, you are welcome here.
Greetings. You'll no doubt have a request – I'll hear it now.
Nai, urk. Now run!
You are a fool to approach a Slayer with such a notion!
I wear a cloak of Dragon-hide! Did you expect me to be accommodating?!
I think not!
Nai, I must find my death in battle, not waste my time signing treaties!
The throngs of Karak Kadrin disagree.
I have sought advice in the Slayer shrine. And so I must refuse.
Nai, not for all the treasures in Everpeak!
Pray to your gods that I die, so you may return and entreat my sire.
Only as it serves Karak Kadrin!
I don't like it… Betray me, Vampire, and your head will be skewered on my gate!
Make no mistake, I don't do this as a kindness, Vampire!
I trust this agreement as much as you enjoy the sun, beast!
Ai, I will work with the Uzkular. Keep your enemies close. 'Tis sage advice!
Very well, although it sticks in my craw to do so.
How dare you darken my hall, Uzkular!
I have no time for such filth. Your words better carry weight, fiend.
You defile my realm, creature, spit out your words and then the Axe of Dargo will speak!
I don't see any reason why I should address something that cannot breathe in fine mountain air.
I'm an oath-bound to slay you, Zangunaz, but let's hear your pathetic plea first.
The Undead come to parley! Your Necromancers must be incompetent!
Don't try and manipulate me, Uzkular. I am king of the Slayer Keep!
Ha! You think I would betray my Ancestors so easily? You will die again, beast!
To even suggest this! Prepare to face my wrath, Vampire!
Nai, the Drengi of Karak Kadrin will never work with your kind.
Ha! Do you think I would forsake my oath so easily?
Work with the Undead! I'll chew on their bones!
A most worthy offering.
You have our thanks, this will be placed in the vaults under Altdorf.
Even Volkmar would not refuse such a gift.
A wise decision, perhaps we can overcome our differences after all?
Sigmar be praised! You will not regret this.
At last, we have accordance.
The drums of war will beat soon enough.
How disappointing - the Runefangs will soon be unsheathed I fear.
I might have known signing anything with you was not worth the parchment.
If you do not want our aid then so be it!
Reject us? Sigmar damn you then!
Your refusal offends the Emperor.
We call to Ulric - the God of Battle, Wolves and Winter!
You will not find us cowering from a fight, we are Sigmar's sons!
War it is…
Alas we can no longer align our interests to yours. A word of warning - do not let pride lead to rage.
The treaty is ended! A regretful decision but one that had to be made.
The Arch-Lectors counsel against continuing this treaty. It is finished.
Muster your armies! Sigmar and all the gods demand blood!
War has come, time to answer Ulric's summons.
What are you waiting for? The End Times? To battle!
Payment is due on the debts owed to my people, scum!
Gold is owed. The choice of payment is yours, we take Imperial Crowns as a preference.
The Imperial treasury must be replenished. Alas, I must call in the debt.
Do not pretend to be deaf, Bretonnian, or we will cross the Grey Mountains and make you listen!
I'm not asking for an audience with the king, I demand one!
We have an offer that should benefit both great nations of men.
It is time for the Lady and Sigmar to work together.
Many times have Bretonnia and the Empire been allies. Hear our request.
We have an offer that the people of Bretonnia should hear.
Although it fills my heart with hatred, we have a proposal, Chaos filth!
Listen carefully, northern scum, so your master can hear our offer!
It is a dark day when we must parley with Chaos, but these days are the darkest yet.
I am sure we have been played by the Great Changer, but an offer must be made.
Come, minion of Chaos, why not accept our offer?
Do the Ruinous Powers hesitate? This offer scares them then?
We have an offer for the Dwarfs - surely pride will not be your downfall yet again?
Stop your incessant grumbling Dwarf and listen to what we have to say…
The Karaz Ankor could be great again, with the Empire's help…
A message - an offer for your High King - hear it or remain stuck in the past and hidden in your mountain burrows.
Dwarfen hospitality has always been welcome, and will you share a mug of Bugman's with us as we make our humble request?
Welcome honoured guests, our longest allies. We ask you listen to our proposal…
You bring shame on the Empire, let us end such hostility!
Sigmar weeps bitter tears! You will hear us out, or the Cult of Sigmar will come upon you in a burning crusade! Do you want an Empire in flames?
Come, let us rest our swords and hammers and speak for the good of the Empire.
I know you have not forsaken Sigmar, prove it to us by hearing our proposal.
The Empire should be united under Ghal Maraz. Hear us out, friend.
You do not doubt who is the true Emperor. That is progress, so I make this offer.
Are you capable of listening to our terms, Greenskin? I doubt it!
I demand you listen, Orc scum!
I despise talking to Orcs as much as I enjoy killing them, yet we have terms to broker.
Hear me, Orcs, listen to my offer, you may find it favourable for your tribes.
Perhaps man and Greenskin can work together after all? Our offer…
Will you put down that crude weapon and listen? Will you hear me out, Orc?
I speak for the Empire! You will listen!
I have the ear of the Grand Theogonist and if you don't accept my proposal I will send a hundred thousand flagellants upon your cursed lands!
By Ghal Maraz, you will take notice of what I have to say!
This is what I offer… Think carefully and be prudent.
We deem it wise to make this offer. You, in turn, will be wise to consider it.
By Ranald, I swear no trickery here, listen to my offer…
Be welcome, and hear what we have to say.
By the blessing of the Prince of Altdorf, I bring good tidings and an offer.
Let us talk, perhaps it will bear rich fruit for both nations.
We do not treat with the Undead! But for now we must…
Know that you will never take the mantle of Emperor, corpse-creature - still we have a proposal…
Morr will shun us for such heresy, but there are terms…
Keep your fangs behind your lips, vile thing! Here is our offer.
Perhaps one day we will recognise Sylvania as a rightful province. Until that doomed time, we may be able to strike a deal.
It is our sad duty to engage with such abominations… never-the-less, we have a proposal…
Perhaps a treaty?
The wisdom of Verena guides us to co-operation…
It is Festag! We should consider a treaty between us.
I offer a hand of peace and co-operation across the Grey Mountains.
Come, followers of the Lady - let lance and hammer work as one.
Sigmar damn us all, but a treaty with the Ruinous Powers is the only way!
I cannot believe I ask this… a treaty with the Northmen is sought.
As we fought together many times in the last two and half millennia, I ask again - will you join us?
The Empire and Dwarfs should march together as they once did?
As Magnus the Pious taught us, a united Empire is better than one riven by spite and jealously…
Come, men of the Empire, let us fight under one banner again.
Though it pains me to consider it, consider it I must - a pact?
Come, Greenskins, you seek war. Work with us and I promise you battle!
Although I know it will end in me being declared a heretic by Volkmar, I seek a treaty, Vampire…
If you can stop feeding on our citizens for a while we may be able to hammer out a treaty to suit both living and dead…
It is a simple gift, gold. Sigmar preferred such things also.
We offer a small token, blessed by the Arch-Lector and worthy of your status.
Here is a gift with Sigmar's blessing - use it as you will. Now, to business!
Your foes are also the enemies of Sigmar - we fight together, yes?
We offer our hammers, let us fight with you!
The Empire hears your call and comes ready to make war!
The sword becomes blunted from constant use, the hammer weighs heavy. Now is the time to consider peace.
A strong nation does not mean one constantly at war. Peace is achievable.
Peace in our age? We can but hope…
Put down your lances, there is no need for war.
Come Bretonnian, would you not rather drink wine than make war?
We wish to broker peace, Northman, are you even capable?
We are not at the End Times yet, Chaos scum. It is time to fight on a different front.
Come Dwarfs, let us be allies again.
Together we can help rebuild the Karaz Ankor.
Unite with us friends, make Magnus the Pious proud of our generation.
This is no Age of the Three Emperors, we must sue for peace.
Fight amongst yourselves, Orcs. Keep us out of this!
Do the Greenskins even understand… peace?
Von Carsteins - you have had your tally of corpses. The war must end.
We seek peace. Even the Undead must rest at some point.
These are Sigmar's people and nobody else's!
There will be no alliance while I draw breath!
I swear by Sigmar's comet and the wolves of Ulric that we will never join with you!
No, my men crave glory, and I plan on giving it to them.
There is no peace - there is only war!
Sigmar is a warrior's god; I cannot appease him with talk of peace.
The king has gone too far, we must teach him a lesson.
Bretonnia must be chastised for its actions - the war continues!
Peace with the followers of the Dark Gods? No, scum, never!
Get from my sight, Chaos filth, and know we will fight on!
We have been shackled by the Dwarfs for long enough, let them bear us a grudge!
The Dwarfs will know that their time is over!
A lesson must be taught, so the usurpers know who is the true Emperor.
No, these brigands will feel the wrath of Reikland.
The Greenskins have no notion of peace and so neither will we!
Get back to your mud huts, savage - the Empire comes to wipe you out!
Back, Vampire! We will not rest until the sun blazes upon your open tomb!
There can be no peace with the Undead - the priesthood of Morr has ordained it!
The Twin-tailed Comet burns in the sky, a sign to take up arms - it is war!
The Celestial College augurs war - muster the State Troops!
War comes to the Empire once again, make ready the men.
Bretonnia will not see sense - they must be taught the hard way.
We will set these Bretonnians right - with hammer and shield.
The Blood God demands blood, let us ensure it comes from His followers.
We fight the Northmen, the true enemies of Sigmar - it is war!
If the Dwarfs won't listen to reason then they must be persuaded with blade and hammer!
We go to war against the Dwarfs. Make them pay for this folly!
You leave me no choice but to declare war, and Sigmar damn your hides for making it so!
Magnus weeps, for we must make war within this once-great nation!
The Greenskins crave war, let us give it to them!
We go to war with the Greenskins, as fathers have always done!
We cannot - must not - let the Undead triumph - it is war!
We will make the Vampires pay for every Empire corpse that Morr has been deprived of - to war!
Have you seen what a master of the Gold Order can do to an armoured man? I can only surmise not.
So your serfs have spared you the gallows jig for now, lordling? Perhaps I will treat with them some day?
Let us joust with words for now.
Yours is a long ride home through the Grey Mountains, so let us get to business.
Hail to you, Lord of the Lance!
Honour to you, and to the Lady's Realm.
Have you heard of the Slaughter at the Six Spikes? That was one of mine. Speak!
That armour is fused to your body, no? Think how it would be if it were to grow searing hot…
I am the Supreme Patriarch, Northman, and your power does not overmatch mine.
Artefacts of power I bear. Pray to your Dark Gods that our truce holds.
Circumstance dictates that I listen to your words, Dark One.
Expediency makes for strange bedfellows, servant of Chaos.
A grudge is as an axe with two blades. Have a care lest you cut yourself, Dwarf.
Dwarfs grumble, rain falls, the sun rises and sets. There is nothing new in this world.
What would your High King have of me?
What errand brings the Dwarfs from their mountain holds?
Welcome, brothers in metal.
Hail, mountain lords! May your hoard increase.
Might and magic are mine to command! On your knees lest I unleash my wrath!
Your traitor-count's mewlings are as pitiful as those of a kitten!
The time of the Supreme Patriarch is not to be wasted lightly. Say your piece then!
As a fellow countryman, I trust you will not tax my time overly.
Greetings in Sigmar's name.
The Empire's unity is the surest shield against our enemies.
Interesting. The Bright Order are seeking targets for their initiates to practice on. And here you are...
A face such as yours would make for an interesting gilded statue. I have a spell for that, you know…
You stand before the Supreme Patriarch, like an ant before the descending boot.
I will set aside my studies for a moment to hear your words.
What brings you here to disturb my work?
Time is gold. Let us not waste either in idle chatter.
I trust our dealings will bear fruit, friend.
Friendship is more valuable than gold. Or so they tell me.
Welcome to my private study. Wine of palest gold will wet our palettes whilst we speak.
Yes, yes, "Raaar raaaar, smash, kill!" You have until the sand runs from this glass to bark your nonsense.
Tell me, Greenskin, once I have endured your rantings, what is to prevent me reducing you to a pile of smoking ash?
Your primitive posturing does not impress me, Greenskin. Save it for the Snotlings.
My brothers in the Celestial Order could make an interesting study of the gulf between our intellects.
Let me hear what you have to say, Greenskin.
I will do my best to interpret your grunts as best I can.
Give me a reason why Gehenna's Hounds should not pursue you back to your accursed master!
Many are the methods by which I could give you a true death, carrion-thing!
I will have an initiate open a window I think, to disperse the grave-stench in here.
Spill your rotten words, dead-thing.
Strange days these in which I must parley with the dead.
Welcome for now, grave lord.
Even though this is against the Grand Theogonist's will, I accept.
I agree to this pact, but betray me and suffer the wrath of the Empire!
Be warned - I spit blood at this agreement and expect you to break it!
I have the authority to sign such a treaty.
Sigmar was not just a warrior but a diplomat too. I take his example and agree.
We have an agreement.
If the Emperor bids, then it is so.
Very well - we have an agreement.
A solemn pact. Sigmar will decide if this is wise.
It is late in the day for Bretonnia to come running on their ponies demanding aid.
Here come the embodiment of mounted arrogance, the Bretonnian Knights!
Greetings, Lords, I hope the lakes of Bretonnia run clear this day.
So what can the Empire do, that the mighty flower of Bretonnia cannot?
Greeting neighbours, how fair the lands beyond the Grey Mountains?
Honourable Knights come to parley with the Empire on this fine Aubentag.
Yes, we will aid as we always do when you come crying for the mother's milk of the Empire.
Very well, we have an agreement. Do not betray us, "noble" Knights, you are not fooling anyone with your claims of chivalry.
We will work together. You'll have to get over your disdain for black powder!
I accept the terms - on the acknowledgement that our Knights are superior to yours, of course.
We will sign a treaty and toast our king and emperor!
Man allies with man - there is hope for the Old World yet!
No - at least with the Orcs, you know what you are getting. I despise Bretonnians because you are weasels in armour!
Get from thee, messenger, I have no patience for the bumpkins of that festering hole you call a country today.
I'm afraid you'll have to cope without "unchivalrous" allies like us.
Go then, return to your king with a tale of Empire "greed".
Unfortunately not, we cannot aid fair Bretonnia this time.
It is with regret we cannot aid you, the Empire looks to troubles elsewhere.
Agreed, but I pray to Ulric that his wolves will guard against Chaos betrayal!
My hand is forced, we have been coerced by agents of Chaos to accept! The Emperor will not forget this!
It chills me to my bones, but for the good of the Empire, yes.
We have an agreement - tell your masters that they must claim no souls in recompense!
We will work together for now, minion of Chaos.
There is a common cause, but do not underestimate brave hearts of Empire men, Chaos worm.
The bastards of Chaos are here to treat, I invoke the protection of Sigmar!
What comes slithering along the ground? A serpent in thrall to repulsive Gods!
Speak no lies, Chaos filth, for I will know them…
You have a message from your despicable masters, Northman?
The thought disgusts me, but I will hear you, agent of Chaos…
Speak then, Northman, let us hear your lies.
Never, Chaos scum, tell me why the Greatswords shouldn't slay you on the spot!
By Sigmar! As long as there is breath in my body I will never agree to such a thing!
I should take your tongue so you can speak no more lies, vile spawn!
You are nothing more than a servile thing in thrall to Chaos. I deny you.
You are our mortal enemy, the Empire could never work with you.
Do you think me corrupted by your foul masters? Why would I seek a pact with invaders?
You drive a hard bargain at the Empire's expense, Dwarf. I will not forget this!
Very well, although I see no Dwarfs helping the Empire's families. You're certainly eager to take our coin though!
We have an agreement - let us drink to another alliance!
The contracts are signed, the terms settled, so please no more grumbling!
Yes, just as in the times of old!
Of course we shall work with you, for it has ever been that way!
No! You have always looked down your beards at us, but whose Empire lies in ruins?
Dwarf! Insult us again, and you will see how accurate my handgunners truly are!
The terms are all in your favour! I will not agree, Dwarf, I do not fear your High King's wrath!
Come now, you do not negotiate with some callow youth. I cannot - will not - accept this, even from a Dwarf!
The Elector Counts will not permit this pact with the Dwarfs.
An agreement! Let us drink Dwarfish brew to celebrate!
And so come the Dwarfs – late as usual – to sour my day!
Make your demands then, Dwarfs, but don't expect the Empire to concede.
Well met, Dwarfs, what are your demands? I hope you will be more accommodating than usual.
Dwarfs, I hope we can strike some petty grievances from that book you hold so dear.
Welcome, ancient allies. In these troubled times Dwarfs are a fine sight to behold!
The Dwarfs have come, I hope they have brought a few barrels of Bugman's with them.
Although it gulls to work with your petty province, I will for now.
Very well, but I find you as trustworthy as a band of Marienburgers!
I endorse this - together our nation is stronger!
Yes, for the good of all the provinces we will do this.
We should feast to this grand accord! Is it Festag yet?
Of course, I accept. How could I not when it is my fellow countrymen who ask?
You dare come at me making demands? Call yourself men of the Empire?!
Why talk to you? The Grand Theogonist should declare you traitors and heretics!
Greetings my countrymen, do you come in peace on this fine Marktag?
Surely an agreement will be reached, for are we all not sons of Sigmar?
Welcome, my countrymen!
It is good to see fellow sons of the Empire this day!
No, traitors, you do not dictate terms to me!
No, and a pox on your province for even asking such a thing!
Not this day, I'm afraid, your demands are too much.
My heart is saddened when countrymen such as ourselves cannot make common cause.
Alas, I have my orders and you have yours. We could not make this work…
No, not with Morrslieb so low in the sky - dark omens…
May Sigmar forgive me for working with his greatest foe…
We must accept, Orc, but our swords will remain at your green throat!
An uneasy pact - but one that might work if the green scum can keep their word.
I look to the Goddess Verena for her wisdom in this pact with the Greenskin daemons.
It is not something I have heard of in many generations, but there is a precedent…
Prove to me then, Greenskin, that you can keep your word… I remain sceptical.
Greenskins… you are a curse upon the world, a blight on the land, and we will wipe you out!
I don't know who I hate more... the great green beasts or those little bastards who follow them about.
I don't think so, Greenskin. The Empire will never ally with beasts!
The concept would be laughable if the thought wasn't so disgusting. The answer is no!
Not this time, if ever. Tell your Warboss he is beyond dim, even for your kind.
You'd have me the jest of every noble court in the Empire. I don't think so.
Do not waste my time with petty talk, make your offer and be done!
Deliver your missive and then get from my presence.
My hand hovers close to my blade, utter your demand before I raise it!
I will listen, but my time is short…
Approach and make your offer, but I make no promises to my assent.
Greetings on behalf of the Empire, now what brings you with here with a sheathed blade?
By Sigmar's will, come in peace.
Approach as friend and make your offer.
Come then, only Sigmar's God, Ulric, can judge it worthy or no.
Orcs come before me with a proposal. I am duty bound to listen, but my arm aches to strike them down.
Speak then, Greenskin, but know that the Empire does not willingly treat with your vile kind.
Do not expect me to welcome you, Orc, if you can talk then say what you must.
I will be pragmatic, and treat with the Orcs, if it delays them from attacking.
The Orcs have come to talk? This should be amusing…
I am both intrigued and suspicious, what could the Greenskins want from us?
I will not accept this - not for all the gold in Marienburg!
Get away! Before I have a Battle Wizard burn you alive!
You are a painted fool if you think I'd betray my nation by agreeing to this vile plan!
No, thank the gods, I do not have the authority for such a thing.
You rush me to an answer and that has cost you dear!
There is no advantage for the Empire in this.
No, not this time.
Alas, I must refuse your offer.
Do not take offense at my refusal, Morrslieb hangs low in the sky so the omens are ill.
I will not parley with the dead! Be gone, abomination!
Von Carstein! A curse upon the Empire for centuries, what do you want, creature?
A minion of von Carstein dares to come before me…
I'll hear words from that Unliving throat, but I make no promises that I won't draw my sword.
Dark days indeed, when Vampires come to pay social calls.
You may deliver your message, abomination.
May Morr forgive me, but I agree.
You leave me no choice, Undead beast. I agree to the pact, but it makes me sick in the gut to say so.
Sigmar cannot look upon me with favour for this, but I must agree.
So be it, but I do not like this. Do not look me in the eye again, Vampire!
I won't deny that this is a strange treaty, but it must be done.
Very well, Undead monster, we will see if this works fair or foul for the Empire.
Never! Not even if Franz ordered me to himself!
Get out of my sight, creature! Tell your masters the Empire will never ally with such blasphemies!
If you utter one more sound I'll have the Light Wizard banish you from this realm!
No, you should never have left Morr's embrace!
I could not make peace with Morr if I were to ally with these creatures.
No - there is no pact with Vampires this day!
It is late in the day for Bretonnia to come running on their ponies demanding aid.
Here come the embodiment of mounted arrogance, the Bretonnian Knights!
Greetings, Lords, I hope the lakes of Bretonnia run clear this day.

Speak then, Northman, let us hear your lies.
And so come the Dwarfs – late as usual – to sour my day!
Make your demands then, Dwarfs, but don't expect the Empire to concede.
Well met, Dwarfs, what are your demands? I hope you will be more accommodating than usual.
Dwarfs, I hope we can strike some petty grievances from that book you hold so dear.
Welcome, ancient allies. In these troubled times Dwarfs are a fine sight to behold!
The Dwarfs have come, I hope they have brought a few barrels of Bugman's with them.

Why talk to you? The Grand Theogonist should declare you traitors and heretics!
Greetings my countrymen, do you come in peace on this fine Marktag?

Welcome, my countrymen!
It is good to see fellow sons of the Empire this day!

Deliver your missive and then get from my presence.

I will not parley with the dead! Be gone, abomination!

An abomination of Morr dares to come before me…
I'll hear words from that Unliving throat, but I make no promises that I won't draw my sword.
Dark days indeed, when Vampires come to pay social calls.
You may deliver your message, abomination.
As a means to an end, I must agree.
It pains me and this grand office to do so, but yes.
We have an accord, but I warn you - betraying the Empire will be a fatal mistake.
Very well. Get the papers written so I may set the Silver Seal upon them.
A pledge for our mutual benefit then.
This is the most sensible course.
We have a treaty!
I consider you an ally in these dark times.
A welcome alliance!
Your appearance is inopportune, Knight, but I will hear you out.
Come then, approach Sigmar's throne and bark your message from Leoncoeur.
Come before me, envoys of Bretonnia.
Your king sends brave men to approach me this Hexenstag!
Welcome, brothers from across the Grey Mountains.
Hail to Leoncoeur, how can the Empire aid you in such evil times?
You have forced me into this pact. But it's not to my liking!
We have common cause, but do not mistake this for friendship, boy!
We have an agreement, only together can we push back the forces of destruction.
Agreed, our Knights will march in step with your own.
An alliance of men - the Old World needs such treaties.
Our Bretonnian cousins will stand with us against the darkness!
I have no time and little love for Bretonnian beggars right now!
Your king is as impotent as a Bretonnian cannon! Now go!
Tell your dukes I must dismiss this out of hand.
You have not always been friends of the Empire, Bretonnian, and I regret to say this at such a time.
Return to your king and tell him that on this occasion we cannot agree.
Bretonnia and the Empire will take to the battlefield once more… but not this day.
Agreed… I can only hope that one day Sigmar will forgive me for this!
I make the ultimate sacrifice - the Empire must align with the Dark Gods.
Strike this meeting from the chronicles! I will not have the shame of this treaty mentioned in the scrolls!
Agreed, but I pray to Shallya that I will not regret such a pact.
It is a fell pact I make, but one that must be done.
You have my attention, but don't mistake this temporary alliance as complicity in your masters' designs.
Chaos! The fact you are even stood before me is an affront to my country!
I have done dark deeds in my time as the Emperor, but never would I willingly entertain an agent of the Ruinous Powers!
Do not test my patience, Northman. Say what you must then get out.
Chaos! The fact you are even stood before me is an affront to my country!
The days must be fraught, when peons of Chaos deign to parley with me!
I will not welcome you, raider, but make your offer.
Never! Not in my reign or the next, be gone maggot of Chaos, putrid scum of impotent Gods!
Get this Chaos filth out of my sight - tell your Gods the Empire will never submit to their despicable rule.
Whether it's in Reikspiel or your own foul language, Sorcerer, the answer is no.
Be gone, spawn, tell your masters I am not their puppet!
I would rather Todbringer take the mantle of Emperor than have a pact with you!
One of my titles is Defiler of the Dark. How could I claim such if I allied with Chaos filth!
We will join again, but remember you need the Empire more than we need Grudgebearer.
Agreed, although I find your tone grating, Dwarf-friend.
We have an accord to make our ancestors proud.
Agreed, but do not mistake this for obedience, Dwarf.
As Sigmar did, so we ally with the Dwarfs.
Of course, the Empire has ever been in your debt.
No! I will not be lectured to by Dwarfs when your kingdom diminishes before my eyes!
Not this time, the old alliance has long since passed.
No, the Empire cannot help you this time, you are on your own, Dwarfs.
Unfortunately I must refuse, Grimnir's kin.
Forgers of Ghal Maraz - it is with great regret that I cannot agree to this endeavour.
Sadly, not this day, honourable Dwarfs.
Approach me Dwarf, but do not expect alliances to be reignited on history alone.
You come for favours but all I hear is scorn – always the Dwarfs come to scold us!
How fares the Karaz Ankor in these dark times?
You approach us in difficult days, Dwarf.
Welcome, oldest friends of the Empire!
It is good to see our allies of the mountains.
Bow before your Emperor!
You come before me as arrogant fools, refusing union weakens us all!
I hold Ghal Maraz, you may bow.
Greetings countrymen, I welcome your offer.
Greetings, fellow heirs of Sigmar!
I am Karl Franz, many call me Emperor…
Very well, but I will reunite these lands despite you.
An accord it is, but Sigmar weeps until we are as one!
Agreed, but soon you must return fully to Imperial rule.
Yes, you have your Emperor's accent.
Of course, together we are stronger!
My seal will be upon the treaty.
I will not condone such a travesty.
A notion from petty fools who refuse my legitimate rule!
No, now return to the bosom of Imperial decree.
There will be no agreement from me, secessionists!
I'm afraid not, I must consider the whole nation.
I have consulted with the Arch-Lectors - the answer is no, but go in peace.
This a measure of the age we live in, when I am forced to ally with accursed Orcs!
Do not test my resolve, Orc. If we agree this pact, I can be magnanimous in victory but also your worst nightmare!
Against my advisors wishes we have an accord then, Orc.
Sigmar preserve my crown! For I cavort with Orcs!
A strange circumstance that we must work with Greenskins.
Sigmar preserve me! But I am forced to agree with the beasts.
Summon Schwarzhelm! I would have this Greenskin slain where it stands for such insolence!
You are ancient enemies of Sigmar, of the Empire! We could never have a pact!
I reject your offer Greenskin. As would any in my office!
No - to work with the Greenskins is to ally with our oldest foe!
Get out, Orc! Even Emperor Ludwig the Fat never considered allying with Greenskins.
To even ask such a thing is to mock my sovereignty!
You are not welcome in my court, and yet here you are. Friend or foe? We will see…
Speak, I will hear you now! Be warned, my mood is dark.
I will hear your petition, but make no promises to act on it.
Greetings, all you survey are loyal to me, so I advise caution with your next words.
I will hear what you have to say.
The Celestial College implores that I hear you, I remain unconvinced…
Friends of the Empire, come!
Greetings from Sigmar…
Be at peace, for that is all I ever want.
Orc scum! You dare to presume by coming before me!
Orcs come before me! Be careful what you say, beast, or my Reiksmarshal will have your tongue!
Orc, you have me attention, issue your demands, but be quick!
What could possible warrant the Greenskins to prostrate themselves before me?
Fine! I will talk to the beasts, its makes a refreshing change to slaying them!
Come then, Orc, I'll hear your offer. Can you even speak Reikspiel?
No, do not darken this throne again.
I should strike you down with Heldenhammer's wrath!
Leave now! Before I have the Reiksguard send your head into the river!
No, we will stand on our own!
I will not bind my nation to these terms!
I refuse. Do not question this, I am Emperor!
I regret that we cannot agree terms.
Let us try again, some day, perhaps when the Twin-tailed Comet appears in the sky?
I'm sorry, my advisors are against this.
You dare approach me, vile beasts?
Von Carstein sends his minions to threaten and parley?!
You are no Lord of the Empire, Vampire to even dress as such is a grave insult!
Let the thing deliver its vile message.
Vampire… speak before I summon the Witch Hunters.
What have you to say, monster?
Morr forgive me… but yes.
Agreed, but never forget, sorcerer, that I can unmake you!
Understand - I do this only because I must, von Carstein.
Agreed, I can only pray that Sigmar will forgive me for such a dread pact.
Very well - the living and dead shall work as one.
The Grand Theogonist will curse me, but we have an agreement.
Not for all black powder in Nuln! By the grace of Sigmar, be gone, Undead filth!
No, Vampire, no, I will send you back to Morr's realm for even suggesting such a thing!
You desecrate Morr's realm and expect me to endorse an alliance?
A treaty with the Undead? Not as long as I rule!
I think not, Vampire!
You are no Lord or noble of the provinces, yet you come to me as an equal!
Your misplaced faith will be the ruin of your people.
What do you want from me, Bretonnian?
Speak, Bretonnian, I would know of what you seek?
Your heraldry cannot hide your empty soul from one such as me.
Men of Bretonnia, what matters do you wish to put before me?
In these dark times, we men must stand together!
Your twisted Gods have no power here!
It is my sworn duty to destroy Chaos in all its forms!
Your twisted Gods have moulded you in their image, and sent you to carry their words.
From the depths of despair you come forth, puppet of Chaos!
Your dark masters have sent you forth... What do they seek?
Creature of Chaos! Your mind and soul are nought but empty vessels! What brings you here?
Your Ancestor gods are powerless before the might of Sigmar!
Your greed will be your undoing, Dwarf.
We must work together to keep the forces of Chaos at bay!
Long have our races stood together against the forces of evil.
Most ancient of allies, you are always welcome!
Forgers of Ghal Maraz! How can the Empire be of assistance?
You will taste the righteous retribution of the Sons of Sigmar!
If I had my way you would be dealt flame and hammer!
I am Volkmar, the Empire's great defender!
The Empire's foes do not escape the Grand Theogonist's wrath!
I will scour the enemies of Sigmar from these lands… from all lands!
You stand before the Grand Theogonist of the Cult of Sigmar. Speak and I shall consider your words.
Choose your words carefully. I am not a patient man.
Mighty Sigmar has granted me the power to see untruths in the words of others...
I will decide whether you are worthy to stand before the Sons of Sigmar!
Be warned – it is my sworn duty to rid the world of Chaos and all who facilitate them.
I bid you welcome, in the name of the Emperor.
The Empire is beset on all sides by the savage and the unholy, but you are most welcome.
I am Volkmar, Grand Theogonist of the Cult of Sigmar. Welcome!
The Sigmarite faith are willing hosts to its friends and allies.
Praise be to Sigmar! What brings you to the Empire?
My rage is terrible to behold, Greenskin! Speak quickly!
I would lay down my life if it would rid the world of you and your kind!
Those that have no faith can still die by it!
I am a busy man, Greenskin, what brings you here?
Death and destruction follow in your wake, Greenskin! What do you want?
The Sons of Sigmar have suffered much at the hands of your race. Speak carefully.
You will suffer for your sins, traitor!
You are touched by Chaos! I will cleanse your soul!
The words of the faithless hold little sway here.
Sigmar does not extend his protection to traitors... Tread carefully...
Brother! Have you come to atone for your sins?
Sigmar is mighty, but he is also forgiving to those who are willing to repent.
May the light of Sigmar burn out your red eyes!
I will not rest until I have cleansed the world of the curse of Undeath!
What do the von Carsteins seek? There is nothing for them here!
My faith shields me from your 'Dark kiss'! Say your piece and be gone.
What do you seek, child of darkness?
You are blighted by the curse of Undeath, yet I must hear your words.
Bah! I don't like dis. But, we'll agree.
I hatez dis, but yoo forced ma hand.
Yez, but yoo're gonna regret it!
Fine, no stabby - we'll, do it your way.
I'll agree dis time...
Da Spider-god finks I should accept.
Da Great Green speaks ta me - yez!
Good - we'll be rich, lotz of shiny stuff!
Da bad moon iz grinnin' in my 'ead. Dat's a yez!
Oh look, da flouncy humies want to talk, where yer lances now!?
I hate yoo humies, so start talkin' before I get Mork to splat yer.
Here come da humies, looking all posh like yer too good for us…
So, da humies deign to see us…
Not deses humies, dey all squiffy with dere stoopid 'onour!
Welcome to my lair, Bretonni'un! Tell me why I shouldn't zap ya right where yoo stand…
For da tribe, I sez yez.
We accept - but if ya betray us before we stabs yoo in da back I'll get angry!
Talked to ta Mork, he said we should agree.
Alright, humies, we'll do it, just dis once.
If yoo do dat, dis might work.
Ha! As if we'd agree anyfing wiv yoo weirdo humies.
Da Spider-god would eet us whole if we worked wiv yoo!
Get out before I get my nasty glare on!
Da Great Green sez no.
Go back to yer king and tell 'im to zog it!
Ha! As if we'd agree anyfing wiv yoo weirdo humies.
No. No workin' with yoo nag-lovin' gitz.
Yez, but keep dose spawn fings away from da ladz.
Don't fink for one moment dat I like dis. Chaos, ugh!
Dis suits us, so we'll chum up wiv Chaos.
Not sure about dis, but yez da tribe agrees.
Yez, whatever da Dark Godz want.
Yeah, yeah - just keep ya freaky-gitz back from da ladz.
Da dark godz ain't welcome 'ere!
Bloody Chaos-gitz! Wot do ya want?!
Da Chaos-men, dat's all I need!

So be it. I will flay your flesh with the utmost tenderness.
You bring me no pleasure.
Slaanesh tires of this plaything.
You entrance us no longer.
Come, join this orgy of destruction!
Revel in the coming excess!
There can be no rapture without you by my side.
The Dark Prince will never accept no for an answer.
Repay your debt. Submit to Slaanesh!
Worldly belongings spark no joy. Liberate yourself!
Part with your land, or part with your agonised soul.
Slaanesh desires a new playground. You will oblige.
The kingdom of pleasure must expand! Indulge this or suffer beyond your wildest dreams.
Even Dragons may not resist Lord Slaanesh!
Obey, or even your foolish wall will not save your soul.
Mortals! Heed the song of Slaanesh!
Do not avert your gaze, Dragon-child.
Let the Dragon know rapture, for Slaanesh is here!
Let my lips dance across your mortal ear.
On your knees, Daemon!
Accept the word of Slaanesh or suffer for an eternity, pretender!
The true prince of Chaos calls upon you!
Open your dark heart to excess!
Such a strapping specimen. Will you submit to Slaanesh's call?
There is so much I yearn to do with one so mighty. Let us start with this.
Witless thug! Accede to true Chaos!
Hear me, or experience suffering beyond even Kharneth's imagining.
Hear the call of excess, blood Daemon!
I would speak with Khorne's savage consort.
Welcome, kindred servant of suffering.
What say you, my delectably destructive friend?
Heed the word of Slaanesh, or your frigid soul is forfeit!
Obey, human! Obey Slaanesh! To refuse is death!
The Bear-slaves will hear the hymn of the Dark Prince!
Slaanesh's song will thaw even your frozen heart.
Your glowering resolve is so delicious. Now, what you say you to this?
I believe this will stoke rapturous fire in your cold soul.
Succumb to me, or suffer beyond all imagining!
Your soul belongs to Slaanesh. Accept this or perish!
Refuse this temptation and I shall devour your very soul!
I pray you will ignore this, for such suffering shall result!
Heed the euphoric words of Slaanesh, or your flesh shall be sundered!
Succumb to the will of Slaanesh!
I bring you temptation...
I am the vision you cannot refuse.
Accede and rapture shall be yours.
Submit to Slaanesh's desire!
Foul waste of flesh! Heed this or face obliteration!
Accept the word of Slaanesh, or your rotted flesh is forfeit!
Tune your festering senses to the song of Slaanesh!
Accede to a darker power, rotted one!
May Slaanesh whisper sweetly into your decaying ear?
What says the Urfather to the Perfect Prince's tantalising overture?
Accept the Prince's will, brute, or your soul shall be consumed!
Focus your loutish mind upon Slaanesh's song, or you shall suffer!
What thinks the Maw-consort of this?
Wipe the drool from your slack jaw and focus upon this.
This will make your greasy flesh shudder in delight, no?
Perhaps this can slake your improbable appetite?
To see you brings me more pleasure than you can know. What say you to this?
Does this not make you shiver in rapture?
You are as ravishing as ever, my dear. That is why I must say this to you.
Tempting, is it not?
My yearning for your response is almost unbearable.
Heed this well, or you will suffer for your betrayal of our Prince!
False consort! Obey or a true concubine of Slaanesh shall destroy you!
I bring rapturous proclamations from our dark master.
Lie back and think of our Perfect Prince, for this is His word.
I bring you excess! I bring you bliss!
I carry a decree from the Perfect Lord. May it bring you undying pleasure!
Obey, changeling! Deception invites only destruction!
No more schemes! No more trickery! Submit or suffer!
Slaanesh makes a delectable new move in our Great Game.
Will Tzeentch hear the forbidden voice of divine Slaanesh?
Entwine your mind with mine, changer, and know my thoughts.
This will aid our mutual pursuit of the forbidden, no?
Remain here a moment longer and I shall drink deep of your soul-stuff.
Suppress your desire to gaze upon me and leave, or else face annihilation!
Begone from Slaanesh's domain before I slowly slice the living flesh from you!
I did not consent for you to join me in my boudoir.
Transgression has its place, but now I desire you gone.
Please leave, for here there are sensations which would break your mind in two.
Let us become entwined!
Mutual pleasure shall be ours!
Ravish me and I shall ravish you.
I thirst for union with you!
Caress my flesh and I shall caress yours, dear one.
Will the Dragon accept this offer of congress?
Let our ancient enmity give way to mutual bliss!
Join with me, for the glory of Chaos!
A pact between dark souls!
Together, we can bring about an orgy of suffering!
Just think of the screaming should we aid each other's deadly cause...
Will you join Slaanesh for this dance, brave mortal?
There is so much we could do for one another, bear-child.
Come, plague-child. Such destruction this union shall bring!
Tell your Grandfather that the Dark Prince craves union with him.
Let us sate our mutual appetites!
Your strength, my cruelty – what a combination it would be.
Our Dark Prince demands our congress.
We must become entwined: it is Slaanesh's divine will.
Forbidden knowledge, in union with forbidden pleasure!
Let us make the next move in the Great Game together.
May it bring you bliss.
I implore you to spend this on only the most excessive pursuits.
Lord Slaanesh admires you, body and soul.
Might I join this dance?
Accept my aid and your foes will know indescribable torment.
How I crave the sensation of blade parting flesh! Let me join you!
Shall we kiss and make up?
Now that their suffering is done, let there be love!
My lust to bring pain is sated, for a time.
My thirst is quenched, for I have drunk so many of your souls.
Might we take this to the bedchamber instead?
You Dragons have surely suffered enough.
I thank the Dragon for the exquisite pain he has brought me.
This war of Daemons has been thrilling, but enough is enough.
Let us shake talons and put this misunderstanding behind us.

Come, my blood-soaked rival, embrace me!

Come now, child of rot! Let us make love, not war.

Such excess we wrought! The Dark Prince is now satiated.
The pain has been glorious. Let it now give way to pleasure, my kin.
Changeling screams are music to my ears, but I have heard enough.
Has the Raven foretold this truce?
Take this trifle, and leave us to our sins.

Take it, take it, take it! Oh yes!
I yearn to hear you beg!
You will do anything for my love, I know it.
Submit to me! Wail, beg, and beseech for my favour!

Only I make the rules of our courtship.
I will not dilute my pleasures by granting control to another.

Not while so many violent delights still await us.

Not until I have heard your Dragon-Emperor's screams.

Slaanesh grows tired of our dance. Agony must follow.

Rejoice, for I have resolved to grant boundless suffering to all Cathay!
Let our hell-sent flesh entwine on the battlefield, little prince!

Time to die, little blood-drinker.
Dance with me, skull-taker. Dance until one of us can bear no more!

Rejoice, for in death you shall hunger no more!
I have resolved to tenderly strip every inch of your bloated flesh.

Rejoice, sister! A festival of suffering awaits us both!

A most worthy gift.
We thank you for the offering.
May the gods of the Old World bless you for such a gift.
This is wise.
You may be worthy of our nation's respect.
We have an accord.
The drums of war will beat soon.
The treaty is void!
Just because we are not the largest of countries do not believe we are the meekest.
You think us your puppets, ready to dance on our strings? Never!
This offends us all.

Do not underestimate us, fools!
This treaty is void!

Our agreement has run its course.
Please, call your warriors!

Compensation is sought.

Listen to us!
We have an offer that should benefit both great nations of men.

Please, I beg, hear our offer.

Hear me, Orcs, you may find it favourable for your tribes.

Will you hear me out, Orc?
We demand an audience!
You owe us an audience!
Do not put us off, we have demands!
We have an offer.

By Ranald, I swear no trickery here, listen to my offer…

We bring good tidings and an offer.
Let us talk, perhaps it will bear rich fruit for both states.

Will the chivalrous Bretonnians consider peace?

It is nothing, a small bauble to mark our friendship.
Please accept our gift, and blessing of Shallya.
We fight together, yes?
For all our sakes, let us fight with you!

War with Bretonnia!

By all the gods of the Old World, no, never!

As was foretold.

Take your place alongside the champions of fate.
You cannot refuse destiny's call.
Ally with Tzeentch! Play your part in the Great Game!

The Raven will have His due.

When Tzeentch speaks, all Daemons listen.

Obey, or never know slaughter again.
From beyond time and space, Tzeentch addresses Kharneth.
Will the Skull Throne hear the Raven's cry?

Let slaughter and deception find an accord this day!

Heed the Raven, or paltry Kislev will be stricken from existence!

Comply, or your mind will be taken from you!
Heed Lord Tzeentch, lest your inevitable death be hastened.
Dare ignore us and you will know only madness for the rest of your days.
Hearken to the Architect, or Eldritch flame shall consume you!

Accede to Tzeentch, for he knows all that you are and all you shall be.
Accede now to the Architect of Fates!
Hear the voice of change!
Tzeentch speaks. You are fated to listen.

Will the children of rot open their minds to Tzeentch's brilliance?
Deception would speak with decay.

Hear the true voice of Tzeentch, or know obliteration!

Leave now, or be consumed by alchemical fire.
Begone, else we shall unravel your tiny mind.

Tzeentch can grant you power beyond your wildest dreams.

Skulls and schemes!
Embrace change, and Kislev shall become man's greatest empire!

Let decay stand with change!
Aid Tzeentch, and feast as you have never before feasted!

Let us explore the forbidden together!
Whispers in the dark, promises upon promises…
Let us unite, and bestow ceaseless change upon this world!
We are fated to align. Our all-seeing master has foreseen it.

The Architect of Fate wishes to see you ascend.
Your triumph is part of Tzeentch's grand design.
Tzeentch would see your enemy obliterated.

We can transform this land from ours to yours.
