A gift… to seal an Unholy pact perhaps?
An amusing present, but such fripperies bore me.
I am glad you accept, mayhap there are more pacts we could bind you with?
An offer you won't regret!
Good… good, now let us discuss other requirements…
Think carefully before making an enemy of me!
You break a pact with us, you forfeit your soul!
You think this contract doesn't bind you to me? Then you are a fool!
Reject us and reject your petty lives.
You decline? Not unexpected, but supremely foolish nonetheless.
This will be your undoing!
War with us, you think that wise?
It makes little difference to us.
We will make such charnel pits that your dead will choke the lands and then rise on my command!
Contracts with the dead are always invalid…
There is no treaty.
No earthly binds can hold the Undead!
Come and join us, we will slay the foe together!
We march to war. Join us!
War is an inevitable as death, we shall create it together.
Do not think death releases you from your debt.
Settlement is due.
Let us discuss adequate compensation.
Death protects, Bretonnian filth - if you don't accede to our demands we will bless you with it.
Your lake-witch hides in the Silver Pinnacle. She won't shroud you from us, so accept our offer.
This is the Age of Shadow and your lights will dim, so best listen to our demands.
The nights draw in, Bretonnian, are you ready? We could help…
How do our kin in Mousillon fair? We have an offer that could ensure they stay within the city walls.
We have a request for the king. Surely he will hear a fellow noble?
We don't need your pathetic Gods, just as we don't need Nagash. Thy power lies with us, so hear our demands.
You think yourself the true threat to this world? All you do is reap death, and that is our realm. We hold the keys to this plane and we have demands.
Here is our offer, puppet. Take that to your masters, let them know true power awaits their answer.
You'll hear us, Chaos, for our bat swarms will not cease screaming our demands until you have answered.
Together we can rule the mortals, accept our offer and let the terror commence!
Yes, sign the pact and let us bring damnation to the living.
Come, beardling, you think to refuse? We will crush the remnants of your race and make it as dust if you do not heed us.
Dwarf-scum, you are in position to refuse our demands. All your petty grudges are nothing compared to the true power of Necromancy.
Let us into your Holds, take the offer and a new era of Dwarf and Vampire shall begin!
Come Dwarfs, you may be long-lived but do you not crave immortality? Think how that would aid your Karaz Ankor?
We can work together, Dwarf. Forget the past, your grudges are immaterial. What matters is the future of your empire.
Take the offer, Dwarf, seal the pact and enjoy the riches such a deal brings us.
Your true Emperor speaks! Obey me and your miserable lives will endure. Meet our demands or suffer the consequences.
Sigmar was a fraud, a mere barbarian who could not better Nagash. Bow to your true masters, cattle - these are our demands!
Tell the Prince of Altdorf that the true sovereign awaits his answer.
This Emperor, he speaks as if all voted for his ascension, yet  the true Counts of Stirland did not. But we can soften our stance should he consider this offer...
We may have had differences in the past, but every Emperor has quarrelled with his Elector Counts, yes? May this offer help?
We have a request, a small trifling matter in the grand scheme of things.
This is our demand, Orc-spawn, I advise you to take it and keep your filthy blood in your vile bodies.
Do not test me, Orc. To reveal my full majesty will seal the doom of your entire tribe. Now hear our demands and pray for my mercy.
You low-born savages may rule the Badlands, but I have a way for you to move into more ripe nations… make the pact.
Now Greenskins, unleash your true potential and accept the pact before you.
Orcs are unlikely allies, but if you are content to murder and maim, then we are happy to claim the corpses in your wake.
A great boss such as yourself will consider this arrangement, as the offer is a good one.
Fool! Our bloodlines ascend the centuries. Hear our demands!
You will take our offer, for your bodies will wither and your souls be tortured for eternity if not.
Cower, for the darkness comes and we will have what is ours!
We have demands, for the night is eternal and we seek succour.
We have an offer, do not make the mistakes of your predecessors and shun the Unliving.
We both want something, breather, let us not sully ourselves in meaningless threats to get to it!
Oh, to be so young, virile and warm again! An offer then?
We come bearing gifts of life ever-lasting; it is the greatest gift - the Blood Kiss. Surely, it is worth adequate compensation?
We have an offer, not one usually given to those whose hearts still beat…
Get back, thrall, know thy place! I will leech your essence should you disobey my will. Now receive my demand and know thy place!
Your crippled bloodline is of no use to me, but there is a place in my legions should you bow to these demands.
As a servant of darkness, you should consider an offer from those that shroud the light.
The von Carsteins will march. Surely you wish to be part of such unholy majesty?
Well, my kin, let us unite and bring eternal darkness to the world. There's just the small matter of this contract to sign...
If the Vampire Counts unite then none of the mortal filth can stop us. Make the pact and let the Age of Shadow begin!
Perhaps a pact, or even a treaty if that sounds more agreeable?
Should we ally, you have my blood oath that your corpse shall be left in peace.
Let us co-operate - a treaty between those that live and those who have lived?
A treaty will ensure that your smallfolk will be the only corpses we use. Your nobles will be for Morr only.
Let the Lords of Mousillon charge with the flower of Bretonnia once more!
A pact with powers as determined as we are to snuff out life? It makes sense.
Bring forth your contract, Chaos filth. We will sign for there is no soul to lose.
Do we have an agreement, Dwarfs? It will earn you access to our tombs, where valuables and other trinkets could make this a most profitable venture.
Consider an alliance. Have we ever desecrated your dead like we do the humans? Have you ever seen a Vampire Dwarf?
Come, let us truly unite the Empire. Bring Sylvania to your bosom and we will repay such loyalty in kind…
We were all men once, perhaps a vestigial of sentiment still remains that will allow us to come to terms?
If you like carnage so much, Greenskin, then join us and we will ravage the world!
Now is the time of darkness, when Orc and Necromancer shall inherit this rock they call a world.
Let us unite, my kin, with a signed treaty - and together our blood line shall take throne.
The Vampire Counts shall inherit the Old World. Its tombs and gardens of death will open for us - together!
What is your greatest desire? Riches, trinkets, power… eternal life?
If you prefer I can give you the gift of my blood, a few drops is all it takes. Or you may choose anything in my vaults if your tastes are more… mundane.
I have a gift for you, best not to refuse and repeat the tragedy of McDeath.
We have a mutual enemy. Let us march with you and we will ensure victory.
This is a war you cannot win alone.
Add our unholy might to yours, and victory will come. We can then unpick the consequences of any pacts.
Rest in peace…
Our magicks weaken, so perhaps a cessation of the war is best?
We return to our graves and ready ourselves for Geheimnisnacht. You have peace until then.
You have peace, Bretonnian. Bury your dead for they will not rise... for now.
We are fed up of your rotten peasants, Bretonnian. There is peace because we crave fresh, wholesome bodies.
Peace it is, Northman. Let Khorne worry about constant war, for we have all the time in the world!
We know all too well what it is to desire blood. The difference between us, Chaos scum, is that we can control our thirst, so let peace reign.
No, Dwarf, there is no need to war. We return to Hunger Wood and the surroundings of Corpse Run, where we shall slake our desire for bloodshed.
Take the offer of peace, Dwarf. Forget your grudges and serve your race's interests for once.
Vorhexen approaches. Go in peace, and have Morr's Priests prepare for the Night of Witches. Expect us to call then - Morrslieb shall be our sign.
I can say it in any language you wish - Khazalid, Queekish, Reikspiel? It is an offer of peace from the Midnight Aristocracy - I suggest you take it.
Peace, Orc - set your filthy minions on weaker prey, for we tire of you.
We will stop despoiling your filthy corpses if you stop attacking our lands. There are plenty of other, breathing creatures to annoy.
Peace, my blood kin. Instead of war, let us drink a fine vintage - I have particularly arrogant Bretonnian noble in my cellar, with ripe veins.
We offer peace. There will be a place at my table, should you accept.
There is only the Vampire Counts!
No! Why would I walk in the light when I can stride alone at night!
The only confederation will be when you have turned and are my willing thrall!
There is no rest, no peace - just Undeath!
No, your time has come.
Peace? That is what Otto von Drak begged for one night long ago, do you think our kind would revel in such power now had we granted such a feeble request?
Beg, Bretonnian. Lay down your lance, sully yourself in the mud and then beg for peace. The answer will still be no.
There is no reason for peace. We despise your pitiful nation and will not stop until its people are part of my legions.
Peace with the puppets of Chaos? Proof that the Ruinous Powers fear us - they know the true Dark Lords hail from Sylvania.
You betray your brass god do you not, by asking for peace? How delicious! The answer is no.
We reject peace, Dwarf. Go back to your Holds, seal your gates, and know they will become your tombs.
Yours is a fetid race, one cursed with undeserving pride, which would be better purged from the world - that is the task I have set my tireless legions.
The only peace will be when the true Emperor sits upon the throne and wields Ghal Maraz. The Empire of Night will come!
The lambs of the Empire call for peace but all I hear is their bleating!
No peace, Orc, your race are pests that need eradicating.
There can be no peace with Greenskins. They are not mentally able, so we will wipe them out.
I dominate the von Carsteins. You should have bent your knee earlier; now you will pay with the loss of your head.
There can only be peace in Sylvania when these petty squabbles between kin are ended. And I will end it, for I am the true Lord of the von Carsteins.
The Undead march forth, it is war!
We declare war, let night come forth!
War, mortals! All will die and rise again.
Time to end your pitiful nation once and for all, Bretonnian!
The peasants will revolt. But as my minions - war comes to Bretonnia!
War is as inevitable as the grave. Prepare thyselves, Chaos filth!
It is war! Surely your Blood God will rejoice?
We will bring death to the Dwarfish realms - war!
War! The Age of the Dwarf is over, the Age of Undeath has begun!
The Vampire Wars begin anew!
Sigmar cannot protect you, mortals, war comes!
It is war, then, Orc filth.
We will bring ruin on your tribes, Orc!
Sylvania will be overcome with war, it is time the lesser Vampires realised who is in charge.
It is war! I am Undeath Ascendant, my will alone and no other!
There is a stain on the world, and that blight is called Bretonnia. But please, do go on!
Ahh, my old stomping ground, so many deaths… is this a parley to stop me returning, I wonder?
The minions of a King! Come to take my tally no doubt. Let us haggle for souls!
I see no great Bretonnian flower here, what has become of my adopted nation?
Ahh, it is good to be back in Bretonnia, how fair's the abbey at la Maisontaal?
Greetings, messenger, tell Leoncoeur that my services are always open to him.
Chaos… you think you control me… bah! I am Kemmler, the Lichemaster, my destiny is my own!
Lickspittles approach me thinking they're in control. But I am the one that holds life or death in his hands.
Agents of Chaos, free me from these invisible obligations so I may cause my own mayhem!
The Dark Gods petition me, but they shall realise that I am no being's puppet!
Greetings, how do my true masters fair in these gloriously dark days?
At last the Chaos Gods come to me directly. What is their desire?
Approach me Dwarfs, envoys of your stunted kin, your offer better tickle me or I will damn you all!
Oh, how I enjoy the pleading, mewling bray of Dwarfs! It makes all this worth while!
Stunted beard-creatures, what have we here? You reach out to me, how wonderful!
There's desperation in your voice, Dwarf, be reassured that I find great pleasure in that!
Ah, the Dwarfs come to treat, to plead perhaps? To beg I don't reanimate their precious ancestors?
The Dwarfs - I have met your kind when I was wondering the mountains, you are beasts of burden are you not?
Your Emperor’s mewling entreaties are as insufferable as the cries of a new-born child – and as easily choked off.
Death comes to all eventually, and no pathetic Soldier-God may forestall that meeting. Time passes: speak!
Oh, look, it's Sigmar's weak-willed progeny - I have dealt with you before it will take little effort to do so again.
Your Empire is finished! So it is wise that you seek out my children and I.
Ahh, Sigmar's children are my favourite vessels, I'm sure we can come to some arrangement, yes?
Your eminence's emissaries are always so wary of me, I am but a humble old man looking to extend my miserly lot.
Careful now, to summon me is all but an invite to join my hordes.
Say what you must - but know you play a dangerous game, and I am no pawn!
My minions are restless, this had better be important… for your sake!
I will hear your words - your riddles! - but best not displease me, Krell would not like that!
A message, for me? Then best deliver it, my children may not be impatient, but I am.
Go on then, speak your words, but don't mistake for some hedge-wizard - I have more important masters than you.
My Skull Wand cackles in my ear… it tells me you have a proposition, yes?
Excuse the tomb-breath, now, what is it you want?
You summon the Lichemaster, I see, I see. A pact is it?
I always distrust Orcs that come to barter when they should be here to kill - weak specimens of their race.
Greenskins - it is better say something interesting or I'll curse their whole sorry race.
Orcs approach - how delightful! Should I have my thralls gut you now, or after you have spoken?
The Greenskins are indeed a blight on the lands, mayhaps I can tame them?
Greenskins, another of my favourites, what is it you desire?
You know, many of my kin, cannot bring the Greenskin form back to life. I have no such trouble!
Oh, should I bow and scrape? The great vampire blood lines deign to call upon humble me…
Vampires and Necromancers both, they think they can raise the dead! But there is only one Lichemaster!
We will parley - for now, fellow immortals, you have the ear of the Lichemaster.
You will deliver your message to me and I will then decide on its worthiness, my lord.
My lords von Carstein, how may thy humble Liche, serve you this night?
I am always open to furthering the course of Unlife, please, please let's discuss plans.
The pact is signed, pray it has only cost what you believe it has! Haha!
So mortal, we have an agreement. Do not cross me, for that will be the last mistake you make.
Mortal, we will accept but do not mistake this for anything but a convenience - we are not your allies, we are your masters!
I accept, now you must fulfil your promise or I bring eternal darkness upon you!
We will bind this treaty in blood. The cost if you renege? Just your immortal soul!
Only the well-prepared or the very foolish join a pact with a Vampire. Now the deal is done, which one are you?
A pact then! My services for what I desire, the price maybe too dear?
An agreement - mine hordes shall rejoice, for I will command them to.
Yes, there is a way we can both claim what we need from this understanding.
You come with Lady's tidings? What does that lake-hag want?
Before we can begin, I must slaughter all the low-born in your ranks. They are your gift, yess?
Impress me then, Bretonnian. What favour does your impuissant nation deign to ask?
Bretonnia must be in trouble to come here. Does Mousillon fare badly?
Bretonnians! Come then, let us eat and talk - once the meal is over I’ll decide if you shall live.
What message do you bring, Bretonnian? Do the living still delude themselves?
Your folk taste of desperation and sorrow - it is a fine vintage, so let's agree terms.
Yes, you will do as I say, Bretonnians - if you value your pathetic lives!
Agreed, but do not risk offending me by asking for further quarter, Knight.
As a show of favour I require the company of your damsel... no "permanent" harm shall come to her.
Very well, Knight, we have an accord, pray to the Lady that you do not disappoint me.
I'll take your word, mortal creature, but if you do not deliver I will find you.
No, your insignificant country is finished, fools! Your only choice is to bow before me and pray on my mercy.
I reject this and any such offer, why would I need the aid of such living, feckless cowards?
Haha, Bretonnia is a mongrel nation and I have no desire to help it.
Never - tell your lake hag I will drink her life force, should we ever meet.
No, this won't do, not this day or ever, Knight.
Get from my sight, Bretonnian, you are lucky that I am sated.
So be it - a union with the Archaon's insipid followers is a small price to pay for mine own domination.
Yes, a pact, but do not betray us, even your gods will cower before my wrath!
Good, this is a pact, the forces of Chaos and Undead will join and those of Order will pay.
Agreed, Northman, do not fail me.
Good - the Dark Gods shall work in concert with mine own designs.
Very well, creature, tell your true masters we have a deal.
Careful, Warrior, for you know not who you treat with. My power is death; my will absolute.
I have no more patience for the maggots of Chaos, they are nought but scavengers in my wake!
Spit your hate at me, Chaos creature, I care not for your Gods or their threats!
Rage all you wish, minion, but know that I am no peon, I create them!
What is your message, Chaos pawn? Mark that you do not address some quivering mortal!
Welcome, messenger of the Dark Gods, if your terms intrigue me, we could work together.
You think me weak, Chaos scum? I am a Lord of Darkness and answer to no god!
Your Gods cannot touch me, thrall, my will is stronger than any atrophied deity's!
No. I do not fear you or your Gods for my soul has already been claimed.
Chaos creature - go back north to thy fetid realm, tell your masters these mortals are mine.
No Chaos thrall, my destiny will not be tampered by Tzeentch.
Alas, I must reject this notion, although we may join our damned forces in the future.
Sign your precious contract, bearded creature, parchment will do you no good when I bore of it.
I demand a sacrifice to prove your willingness to this endeavour, but what will it be? A life or your so-called honour?
We have a blood pact then, Dwarf. It will cost you more than dishonour if you break it.
Very good, I know such a treaty raises the hairs in your beard, Dwarf. That thought alone makes this worth it.
Very well Dwarf. Show me your contract and I will sign it… in beardling blood!
Good, Dwarf, you'll do as I say!
You think your broken empire can be repaired, Dwarf? You are wrong and my legions will prove it!
Never! My Crypt Ghouls will gnaw on your ancestors' fetid bones!
I think not, stone-gatherer! Your desolate mountain slums offer nothing for my host.
There is no pact! Your arrogance will be your undoing, Dwarf scum!
No, stone-gatherer. Back to your mountain holes.
Don't be foolish, Dwarf, I care not one bit for your barren halls.
Why do the Dwarfs pester me so? I have had my fill of their stunted forms and baseless pride!
The last time I killed a Dwarf, I sucked the marrow from his iron-flecked bones, but do go on…
Dwarfs… Rarely can you get a clean bite of their neck, far too hairy, what do you want?
Tell me Dawi, why should I not leech you of life whence you stand?
Why Dwarfs! How amusing of you to deign to talk to me. What do you wish?
Here come the Dwarfs to sour my mood, what do the stone-gatherers want?
I wonder which one of your party is a Witch Hunter? He shall die first.
So, Franz sends his sheep to bargain for their own lives. A pity it is harvest time.
Welcome to the midnight realm, pray to your Man-God we come to an accommodation.
Greetings, only noble blood should deign to negotiate and we are the noblest of all!
Then we have a pact - betray this and I'll bleed every Sigmarite priest from here to Altdorf!
What a strange night! Me allying with the bags of flesh I call food!
Do not be afraid - you will find me a benevolent lord, as long as you do not fail me.
Sign the treaty in blood, mortal. I wish - I need - to see you bleed!
Sigmar's heirs shall ally with Vlad's progeny - truly a match worthy of legend!
Yes, we have a pact, Empire-men. Do not disappoint me.
You come in the name of 'Sigmar', a mere mortal man born of camp whores, yet called himself a 'god' - what, mortals?
The Empire is finished, you mortals just wont accept it. Speak then…
What fools Ulric's progeny are! If you leave here alive you will do so as my puppets!
No! I will never signs pacts with Karl Franz' inbred brood - you are not even fit to drink!
Curse all the living, and their fruitless attempts to remain so.
Your Empire is doomed - it will be Sylvania that rises from the ashes.
No, I find your kind - breathers - too disagreeable.
Thank your Man-God that I don't feed on you right now! Be gone!
It will do I suppose. However, I bore easily these days, so keep your stinking minions on-side or else.
It is an accord, creature, but only while our ends walk the same path, once we diverge you shall be exterminated.
Yes, Orc, we have a deal. Pray to whatever disgusting gods you worship that I don't change my mind.
I accept your terms, Orc. Should you fail then your body is mine to take.
Very well, the crude beasts shall rampage and our silent armies will follow in their wake.
Good, an agreement. Let us hope the Orcs are capable of remembering it is in place.
A strange notion - mine noble blood line allying with such base creatures. No, better to destroy you.
Even Nagash, balked at allying with Greenskins. For once I agree with him - not ever, Orc scum!
No, my bloodline is pure, I will not sully it by working with such creatures.
I will not consider such an alliance. You are base creatures and I only feast on the finest.
No, Orcs, I don't trust you - I despise free will.
Foolish Orc, just because I prefer to drain humans doesn't mean I cannot snack on beasts!
Morrslieb glows… I can tell, for you come thinking to bargain, but I have already won!
There is desperation in your pitiful eyes! That knowledge alone will be leveraged against you!
You reek of anguish, or hopelessness, haha! Yes, let us parley!
Mannslieb wanes and Morrslieb waxes, of course I was expecting you.
Ahh, you come here in desperation, yess? Good, I can deal with desperate mortals.
To stand before me and ask, proves you are no craven… but cowards often live longer!
Why, do come - what can we help you with this night?
Ahh! You seek out the von Carsteins, a bold action…
I'll have you speak now, pray to your gods I like what you say.
What could you possibly offer me, Orc, I cannot even drink your abhorrent blood!
Greenskin, I cannot tame you, so tell me, why I should not wipe you out?
How vile… what could you possibly offer me, Orc?
Greenskin, you are stood before me alive for I despise the taste of your fell blood, so speak.
I will address the Orc creature, I hope I can understand its guttural tongue.
Deliver your message, Greenskin, just maybe we can work together.
Never! You are to be dominated, not appeased!
Foolish mortals, why would we treat with cattle?
No, prepare your armies, ready your defences - it will do no good!
No, why should I make pact when I can take what I need from you?
No! You offer me baubles! I will take what is rightfully mine!
There is nothing as foolish as a mortal with a shred of power. I can show you true power!
No… and thank your pathetic gods my attention is pulled elsewhere.
I think not!
Not this time, but should you desire something more then call on me.
Dawn approaches and mongrel blood lines come to leech off me. What do you want, half-breed?
Call yourself von Carstein? I have seen Strigoi more noble than you! Your offer then?
Welcome, kin. You must want something, it better not be my head!
It is always a pleasure - a dubious pleasure - to welcome a fellow Lord of the Night to my domain.
Greetings, brothers, what does mine Blood Line require?
Very well, let us hold a conclave, my kin.
Very well, cur, but betray me and I'll take your head and gift it to Volkmar's minions.
Agreed then, parasite, for that is all you are!
Yes, we will swell the von Carstein hosts, and the living shall fear us!
With Morrslieb so high in the sky, it makes sense for a union.
Yes, together we will feast on mortal flesh!
Agreed, kin, this will end mortal dominion.
No, do not mistake us, we are not the same. You are a vessel of filthy blood, mine is pure and I shall wipe you out.
Parasites are drawn to me like fleas on some mangy cur! Get thee from my sight or I'll end you!
I don't think so. I do not need your shambling hordes, I have access to much better stock.
With callous respect, I reject your offer... it lacks bite.
As the true master of this realm, I disagree.
Please - challenge me, feel my power and realise you are outmatched.
You come with Lady's tidings? What does that lake-hag want?
Before we can begin, I must slaughter all the low-born in your ranks. They are your gift, yess?
Impress me then, envoy. What favour does your impuissant king deign to ask?
Bretonnia must be in trouble to come here. Does Mousillon fare badly?
Bretonnians! Come then, let us eat and talk - once the meal is over I’ll decide if you shall live.
What message from your king, Bretonnian? Do the living still delude themselves?
Careful, Warrior, for you know not who you treat with. My power is death; my will absolute.
I have no more patience for the maggots of Chaos, they are nought but scavengers in my wake!

Very well, let us hold a conclave, my kin.
I will take thy word, but only a fool would renege on me. Are you a fool, mortal?
Bind your soul to this commitment. It is forfeit if thou fail me!
I accept those terms, but the reek of betrayal surrounds thou. I warn thee, do not succumb to it!
I accept these terms, we'll sign the contracts in blood… thy blood.
We have agreement, mortal, keep thou side of the bargain and I may do mine.
Very well, we have a pact. Do not disappoint me.
A fine choice, one I will savour!
Thou hast chosen wisely, mortal.
This is the correct pact to make!
Thou strivest to preserve that which is already lost, Bretonnian fool. Nevertheless, I will hear thine offer!
I shall harken to thy king's words - but I can already tell thee, the answer shall not be to thine liking, mortal…
Bretonnian, make thine offer. Only then shall I decide if thou join mine hordes or return to thy feckless lands.
I struggle to address the riddle in mine head - art thou brave or foolish for approaching me with this 'offer'?
Hahaha - mortals of Bretonnia, welcome. Drink of this wine, I have some robust reds in my cellar…
How fares thy kingdom? I hear of unrest in thy city of Mousillon, nothing too troubling I hope…
A truce then - if such a thing is needed with such an insignificant nation of flesh bags.
Scrawl thy name on this contract mortal, do it in blood so I can scent you out, when thy betray me!
I accept, mine Knights and thous shall charge as one.
Very well - thy smallfolk shall not be feasted on until our alliance comes to an end.
Yesss, why not… and should thy troops prove feckless in life I may have a use for them in death.
We have a pact, thrall of the Breton. Do not fail me.
I have no time for such pathetic creatures - thy blood is thin, thou lands are riddled with disease.
Haha, you are some thrall, recently emerged from the Blood Kiss? My legions shall march on Bretonnia not ally with it!
Back to your dreary land, mortal - tell the wench you worship that I shall suck her people dry!
No… Now thy must face my legions... and they hunger…
I think not. Take your offers back to thy wretched realm; tell thy nobles to expect me soon enough.
Such an alliance was always unlikely, mortals. Thy stock tend to make weak allies.
So be it. I'll deign to work with the Chaos Gods, but take care not to let thy servants anger me, for there will be consequence.
Yes, we shall work together to free the world of the living, but when thou think to betray, know that my vengeance will run deep.
This suits our purposes, tell thy master we have a pact.
Very well, but do not mistake this for acquiescence on all souls. The von Carsteins will have their share!
Agreed - the mortals will despair!
Yesss, a doom befalls the world. If I can't have it no one will!
The so-called Everchosen has no idea with whom he trifles! Bid him to step into thine court so that I may rip his throat out!
Thine Chaos Gods are spectators to what happens here. I am the God of Inexhaustible Blood and I shall have my way!
Chaos, thy Gods mutate thee as reward, but I can give thee the ultimate gift… death.
Speak then, Northman, but know I shall drink thy bestial blood if thou displeases me.
Welcome, brothers of the darkness. What could mine blood line do for thee?
Ahh, the minions of Chaos, come to mine grave, looking for common cause no doubt?
No, the mortals belong to me! Send thy champions in challenge and I will end them all.
I think not! Tell thy Lord Archaon, he is a greedy peon to weakling Gods and that will cost him dear!
No, tainted ones, I would feast on your flesh if I knew thou blood was not infected so.
I see no benefit here - Archaon is a fool, a charlatan who needs to be taught a lesson in manners.
Thou hast erred, Chaos thrall - we both wish death upon the world, but while thou take souls - I cull them!
Impossible - the cattle are mine to reap, not yours to taint!
An alliance with piteous stone-gatherers and grudge-mongers? Very well, mortals.
An alliance with such close-minded creatures… acceptable on this occasion.
Why, yes, prepare thyselves, Dwarfs, for my stipend will be demanding.
I see. Ally with us, and I'll overlook the perceived notions of unfairness recorded in thine little book.
I take your pledge, Dwarf, ensure it is kept as thy reputation states.
Yesss, let's seal it in blood, even the dusty blood of thy Dwarfs will do!
I'll have no such thing! Thou are creatures of deformed height, and I will spare thou no mercy!
Prepare, Dwarfs, for when I come for you I shall shave the beards of thy Unliving corpses!
Thy beards must be interfering with thy heads, we will not ally with stunted hole-dwellers!
I am von Carstein! You think I need the help of an atrophying empire to further my destiny!
Ha! I think not, stone-gatherer. I've had my fill of Dwarf bile this night.
No, I grow weary of Dwarfs. Their blood tastes as dour as their mood.
Speak thy insults, stuntling – let me hear thy pleas, for it is music to mine ears.
Dwarfs! Would that Nagash had wiped thy sorry race out when he had the wherewithal to do so! Speak then!
So, the bothersome stone-gatherers come from their mountain-holes to plead for mercy?
I have no time for stunted-folk, they hold no interest. Dwarf-creature, hast thine words import?
Stunted folk, I greet thee but do not presume too much.
Dwarfs! Thy lives are reckoned long, but the grave is eternal!
The Emperor! A false title! Be careful what you say, mortal, for I am the true Emperor!
So, the sheep come to debate with the Shepard! Very well, deliver thy message.
Men of the hammer - tell me thine tales of woe and a true count of the realm shall appease them!
So, Volkmar sends thou to barter in his stead... What a delicious proposition.
I do this for Sylvania. Make no mistake, mortal fools, this grants thy a reprieve and nothing more.
These terms will have to suffice, but I'll seek proper redress in due course, mortals - have no fear about that!
I see no reason, as the true Count of Stirland, to add my levy to Franz' army.
Fine. The Undead and the living shall work as one.
Yes, as Lords of this realm it is our duty to work as one for the good of our nation…
An accord then, thy commonfolk shall step in unison with mine own sleepless warriors.
Dost the Heldenhammer know what wretched creatures hath sired in his stead?
Does Franz not dare to come before me and kneel? A coward then, as the Princes of Altdorf have ever been!
Why would I, the greatest of all von Carsteins, deign to ally with my food?
Your decrepit Empire is not worthy to form a pact with my sleepless legions! I will see you all dead before I share the glory with the living!
Haha, why should the herder have to treat with his cattle when he can whip them into obedience!
If Vlad would not deign to treat with mortals of the Empire what makes thou think I will…
Franz oversteps his bounds! He is self-declared emperor of the living. My legions do not recognise his authority.
No, as you stubbornly refuse my right to rule mine own lands, I refuse your notions of alliance.
To end civilisation then, Greenskin filth, but do not forget who is the master and who is the dog!
A horde is a horde whether made from my servants or Greenskin beasts. It's purpose will be the same.
Together, beast, we will hunt our prey.
Then let the Orcs run rampant! My servants will be ready to pick through the corpses in the aftermath!
Fine! If the Orcs want nought but war and death… then I will find it for them.
We will work with these green beasts. Let them be the scythe of our harvest.
Get from my presence, creature! Thou are nothing but Strigoi fodder - to even suggest an alliance with mine bloodline is grave insult!
I think not, my legions will slay thy green beasts - I haven't the time or inclination to tame thou!
My bloodline is of the highest nobility; to even consider an alliance with base creatures like these is an impiety too far!
Get thee from my realm, creature! I will not even taste your blood, that should be the greatest offence of all!
Haha - a laughable notion. They are dim-witted beasts, we are regal lords - there's no common cause.
I don't think so, Greenskin. But please, keep killing the humans, their corpses make fine troops.
Mortals… thou hast trespassed. Thy words had best hold prominence or death will visit thee!
Speak thy words and pray to thine pitiful little gods that they ring true!
Do not underestimate the danger thou art in, mortal, mine patience wears thin for thy parley.
The night grows long. I shall hear thee mortal, but talk is cheap!
Don't stand there like some startled sheep! Deliver thy message, lamb, so I may consider a response.
Welcome to mine realm. Let no man say otherwise! For it is *mine* lands you tread upon.
Welcome to my realm, mortal.
Greetings, thou stand before the rightful Elector of Stirland!
Sylvania greets thee, friend...
I shall not ignore the forms - talk, beast, then I shall kill thee.
Orcs! I shall hear it out, and then I shall feast upon its bones should its' words displease me.
What, Greenskin? I am immortal and yet I have little time for thy guttural tones.
I have no interest in these green beasts, their blood tastes foul and they refuse to be dominated.
Talk to me beast, spit out thy base demand.
Greenskins! I have witnessed thy kind many times before, what could thou possibly offer me?
You forget thyself, mortal. I am a von Carstein! THE von Carstein. Thou will learn to respect that name, as thrall to my will!
Thy words are as meaningless as thine miserable life!
So careless, so insignificant - that is what you are to me, mortal insect! I refuse thy insolent offer.
Ha-ha-ha, you think me dense, perhaps? Do not underestimate me… others have and paid with their souls.
The curse of my kind - I talk and negotiate with my food! Would men bargain with cattle? I think not.
I have heard what you have to say. I reject it, as I do all wants and desires of the living.
Alas, with the blood moon hanging so low in the night sky… I must refuse.
You would do well to withdraw…
No, mortals are so impatient. Consider thyself chastised.
Now is not the time, for petty politics, mine brothers, mine kin! Any who defy mine will shall be destroyed!
Come, but do not assume that as we share a blood line thou shalt not be shackled to mine will!
Greetings, kin, mine will dominates here, do not mistake this parley for anything else!
Thou wish'st to entwine hordes? As head of the dynasty it shall be mine to command.
Fellow beatless hearts, let us discuss the destruction of the living, yes?
My kin, I am pleased thou attend'st me.
I am Lord and master, thou acknowledge this with the sundering of thy minions to me!
Let us make a bond on this, but I warn thou, to defy me will be thy greatest mistake!
We have agreement, but make no mistake who leads this host!
All fall beneath my will, thou are simply ushering in the inevitable.
Yes, together our tireless legions will ensure Sylvania's expansion.
Good, we share the spoils - the wide-eyed cattle - between us.
I am Mannfred, the greatest to bear the name von Carstein, thy host is insignificant to me!
From the afterlife, even Nagash trembles at my name - do not think thou can challenge me. The mortals are all mine!
I think not, the death-tally will be mine and no other kin or Necromancer can claim it!
Fools! You are mere dabblers in death, I am Mannfred von Carstein, Morr's realm is mine!
No - my stock is superior, I do not wish to taint it with inferior pawns.
Our goals suffer. Go, but best not cross my path again. It would prove thine downfall.
Yes, we have a pact, but do not interfere in my affairs…
Agreed, though there is an imprudent streak in you. Perhaps I shall have the Crypt Ghouls beat it out?
Yes, sign your precious parchments - as if it means anything to me!
I agree - now the delicate issue of remuneration… it won’t be something as crude as gold that I need.
That is what we agreed. Now leave me to my works.
We have a deal. Prepare the tombs, I require ingress.
Good-good, when do we begin?
Very good, you will not regret this - you'll see!
Yes, this is the right course of action - my servants will start preparations right away!
What demands are you to make, envoy of a fettered king?
Make your offer, then go and tell the Enchantress-hag her nation is dead!
Come Bretonnians, tell me, what can you possibly offer this humble conjurer?
I'll hear what you have to say, only when I'm ready Bretonnian!
So, Bretonnian, I am here, are you ready to make a pact.
I'm glad you are here, Knight, we can work together but my price is your low-born.
Yes, your puppet-king will surrender to me!
The terms are signed, you cannot back out of it now - watch your country wither!
Very good - once you have come round to my way of thinking, you'll realise that this is the right course.
Ha! Those pesky morals, eh? Yes discard them, or hide behind some greater 'chivalrous' notion!
Yes, Bretonnian, we shall work together. There are so many crypts, so many barrows in your lands!
Good, Morr is weak in your nation. We have agreement.
You have nothing, Bretonnian. What could I possibly want in your fetid mudhole of a country?
Fair Bretonnia is fair no more - tell the lake hags that I will take what I need!
No, Bretonnian, that water sprite you claim as a god takes against honest folk such as I.
A kingdom of fools is soon separated from the lands to which it lays claim.
I don't think so. Your king doesn't appreciate my arts. Ask those in Mousillon.
No… I am busy elsewhere, Bretonnia holds nothing for me.
Very well, tell your Everchosen we have a deal. If he betrays me, we'll see how chosen he truly is.
So be it, Northman, but my rights to the dead are sacrosanct!
I ascent to your demands, Chaos creature, but my soul is mine own to damn - you cannot claim it.
Good - my tireless hordes are at your disposal - you have my fee?
Yes, start your killing, Northman, but leave the bodies for me!
Good, the pact is signed. You may have my soul of course - not that it will ever leave this body!
Archaon 'the ever-fool', does that not sound a more accurate title? I'd agree if you wish to flatter me into an alliance? Yes?
I will hear your grovelling pleas 'get of spawn' but you have no power over me!
So Chaos-minion, you come to parley with life-givers and dead-takers, you must need something?
Go on then, deliver your Gods' message - but remember, threats won't work against me.
Chaos, I admire your Gods, although they are too focused on capturing souls when the vessels have far more use.
Well, well - what could such powerful figures as yourselves want with me and my humble arts?
I have no time, nor will I, to entertain Chaos scum. Go away!
Be gone, Chaos spawn, or I will turn you to dust!
I think not, tell Archaon to find another pet Necromancer!
No, and your attempts at intimidation are laughable, really.
No, Chaos, I have masters feared more than yours could ever be.
No - I serve other, more powerful beings. Death holds no fear, I crave it!
Well, well, so the Dwarfs do swallow their pride when they need to? What a delightfully bitter pill, yes?
A Necromancer saving the Karaz Ankor. Ha, I bet this really sticks in your craw, Dwarfs.
We have agreement - I take it you do not wish for the rest of the Karaz Ankor to know?
A fair exchange of goods, but do not threaten me again, Dwarf or I'll see you as a shambling lackey.
I accept, Dwarfs. I'll need access to your crypts, of course.
Good, then we can begin. I require Runelore.
Stick me in your pitiful little grudge book, Dwarfs. See if I care! You'll pay the price either way!
No, Dwarfs, no - the only bargain to be made now is when you beg for the corpses of your kin!
I don't need your baubles or promises Dwarf. It will be all there to take in time.
Go and cower in your mountains, Dawi, my legions will come to your door soon enough.
I think not, you Dwarfs have such a temper.
No stunted creature, I have no interest in your… kind.
What, Dwarfs? Should I animate your ancestors and have them hack off your beards?
I find your persistence tiring, stone-gatherer, perhaps a display of my power will get the respect I deserve!
Ahh, bearded folk, are you not blind, do you not see your domains are surely doomed?
Hail Dwarf! Times must be desperate indeed for Grudgebearer and his ilk to send his peons my way!
No need for Reikspiel, Dwarf, I speak perfect Khazalid, how else would I raise your kin back from the dead?
Stunted folk, your race is thin on the ground of late, perhaps I could help?
Do go on - threaten me with Helborg or Schwarzhelm's wrath if you must, it makes no difference.
Such insolence, do you think your pitiful lost god can save you? Utter your message and be quick!
Poor Sigmarite fools, I almost feel sorry for you, almost…
Ha! You think making pacts with Daemon-spawn is dangerous, Reiklander, I have yet to state my terms…
The Empire, bah! Such nuisances with your Witch Hunters and your Priests of Morr!
Greetings, envoys of Ulric and Sigmar, I trust you haven't come to kill me - yet - then what do you want?
Fine, but I'll slay any of Morr's priests that I see skulking around my domain.
Good, you accept the inevitable, that is the first step in your nation's doom.
Very well, but tell the Grand Theogonist to rein in his Witch Hunter dogs.
Agreed, but I'll need assurances that some Sigmarite fool won't blunder in to ruin it!
Very well - you have my list of requirements, just don't tell the Witch Hunters.
We have a pact then, Sigmarite. Good, good. I assume that the Theogonist knows nothing?
No, the Empire will fall - Franz's corpse will be mine willing servant!
I think not! The Heldenhammer is tarnished, the reign of the dead begins!
No, Empire fools, close your Gardens of Morr if you must, the tombs will still open for me!
Foolish mortals, do not trouble me with your earthly concerns!
No, I know your sort. You'll betray me to the Silver Hammer!
I think not, Reiklander. My arts are for my own gain and no-one else's!
Come then, Orc, send your hordes and I will deign to bring you prey.
Yes, creature, but raise your crude blades to me and I'll see you wither before mine eyes!
Yes, it will be a challenge, but I can work with such crude materials I suppose.
Accept the terms, Orc, then the reign of terror will begin!
Yes, yes, we shall work together, I only ask that you don’t mutilate the bodies too much.
Agreed. Sign in blood, Orc, and we will begin.
Leave me, creature, or you will be returned as Crypt Ghoul fodder.
Gah! Get out of my sight, Orc, or your armies will be nothing but ashes in the foetid winds!
No, beast, you will not interfere with my plans.
What kind of sorcerer do you take me for? I have no use for your… offer, Greenskin!
No, your crude bodies hold no interest for me, Orc.
I'm afraid not, beast, your kind offer no challenge.
What? Who dares disturb my great works!?
It is a imbecilic thing to bother me - others who have, end up as my puppets!
Speak now, then go, or my Zombies will pull out your tongues!
Is this what you truly want, mortal - my gift or my wrath?
Hmm, there are possibilities here, oh yes - but first we must negotiate.
Salutations! We have an issue don't we? Perhaps I can resolve it for a cost we can both agree on.
Greetings, let me rid you of those corpses that crowd your fields and cemeteries.
Oh dear, that smells like grave-rot - an unfortunate disease - perhaps I could supply a cure?
No, I'm not dead, my heart still beats. But am I mortal? Well, that's a different question entirely!
So, Orc, speak quickly! The grave-bound call to me, I have no time for you.
Make an offer but if I don't like it, I'll have your skin sloughed from your bones by Banshee screams.
So, Orc, what have you to barter?
Have your feeble gods sent you, Orc?
Orc, I find my peers can be very scathing about your kind, but not I. After all, a body is a body…
Welcome to my abode, Greenskin, does Mork - or is it Gork - bring you to me?
No, mortal! A pox on your lands! Death serves me!
Go now, prepare your troops for when I come - there will be a reaping!
Whether you want it or not, your dead will rise and serve me!
Oh no, you misunderstand, my stipend is not souls, that is what the minions of Chaos require - I need raw materials.
You have made a 'grave' error, and for that a punishment is needed.
Do not play with me, mortal. That would be your greatest mistake…
I fear that, not only are you wrong, but that you must pay the ultimate price.
No, this won't do at all.
Frankly, what I can negotiate I will take anyway. The dead do not ask permission to wake!
I expected the von Carsteins to come crawling as soon as they had a whiff that power could be had.
Approach me, acknowledge that even Nagash could not better my lore and then we may speak!
Of course, the grave-bound shall rise, but with me in charge.
You are all inferior - our allegiance is based on this fact!
Yes, masters, the lands will run red with blood!
Agreed, but though I have not been gifted the Dark Awakening, do not underestimate my power.
Yes, it will be done, my lord. The dead shall rise - Sylvania ascendant!
Yes-yes! We will join forces and takes the bodies from the living and the sleeping dead!
Welcome, masters - an agreement would be wise, after all we both need to further our plans.
Greetings, let us not waste our time comparing grimoires, straight to business I feel.
How may I serve, my masters von Carstein?
My humble skills are at your disposal, my lord.
No! Be gone, thralls - you are mere gutter-wretches, little more than starving ghouls compared to me!
Never - the power to command Undeath is all mine!
No, we must part ways, I see no gain from working with you.
I reject your terms, I have not been so demeaned since the treaty of Hunger Wood!
No, my lord, I shall have to decline. I am much too busy.
I know I risk a master's displeasure. but I cannot agree.
What demands are you to make, envoy of a fettered king?
Make your offer, then go and tell the Enchantress-hag her nation is dead!
Come Bretonnians, tell me, what can you possibly offer this humble conjurer?
I'll hear what you have to say, only when I'm ready Bretonnian!
So, Bretonnian, I am here, are you ready to make a pact.
I'm glad you are here, Knight, we can work together but my price is your low-born.
Archaon 'the ever-fool' does that not sound a more accurate title? I'd agree if you wish to flatter me into an alliance? Yes?
I will hear your grovelling pleas 'get of spawn' but you have no power over me!
So Chaos-minion, you come to parley with life-givers and dead-takers, you must need something?
Go on then, deliver your Gods' message - but remember, threats won't work against me.
Chaos, I admire your Gods, although they are too focused on capturing souls when the vessels have far more use.

How may I serve, my masters von Carstein?
My humble skills are at your disposal, my lord.
I have seen your banners burning, Bretonnian…
Is that fear I see? Well it should be! Hahahaha!
Bretonnians know much of the power of the Undead, do they not?
Shush, don't plague me now, I must speak to this Bretonnian!
What brings the men of Bretonnia to my darkened corner?
The noble Knights of Bretonnia are here to treat with us, my brothers!
Leave your dark masters. Come, serve me!
I am not some puppet who will dance to your tune!
How can I be of assistance in these times of darkness and woe?
Lords of Chaos, if you seek to control my mind you'll have to find it first!
I long to hear of the depraved deeds your masters seek!
How can I aid the Ruinous Powers?
I will bring your pitiful race to its knees, Dwarf! Starting with you!
Displease me and your honoured dead shall rise against you!
Who disturbs my research?
My mind may wander, Dwarf, but I will hear your words.
Why hello there Dwarf, what brings you here?
I can't ask them that! Sorry, my brothers have no sense of decorum.
You yearn for Unlife, don't you? I see it in the depths of your soul!
I will see you shamble before my cart!
Join me mortal, I will give your weak flesh true strength.
When I have quietened the voices in my head, I shall hear yours.
The Empire… I remember a village… No, it's gone!
Never trust a man of the Empire, they say… but I know they just mean Stirlanders!
Speak your words and be gone!
Leave me! I have better things to think about than your petty desires!
My dark path is set... Your words cannot change it!
Now you are here you shall serve me in death, forevermore!
Good, good… I am in need of more husks for my hordes.
In the far reaches of darkness… Ohh, when did you arrive?
If I could only find the right incantation… What do you want?!
I fear my mind wanders, but speak your words anyway!
Come, let me show you that death is never the end…
Don't be shy now.. My Plague of Blue Roses never killed anyone…
Hush, my brothers! We have a guest!
Welcome – I am Helman Ghorst, Master Necromancer!
Come, come, speak your words and I shall try to listen!
Do you have a corpse that needs raising, hmm?
My dead siblings and I welcome you.
Make it quick, I really don't like you!
Ahhh, I have no time for you, Greenskin! I have books to read!
Ohh how I would love a Greenskin for my army! Must find a way…
The stench of death lies heavy on you, Greenskin.
Move that corpse aside and make yourself at home, Greenskin!
Welcome! I am short a stool, so pull up a corpse!
What's that, my brothers? Kill them? Let's wait and see…
The dark arts are mine to command, I don't need you!
Yes, yes, always happy to serve the von Carsteins.
I am sure we can come to some mutually beneficial arrangement…
My quest for knowledge knows no end.
Welcome! Let us dive into the dark arts together!
The whims of thine watery mistress art of little consequence to me!
Speak plain, Bretonnian. I have no time for thine false courtesy!
I am willing to hear the pleas of thine Lady.
Your presence here is most amusing, Bretonnian.
Greetings Bretonnian! What doth thou wish to discuss!
Welcome! What word from the Lady?
You dare?! I shalt rip thee apart and watch thine empty soul return to thine masters!
Weak willed simpleton! Remove thine self from my sight!
What brings the minions of Chaos to my halls?
Look at thee dance, puppet! Deliver thine message.

You are yet to interest me.
I've no qualms using ensorcelled weapons against Cathay’s own!
What hope do you have against the Iron Dragon?
Ah, the pawn of Chaos, come to face bloody justice!
Hated betrayer! Your dark gifts are mere illusion!
I dream of your death nightly, wretch.
The Iron Wind will strip the flesh from your bones! I swear it!
You have brought death upon yourself.
Do not disgrace yourself by begging for your life.
A Dragon does not forget, and Zhao Ming does not forgive!
My newest Warpstone elixir requires a test subject. You will suffice!
I dream of flinging your carcass from the nearest mountaintop!
Begone, miscreant! We have nothing worthy of discussion!
You are governed only by spite and stupidity.
I have forged a weapon for the express purpose of executing you.
You are fit only for death, Daemon!
I will brew a powerful elixir from your burning blood.
Your Motherland has proven itself a disgrace. You will be corrected!
You squander your brief life on the worship of beasts.
Pestilent stain! You will be cleansed!
Cathay's people will remain forever safe from your pox, monster!
You will soon be slain, as all mountain brutes are.
Become Shang Yang's pack animal or accept death.
There is no place for your perversions in the Emperor's world.
The Iron Wind shall scour away your deviancy!
Chi'an Chi has sent you here to die.
Your desperate games are at an end, fiend!
Shang-Yang welcomes any Cathayan who can aid the Iron Dragon's forges.
The desert harbours powerful secrets that we can uncover together.
Have you come to seek penance for your betrayal?
Renounce the Great Enemy and we may yet work together.
You have the honour of meeting the Iron Dragon.
Perhaps we can forge a new path together.
Forgive me for not recognising you, friend I… took you for another…
I am busy with my alchemies, but for you I will make time.
For what reason am I disturbed from my experimentation?
Know that I expect my every utterance to be obeyed.
Who…? Ah, it's you. My mind was… elsewhere.
Tell me, how do you intend to assist the Lord of Shang-Yang?
I was not informed of this encounter!
For what do you drag me from the forge?
I do not fear the Great Enemy.
Such elixirs I could brew from Daemon blood…
What would your backward kingdom ask of Cathay?
I trust you understand that men obey Dragons?
You are grotesque beyond imagining! Fascinating…
Tell me why I should not part your head from your festering spine.
I have met many Ogres. Few have been inspiring company.
I am more accustomed to shooing your kind from the Western Provinces.
Did you think a Dragon would be shocked by your deviancy?
So Chaos finally accepts Grand Cathay's superiority!
My mind is shielded against Chi'an Chi's chicanery.
Do not seek to trick a Dragon, changeling.
A bargain most foul.
I must, though it is repulsive.
A pact with disease!
Disease addles your mind.
Chaos cannot understand negotiation.
A nauseating failure.
I will shake your meaty paw.
You have a keen mind, Ogre.
Ogres are underrated neighbours.
Leave me, brute!
Shameful avarice!
Gluttonous imbecile!
The Lord of the Jade-Sworn gladly receives you.
The Western Provinces bid you warm welcome, in most places.
Long may our understanding continue.
The Iron Dragon's assistance will only be granted for good reason.
Would you care for a demonstration of the power of fire and metal?
I am open to assisting your ends, so long as they do not obstruct mine.
Do not believe the slander about me. I am my father's most honourable.
Let's not allow pleasantries to delay more beneficial discussion.
Continue working with me and Shang-Yang will be a haven for you.
I understand there are important matters to consider?
Laughable.
You incite only fury!
You waste my precious time.
Why even bother?
I despair of this.
I must transgress.
Very well, fiend.
If only there were another way.
Cavorting fool!
I will not fund Daemonic vice.
Pointless depravity!
If I must, mutant.
My siblings must never hear of this.
A trade with foul Chi'an Chi.
The game is at an end.
Chi'an Chi wastes my time.
Worthless trickery.
A bargain is struck.
We agree.
How delectable.
I knew you would accept.
Good, good!
If it suits the Dragons, it suits me.
Your harmony remains.
Tell your Dragon Emperor we have a pact.
Come then, Daemon Prince show me what you can do.
Do you accept me, Daemon-kin?
From one Daemon Prince to another.
A pact with Brother Blood.
We have an accord then, blood-serf?
The Princes of Excess and Blood unite.
Kislev is safe. You have my word.
I embrace the Motherland.
Rejoice, peons, for you have my benevolence!
Do the weaklings of the eastern realms come to parley? You cannot afford it.
I delight in Cathay's woes. It brings me joy to see your nation suffer.
You are no Daemon Prince. You are an afterthought, a toy to be discarded!
I see a little soul in there. I wonder? What can you do for me?
Why are you so loathsome… so unworthy of my attention?
You are like a figment in a child's dream. Pray I don't become your nightmare.
You are the puppet, I shall pull your strings. Let us begin.
Azazel lurks… I await for you to manifest a scintilla of intrigue in me.
You deign to behold my beauty. For that there must be a cost.
I have no time for insignificants. I demand more important playthings.
There are those whose very existence annoys me. You are one of them.
Your life is so trivial. What do you want?
You remind me of Trinovantes' killer, and for that I shall extract a high price.
There is no free will here. Only what I deign to let you believe.
The Blood God's slaves 'Kill, maim, burn'; any fool can do this!
Boring fools – play with your food first. That's how you make it more delicious.
Does your country freeze, Kislevite? Blood and snow are yours.
The Motherland? A whore's land… I care not for the peons that live upon her!
Stay away! I will not be befouled by your touch!
Vile creatures! I care not for your desires, let us make this transaction quickly.
Fat, ugly creatures. Why should I barter with the likes of you?
You desire gold and cooked flesh. As obvious as the guts on your vile bodies.
Do not think to outshine me, servant. I am favoured of the Dark Prince.
You are a serf, a meaningless peon in my way.
Changer of the Ways? I shall make them change their minds alright.
Your puzzles bore me, minion, I see through them all.
A land of Dragons. How trite. What can I do for you?
When I was Gerreon, Sigmar told me of your empire. It sounded so fanciful.
Intriguing, a fellow Prince of Daemons… How should I respond?
Ooo, I see what burns inside you. Let me fan the flame.
Prostrate yourselves for being in my eminence!
I am Azazel – chosen to bring experiences to this plane.
Do you think me kind, or cruel? I will show you both aspects…
Forget your gods. What can they offer you, compared to me?
There is no wish I cannot grant, no desire I cannot fulfil. Tell me….
I already know what you want, it's so painfully obvious.
They call me Exalted Betrayer, but rest assured, I shall not betray you.
Come to me. Be my champion, my vassal… my new toy.
Yes, believe what your eyes see, am I not beatific?
You think to parley? Why bother with words? I know what you need.
Kharneth calls. Maybe I shall answer?
My father despises you… Yet I am not ready to hate.
Oh, Kislev. Yours hearts are chilled. Let me thaw them.
You are a bulwark against my brethren. And when that fails? You come to me.
Keep your distance, son of Nurgleth. Only then may we speak.
So the Plaguelord's maggots come to grovel.
Fat creatures, you repulse me… yet I might be able to use you.
The gluttons have come. So easy to manipulate.
Brothers, sisters. Let us rejoice and entwine.
Our mother-father encourages us into a tryst.
Do the pimples of Tzeeneth come to treat with me? Hmm, opportunity.
The Changer sends his squawkers. How delightful!
Plagues and desire as one.
Nurgle's servants accept.
Nurgleth's sons agree.
Seal the pact, fat-thing.
Agree it, Ogre!
You have the meat, I'll take the soul.
You come to me, how… delectable.
I know your wants – your desires. Still... Say them out loud.
You can trust me, just as Sigmar himself once did.
Radiate in my aura and realise your hearts greatest desire.
You'll find me a generous prince. Your grandest desires, fulfilled.
Come to me as a friend. I was a great friend… just ask Sigmar.
Take in my aspect, and revel in what could be yours to serve.
Submit to me, I have such wonderful plans.
Damned Prince is damned no longer. Greatness awaits!
I see your whims trapped behind your heart. Let me, unlock it!
Such delights to come.
The Dark Prince smiles on us both.
We are in accord.
The Changer's will aligns.
Reparations will be swift.
A pact with the Architect.
The Great Experiment will be better for this.
You have matched wits with a doctor.
A favourable outcome.
The prognosis is good.
Your wellness is assured.
No infections for you yet, then.
We shall entertain the Dragon's whims.
As you suggest, Cathayan.
Chaos never ceases to amaze.
You appear mindless, but are not.
I will oblige your masters.
An accord in lieu of bloodshed.
So Khorne has honour after all.
I keep my skull, you keep your health.
You have done well for Kislev today.
The cold does not skew your judgement.
It is agreed, Kislevite.
Whatever form the Dragons take, it will eventually be covered in boils and buboes!
Finally I can cultivate some rare eastern pathogens.
Immortality does not mean immunity!
I have the princeliest of plagues for you, my Daemonic friend.
I will make sure your sickness is terminal.
Your flesh clearly yearns for infection. I will oblige!
I shall kill you, then revive you, then kill you again!
Your cadaver will make an excellent test subject.
I cannot wait to get my scalpel into you.
Your demise will be the beginning of the end of your kind!
There's no leaving here without infection or death.
My plagues are coming for you!
You have entered my surgery. Now prepare to be cut open!
I see little more than a squirming organism to dissect.
Martial prowess is no use when you are regurgitating your own guts.
You will die as a leper, not a warrior!
My plagues will succeed where the Daemon hordes have failed!
Contagions love to proliferate in the cold.
Your horde are the basest bacteria in Nurgle’s estimations!
Your pathogens are weak!
So much flesh to infect! I shall delight in it!
Your bloated forms will be easy to strike down with pox-rot.
Your hedonism will be the end of you, if I do not kill you first.
A deathly pox-rot will be a fitting punishment for your sinful pastimes.
Life, death, decay. You are not above such changes.
I have just the deadly ailments for changelings like you.
Many are the shortcomings of Cathayan medicine.
The Dragons are not above the natural cycle of life and death.
You are sick beyond diagnosis, Daemon Prince.
Even a Daemon is not beyond fatal infection.
My company is not for the squeamish.
Speak carefully, for I know all your anatomical weaknesses.
My coming plagues will spare only the strong!
I could sell you an elixir, though I cannot promise it will heal you.
Won't you be a specimen in my grand experiment?
Delightful! Another potential carrier of contagion!
I've yet to decide whether you will leave here with your health.
Behold my boundless knowledge of disease!
It would be unwise to cross a doctor.
Embrace my virulence and you will be stronger for it.
Your incessant slaughter bores me, thrall of Khorne.
Why cut your enemies down when you can watch them die slowly of rot?
I know much of your frail anatomy, Kislevite.
The fragility of man never ceases to intrigue.
I could give you something so much better than your rudimentary afflictions.
What a delightful picture of sickness.
Your bulbous physiology fascinates me, Ogre.
You nomadic types are ideal vessels for contagion.
Disease can be a bodily pleasure too… let me show you.
Your debauch pastimes are ideal for disease transmission.
I dislike your unpredictable ways, but will listen.
There are organisms in petri dishes that I trust more than you.
We both have Nurgle's favour.
I knew I could trust a rot-kin.
Let us now experiment together!
You barter impressively… for an Ogre.
Your greed is strangely equitable.
The Maw clearly knows good diplomacy.
Nothing can ail you that my elixirs cannot remedy.
Any friend of mine is a friend of Nurgle's.
Is that a little cough I hear? I could probably fix that for you.
With my help, your enemies will soon be disease-ridden corpses for study.
Might you offer me a small biopsy sample? It shouldn't hurt… much.
What brings you into my surgery today, hmm?
May the Fly Lord spare you of His most deadly gifts.
My wondrous contagions are precursors to life!
Greetings! What a healthy specimen you are!
Do you seek my medical expertise or to profit from it?
I too take pleasure from this.
Your Prince will be grateful.
Does this feel good?
I see no chicanery here.
Nurgle's ends are begrudgingly served.
Some changes are for the better.
Cease your prattling! I accept.
I will tolerate this.
We have an accord.
This aids the cause of war.
These terms are adequate.
I will spare the Dragons from their ungodly despair.
Cathay escapes Khorne's bloodlust, for now.
The Dragons' incentives cannot be ignored.
Your Daemonic nature does not dampen your intelligence.
Chaos has gifted you well.
I will bicker no longer, Daemon.
Kharneth has us both in His dark embrace.
Let us toast and drink from blood-filled skulls.
We honour our master.
I see you squirm at my acceptance, mortal.
My murderous Lord knows this pains you more than I.
The people of the Bear know diplomacy as well as war.
I will ensure Cathay's destiny is one of war, anguish, and bloodshed!
Khorne prizes the Dragons' skulls above all others. I will deliver them!
Daemon-killing is not just my specialty; it is my pleasure.
Prince or not, another Daemon will die by my spear this day!
Your skull shall be removed slowly, in the most painful way possible!
Your lands will suffer my infinite rage! The rage of Khorne!
I will dismember you and hang your intestines from the nearest tree!
You will die weeping, like the snivelling coward you are!
I am the harbinger of your demise!
Still your tongue so I may rip it from your mouth!
You shall choke on a torrent of your own blood!
Your lifeless corpse shall be dedicated to the Blood God!
The Lord of Murder's host stands ready to annihilate your kind!
Your wretched flesh will suffer unthinkable torments!
Our Blood Lord demands your skull for your treachery!
Betrayal is weakness! You will pay the price in blood!
The Ice Queen will meet her end at the hands of the Gorequeen. How poetic!
I will enjoy fighting you to your inevitable death, Kislevite!
Will your severed head still emit your foul contagions?
Beneath your diseased flesh there is a skull that belongs to Khorne’s throne!
The size of your bloated skull matters little; Khorne bids me to take it all the same!
It is always a shame to destroy creatures of war, but still a pleasure.
The Reveller sends his minions to their deaths!
I will send you screaming back to the Palace of Pleasure!
Your silver tongue will convince me of nothing once I have removed it.
Killing the Trickster's slaves will give me considerable joy.
I am not ignorant to the Dragons' propensity for lies.
The Dragons are not my equals! I am true deific royalty!
Cower in the presence of true Daemonic power, minion!
You are nothing but an infantile beast to me, "Prince".
Do not dare to look at me as if I am beneath your fear!
The Gods give with one hand and take with the other. I simply kill.
Pledge loyalty to Kharneth, or die.
Make it fast and know that I always get what I want.
If you come for blood, it will only be your own that shall pour.
Attempt to deceive me and you will meet your end by Slaupnir's point.
Careful. Only fools make enemies of the God-touched.
Cross me, and I will be your most painful undoing.
Speak before my graven throne while I decide whether to take your skull.
Khorne does not ask much, only for you to slaughter or be slaughtered.
What will it be for you? Death or glory?
You know as I do that life without war is anguish.
Your mortal arrogance is palpable, Kislevite.
I am all that stands between you and Khorne’s hordes.
I do not often court the attention of the Fly Lord's servants.
Admit it! Murder is superior to sickness for killing one’s enemies!
You may be dim-witted, but your appetite for fighting is admirable.
Khorne is interested in all who revel in war, Ogre.
Your sloven, lustful ways make you weak.
The Reveller knows nothing of true glory.
You stand no chance of deceiving the right hand of Khorne.
Do not fan the flames of my anger with your trickery.
The Fly Lord gets what he wants... this time.
We have a deal, slave of Nurgle.
Our duties to destruction are served.
The creatures of the Maw are worthy of Khorne’s gaze.
So we agree on more than just senseless butchery.
You would be wise to give me absolute loyalty.
Play this game on my side and the rewards will be considerable.
You will facilitate my continued slaughtering, minion.
Only a fool would give me anything less than unconditional devotion.
Had I no use for you, Khorne would have me take your skull.
For now, your blood and skulls are yours to keep.
Any further dealing we have must lead to bloodshed!
Kill for Khorne as I do, and you will get your just rewards.
When you speak to the Gorequeen, the Lord of Murder also listens.
Khorne has witnessed you fight with honour, so orders me to spare you.
I loathe your debauchery, but accept your terms.
The Reveller does not waste my time for once.
Degrading, but unavoidable.
I expect we will both come to regret this.
Be wary that Slaupnir will punish any betrayal!
I still watch you with extreme suspicion.
[[col:blue]]…![[/col]]
If you find the terms acceptable, sign here and here.
We accept… do you?
Your obligations are enshrined.
Do not think to betray us.
You will not regret this, Dragon.
This has the Moon Empress' blessing.
Think of it as an investment, Cathayan.
You have made your mind up for once!
A pact is made.
See, there is more to life than bear-slaying.
Good. Now go, run along; kill something.
Yes, yes – Kill, maim, burn etc.
Excellent! Magic and Murder as one.
Kislev will be saved, we promise.
We embrace the Motherland.
This is acceptable to us, Kislevite.
Your little Celestial Empire is mine. You just don't know it yet.
Cathayans, all I need say to make you quail… We are Chi'an chi!
I have little time for such a needy little entity!
You think yourself a prince. I am true royalty! A 'King' of Misrule.
Don't look at him! Speak to me! I'm the one with the power!
Do you doubt our power? YOU DOUBT THE TWISTED TWINS?!
You think to spar with us? Even Thomin has more about him.
War is close, little puppets, do you wish a boon?
Weakling! You need something so you come to me.
I have foreseen your request already. It is pathetic!
Why so silent, did a brain-worm swallow your tongue?
You have knowledge to share, fool?
This had better be worth my time.
This will only extend my power!
You hunger only for blood, so easy to manipulate!
Scions of Kharneth, simpletons all! I will get my way.
Ours is the step-Motherland... Never did like you fools.
Such insolence from the Kislevites. Should I punish them, brother?
Keep your distance, plague-scum! I rule these negotiations!
Does your Grandad want something from me? He will struggle.
Fat fools! Think beyond your guts for one moment!
Ogres… disgusting things. They are more Thomin's level.
There is nothing I want from you that my master hasn't already given me.
Think to tempt me? Then you are a fool!
I am His ultimate champion, bow to me, bow to US!
There are known-knowns, but I am the known-known that you did not know.
The Cathayans come, should we change our tabards?
The Dragons debase themselves to parley with the Twisted Twins.
So, new boy, you think you're the only vassal with a grudge?
I know everything about you… while you wallow in ignorance.
Approach the Twisted Twins but ignore the lummox. I'm the one you want.
I am the mighty Vilitch, you are not so mighty…
A chance to do our master's work, here, brother… Speak then!
Oh it's you! It's you! ...Good…! Go on then.
Don't speak! Silence! Hmm, now you may talk.
Oww, now that is interesting. Intriguing even.
They wish to engage me, the Master of Misrule. See how they TREMBLE!
I like what I see, Thomin likes what he sees. You need us, don't you?
You are dullards. Unengaging – beneath me. What is it you want?
Don't look at him, there's nothing going on under that helmet, keep your eyes on me!
I do not care about the Bloodfather or His sons.
Thomin is no stranger to bloody rites, perhaps we can find common cause?
Kislev's carers come to cry at my feet. I shall take care of it.
Your nation suffers. Shall I make it worse or better, Kislevite?
What does the Urfather require?
Keep back, neither of us want your maladies!
Move your bulk forward so I can hear you better, fool!
Speak fast Ogre, I find your stench offensive!
What do you want, slithering-thing?
You cannot tempt me …What?! Shut up, brother!
We serve the same master, no need for subterfuge.
Are you part of my plan? Or am I a link in yours?
Accept it, Plague-maker.
Good, together we bring ruin.
The Urfather will thank you.
Don't let us down, Ogre.
Ogre! The pact is accepted.
Move your bulk, I accept.
Good, show respect, now get on your knees!
Thomin likes you... I don't.
[[col:blue]]…![[/col]]
Of course you come to me, an agent of the Changer.
I see the Great Sorcerer smiles upon you, as He did on me.
You wish for boons? You talk to me!
Stop moving, brother, I'm talking to this one!
What can the Masters of Misrule do for you?
I do so enjoy it when a willing puppet comes for his strings.
Welcome…. Good, my plan comes to fruition! I told you, brother!
See, you are the one tempted.
We are as one.
Acceptable, send the Dark Prince our regards.
Change comes to all.
We are in alignment.
Good, good... GOOD!
