The pact is struck.
I accept.
I give my consent.
There are many ways, this is but one.
There is more to decide.
Tell the Dragon-Emperor, yes.
Power from the east.
A wise choice, Cathayan.
You reject the Dark Master, Cathayan.
The Dragon-Emperor withers.
No, go back to the east.
The young Prince learns.
This time, you will win.
Ah, how my child has grown.
Not this time, puppet.
I don't take orders from a thrall.
No, little Prince.
More skulls for you.
Blood and shadows rise.
It is a pact, Khorne-follower.
Dust for the Blood God.
Go back to your master.
No skulls for you.
Perhaps a chance for Kislev.
All I ever wanted was to help.
Bearly acceptable.
Freeze and die.
Insignificant, Kislevites.
Your nation falters.
You have been an irrelevance for decades. You waste my time.
Tell the Emperor to get his withered form off his cloud. Then we will talk.
You are mine, mortal, your fate in my hands. What will you give to loosen the leash?
Call yourself a prince. No – I was the Prince… the first Prince!
I am the Harbinger, the Foretoken… the One-Who-Heralds!
I will not perform another coronation – there is no Everchosen, only me!
Do you think you can tread the shadow-paths as I? Fool!
I am all your nightmares as one, speak and I shall select your terror.
You stand before the Shadowlord, why do you not quake with dread?
Do not try to tempt or threaten me, I am the Dark Master – it is foreseen.
Yours is not to question me. I have always existed, accept it.
Fear me, for I am death and shadow. All I can promise you is fear.
You are not the Everchosen…. Far, far from it. Why should I even care about your wants?
You are either brave or a fool, I think the latter.
You are dull, your master unworthy of godhood – give that power to me.
I will negotiate while your master sits on his brazen throne barking like a senile mutt.
Your frozen nation is a speck, nothing more.
Tell me about that 'Prince' you sent to find Ursun.
I know what Nurgle did to his brothers… Should I tell them?
Don't threaten me with your poxes. Shadows are immune to your gifts.
Such greed - you have no idea, what it is to truly lust.
You want to feast? I'll give you all the flesh you crave, creature.
Your master is a lustful crone, grotesque and abhorrent – what could it want from me?
There is nothing you have to tempt me. I know what I want.
Your master is all pretty lights and bright colours… there is no substance. Never was.
Get from my sight, Tzeen-spawn! The shadows are my realm.
Your ideals intrigue me, perhaps we should know each other a little better?
Your disguise is interesting, but I know what your really are Cathayan.
We meet again, little prince. Is it time to be kind?
I made you, I expect gratitude.
Welcome, let me keep you in the shadows.
Do you wish to be crowned as the Everchosen too?
You are here because I deigned it.
No need to summon me, where shadows form I am there.
You play in the dark… that is my realm.
Stay in the shadows, and we might become allies.
You summon the *First* Prince, are you prepared?
Some call me the Dark Master, some call me Be'lakor, neither are my true-name.
You have found me, what will you ask?
I dreamt of a time where I flew across the stars, legions in my wake…
The master sends his dog to parley with me. Speak before your collar constricts.
What could the Blood God offer me that he hasn't already?
Your land of ice needs a little warming, does it not?
I know Ursun. We are old acquaintances, let me aid his nation.
Come then Plague Lord, let us see your latest concoctions.
I waited for Nurgle… he never answered my call, why should I answer his?
You want meat, Ogre, I can find you meat.
Some call me master… others a facilitator… do you want flesh?
Slaanesh forsook me. Why should I hear your lies now?
I am the one that lurks in the shadows.
The Changer cursed me. It is him I despise most of all, yet you dare come to me now?
Get from my sight, Tzeen-spawn! The shadows are my realm.
Your poxes ARE gifts.
Blessings to the Plague God.
I accept, pox-follower.
No, Plague God, no.
I decline your poxes.
I am immune.
We both shall feast.
Gorge yourself.
Our cravings are sated.
No Ogre, No.
The Maw chokes.
You best starve.
I don't think so.
You are no player of the Game
This is insignificant.
You disappoint me.
Our destinies part.
The Dark Prince and The First Prince together.
It is a gift then, Slaaneshi.
I could not resist, Slaan-gor.
Not to my taste.
Not tempted.
Dark Prince rejected.
I still don't trust you.
Your lies, hide truth.
Still, this will not end well.
Your well is dry.
Shadow takes flame.
Back to your master, Tzeen-spawn.
So you have seen sense?
You would make a good minion.
Excellent. The Ruinous crusade continues!
You have some wisdom, then.
I need not annihilate you.
The Dragon is a shrewd one.
There may be hope for Cathay yet.
Now leave before I change my mind and kill you.
We are indeed alike.
Prince raises up Prince!
We are in accord, my rival.
You have power, but no wisdom.
A poor bargain, my rival.
There is no kinship between us.
Well met, skull-taker.
Go with Khorne's blessing
Send thanks to the Murder King.
You think only of blood!
Return to your wretched skull-pile.
Barbarous Khornate worm!
Very well, Kislevite.
My hatred of Kislev abates.
A deal with the Motherland?
Kislev betrays me once more!
I never could depend upon Kislev.
The Motherland fails its children.
When Chaos finally engulfs you, I will be at the helm of it!
Cathay's denizens are destined to endure eternal torment!
There can be but one of us. It will not be you!
You! The inferior Daemon Prince. Know that I am supreme.
You are nothing to me. Nothing!
The only interaction between us I will permit is to crush you beneath my heel!
I will put out your eyes. I will rip out your tongue. I will drink your soul.
All this world will blacken and die. You and your followers are not excluded.
There is but one fate for all who oppose me: consummate annihilation!
I will subject you to a panoply of torments! You will beg me for death!
I am elevated beyond mortal pleasures, but I will take joy in your destruction.
All other lives are brief and pitiful against mine; yours will be more so.
You are here to die a slow, agonising death. There can be no other explanation.
Youl! When this world burns, I will place you atop the pyre.
Hated skull-takers! Forever underfoot during my crusade of conquest.
I will grant the Murder God's legions a taste of their own brutal medicine!
Most deluded and despicable of this world's people! I will destroy you!
Kislev. I no longer sleep, but if I did, I would dream of its annihilation.
Your pestilent interference enrages me! Make amends or know destruction!
A mere plague minion dares disturb me? I will have your rotted hide!
I will feed you to your Great Maw, then I will consume your Great Maw!
I will turn you inside out, brute! You will devour yourself!
Foolish Slaaneshi! Crossing me is a transgression you shall ever regret!
You think you understand pain. I will show you what agony truly means.
You will pay dearly for your tricks and treachery, changeling.
Send Tzeentch my regards once I have hurled you back to his Impossible Fortress.
I was once like your human form. Mortal and weak.
I yearn to put the Dragons' fabled immortality to the test.
We may co-operate, though ultimately only one Godling can prevail.
Lend your dark powers to mine, that together we might subjugate this mortal realm!
You are in the presence of unimaginable power. Kneel!
I will visit eternal torment upon all who dare oppose me. You have yet to do so.
What request would you make of a God-in-waiting?
The petty concerns of your existence are far beneath me, but I will listen.
Come, tell an immortal of your meagre aspirations.
Diplomacy seemed so very important when I was mortal. Now…
I presume you seek to survive this world's annihilation. Give me cause.
Whatever could one so... ephemeral possibly have to offer an eternal being?
You may aid me in the extinction of this thrice-cursed world if you so wish.
You cannot comprehend the extent of my dark power. Choose your words wisely.
We can surely find common cause in ours missions of destruction.
I have only respect for your fathomless blood-thirst, Khornate.
There is none so wretched or deluded as a mortal of Kislev!
Know this, Kislevite: your prized Motherland is built upon a lie.
What tribute does the Fly Lord intend to pay to me today?
Decay I can take or leave, but destruction? That we can agree on.
To think I once feared the Ogres. You are so small to me now.
Perhaps the ravening Ogres can be of use in my Ruinous crusade…
Subjecting the denizens of this world to unspeakable agony is a noble calling.
Perfect Prince and Daemon Prince: perhaps together we can brutalise this world?
What malevolent new scheme has the Raven concocted?
No tricks if you will, changeling: a world's extinction requires no nuance.
Grandfather Nurgle chose well.
Send the Fly Lord my respects.
This will suffice, maggotkin.
Have your senses rotted away?
Leave me be, maggotkin.
Worthless minion of pox!
Feast, brute, for you have done well.
Your tribe is spared.
A sage bargain, Ogre.
Mindless, ignorant brute!
Ogres understand nothing!
Gluttonous ignoramus!
When I am all-powerful, there will be a place for you.
Submit yourself to Chaos and perhaps you too can ascend.
Better to be by my side than in my path.
You fight on the side of true power.
We shall go forth and obliterate in Godly glory!
Once I achieve true Godhood, you may serve me.
Let us lay the world to waste for the Dark Masters!
Though my power is unfathomable, I still need minions like you.
Keep paying your respects to me and few will dare oppose you.
Ask, but remember to whom it is that you speak.
An outrage!
Deluded fool!
Begone, or know annihilation!
You insult an eternal!
You fail my Ruinous crusade.
The pleasure is all mine.
Go, sin with wild abandon.
The Dark Prince bargains wisely.
You degrade yourself, Slaaneshi
Too excessive, even for Slaanesh!
Tell your Prince this Prince refuses.
Well played, Raven-thrall.
The great game continues!
Tzeentch plays a strong hand.
The Raven overplays his hand.
I thought Tzeentch smarter than this.
Save your schemes for another.

[[img:icon_confederation]][[/img]] Join Confederation

Ask the other faction to join your [[img:icon_confederation]][[/img]]confederation. If you are strong enough and they accept your offer, their faction will be assimilated into your own; their settlements will become yours, as may some of their armies. Be aware that depending on the balance of the assets you acquire, your [[img:icon_income]][[/img]]income may be adversely affected.

[[img:icon_defensive_alliance]][[/img]]Defensive allies are sworn to protect each other if war is declared on one of them. [[img:icon_military_alliance]][[/img]]Military allies are sworn to support each other if attacked or attacking another [[img:icon_general]][[/img]]Lord or race. This is the strongest form of treaty. If the alliance is strong enough, an army can be temporarily requested from the ally.

Belligerent and warmongering, their armies reach far with little regard for defence.
Safe and secure, away from the rest of the world, this leader is mostly unmoved by the fate of others.
This leader seeks out items of incalcuable value to their faction.
Vowed to man the Great Bastion that guards Cathay, this leader will do everything that's possible to defend and recapture the fortress gates if they are under threat.
The leader of this once-proud faction has been defeated in battle; broken, he will accept any terms to stay alive.
Roused to a frenzy by the sacrifice of thousands of slaves, these Druchii seek nothing more than to slaughter Ulthuan’s denizens in the name of Khaine.
Extremely aggressive, constantly on the attack, leaving no time for the enemy to recover or to counterattack.
Deploys well-defended camps to support nearby armies with supplies and protection, threatening nearby foes.
Launches caravans to trade with distant lands and gain exotic riches.
Dragged into Khorne's realm, these once-proud warriors have no purpose save to sacrifice their lives to prove their worthiness before the Blood God.
Possesses and exploits special powers when the realm is filled with their God's corruption.
Master of magical manipulation, steals land and creates conflict and teleports forces, causing total confusion among his enemies or anyone he dislikes.
Master of magical manipulation, causing total confusion and havoc among his enemies or anyone he dislikes.
The immutable, alien logic of the Lizardmen means they will only consider strong, emotive states when engaging in diplomacy.
Shapes the realm by spreading corruption with their Heroes and armies, creating a world most suitable for their kind and much less so for others.
Through conquest and destruction, the Daemon Prince may ascend and unlock the ultimate powers of Chaos.
More concerned with maintaining borders than expanding them. Conquest is not their business.
Prefers living among the sands, rarely occupying other territories.
Destroyer of cities and empires, leaving only ruins behind.
Used to the negotiating table, this leader barely considers the other faction's strength during diplomacy.
This leader doesn't trust most Bretonnian leaders, and that has an effect on diplomatic relations.
No Druchii is ever a friend - all are potential enemies.
This leader doesn't trust most Dwarf leaders, and that has an effect on diplomatic relations.
This leader doesn't trust most Imperial leaders, and that has an effect on diplomatic relations.
The games of court always claim victims; trusting fellow Asur is foolish.
Other generations follow a false plan, they cannot be trusted.
Every Skaven - no matter their status - is a traitor waiting to act.
Hates Vampires
This leader doesn't trust most Wood Elf leaders, which has an effect on diplomatic relations.
For too long have the proud Dawi sat languishing in their holds; now they rise to clear the Great Book of Grudges and reforge the Dwarf Empire once and for all!
Like so many of his forebears, this man has fallen to the madness of the Dark Gods. He will see the world burn and remade in his masters' image.
Exploits the order and stability of any disliked faction by constant raiding, gaining more and more Devotees to create Cults and armies.
With powerful invocations, this leader can aid and strengthen Kislev and punish whoever invades it.
Prefers living in lush forests, rarely occupying other territories.
Slumbering deep within a Magical Forest, this faction is mostly unperturbed by events beyond its borders.

Gold and wealth is everything. Trading, looting, sacking, raiding, grabbing riches are the only things that may provide some fleeting satisfaction to this leader but the urge to get even more never goes away.
Greenskins love a fight, and none will miss the opportunity to be part of the largest Waaagh! the world has ever seen.
This leader will do everything they can to protect their homeland.
Their existence revolves around destroying settlements and erecting powerful Herdstones in the ruins, allowing them to extend the destructive power of the hordes.
Dwarfs do not forget grudges, indeed they harbour them, recording the slights and wrongdoings in great volumes.
Enemies will not get a foothold upon the homeland.
Unwilling to raid or sack, unless facing the most foul of foes. Then such acts become a duty.
Imperial matters and internal politics are essential for this leader, initiating diplomatic discussions with other powers are much less important.
So long are their lives, so perfect is their isolation, that the affairs of outsiders seem trivial in the extreme.
Fellow Asur are unimpeachable. For the good of the world, co-operation is the only way.
Only through Saurian unity can the Great Plan be enacted.
Can easily be swayed by Vampires during diplomacy.
Utterly subsurvient to Nakai, this faction garrisons temples within the lands he has conquered.
This leader has access to unusually aggressive tree spirits, who have had to trick Elves into fighting alongside them.
Hegemony over all lands - no treasures, no resources, no realms are out of reach of the Druchii.
Mostly defensive with a weak military, they do not compete or desire to conquer the world.
Prefers attacking enemy port settlements, even if easier targets are inland.
Subjugated by the Warriors of Chaos, this leader follows in their wake, occupying the ruins they leave behind.
Prefers striking at undefended lands whenever the opportunity arises.
A calm boat in tempestuous waters, they will only aid their closest ally, and only fight the most enduring nemesis.
Creates a series of hidden coastal outposts within foreign settlements, leeching wealth from the unwilling host.
Concocts plagues and uses Cultists to spread them among their enemies.
Concocts plagues and spreads them through battle with their enemies.
The Plaguefather infects as many living creatures as he can in order to further his research to find the perfect plague.
In war, prefers to expand slowly, consolidates before moving forward. Fiercely protects own lands, and wipes out harmful corruption.
Seeks to root out all forms harmful corruption and fights the enemy spreading it.
A ravager of lands; often sending out raiding parties to gain riches and disrupt the enemy.
What is agreed is set in stone. It is highly unlikely that this one will break a treaty or go back on an agreement.
Sees everyone and everything as an enemy, except for the chosen few.
Aims to get access to all valuable trading resources, either by diplomacy or by conquest.
This leader commands a wandering army, made up of renegades and outcasts from all factions.
This one often sends troops to capture the ruins left behind by destructive forces.
Constantly plots to break friendships and make others question their allegiance.
This leader waxes and wanes with the coming of the seasons, becoming more aggressive with every summer only to hibernate once more each winter.
Gradually seduces human and Elf factions with every friendly or hostile interaction and then uses them as puppets.
This faction holds a region of paramount importance. It cares little for what happens beyond its borders and will defend its realm to the exclusion of all else.
Willing to set aside hostilities with all Forces of Order factions in order to defeat this inhuman threat.
With the thirteenth toll of the bell, the hour of the Horned Rat has come. Driven into a frenzy, the Skaven rise to claim-conquer the surface world!
Seeks to capture slaves through raiding and battle to fuel their economy.
Trickster that turns one foe against another or teleports armies around using sorcery.
Typical verminous valour - easily dominated and prone to flee.
Aims to dominate and vassalise the enemy rather than eliminating them.
Establishes a network of warrens deep under foreign settlements, undermining enemy progress.
Defensive and capable, intending to survive whatever comes at them.
Looming over the desert, the Black Pyramid is an eternal reminder of the day Nagash plunged Nehekhara into Undeath. Now his servants shall extend his gifts to the whole world.
Instead of trying to get to the top of the food chain, this one prefers joining a worthy faction in confederation.
This one has an unusual mind, making it impossible to predict their next step.
Agreements hold little sway. This one is not to be trusted.
Shyish ravages the mortal plane. Empowered by its energy, the Vampires need little encouragement to slake their thirst for blood on a scale never seen.
This leader remembers actions of hostility for a very long time and reacts harshly if they or their friends were the target of these events.
Declares war on races they despise and brings destruction to their lands by burning cities that are uncorrupted.
This leader prefers exchanging words and wisdom over warfare with whom they deem reasonable.
Hearing the lamentations of the world's forests, the Wood Elves and their Treekin allies punish all those who have defiled nature.

Wot ya got ta offer Grom, then?
Make it good, git. Or yer goin' in da pot.
Whatever you's offerin', Grom could always just seize it.
Grom'll own everyfink soon, but sure, make an offer.
Ya gonna 'elp Grom conquer da world or wot?
Ya better bow! You's in da presence of da Goblin King!
Grom can 'ardly see you past Grom's belly.
Ya betta 'ave brought Grom somefink ta eat.
Spit it out, meatbag. Wot you finkin'?
Grom's listenin'. But Grom's also eatin', so make it quick.
It's true, it's true, yer in da presence of yer king.
Betcha didn't know Gobbos got as big as Grom.
Ain't got much time for pointy-ears.
Dis betta be good, Elf. Grom ain't keen on you gitz.
Give Grom a reason not tear yer earz off.
Pointy-eared git!
Alright, dino? Come ta offer Grom somefink good?
Scaley gits reckon dey can 'elp da Gobbo King, does dey?
Wot ya botherin' Grom for, little mouse?
You need somefink from da great 'un, ratty?
Wot's rattlin' round in dat skull, then?
Didn’t realise you boney gitz could talk. Ain't got no tongues.
Give Grom somefink decent or scarper back ta ya trees.
Talk fast or you're supper, pointy-ears.
What lies does your shining helm conceal this time?
You humans speak of honour, yet act only in treachery.
I see your brutish nature for what it is. Begone!
There can be no safety while Chaos still stalks this world.
What vile missive do you bring from the depths, fiend?
Give me one reason not to curtail your unnatural Unlife.
Twisted mirror of all that is just! You dare come to me?
Druchii swine! Have you come to offer your surrender?
Why would Tor Yvresse ever trust you, human?
You dare waste the grim Warden's time, human filth?
You are a threat to Yvresse. In my father's name, you must die!
The Waystones cannot be safe until your head leaves your shoulders.
I would see you cold and dead. It is my purpose!
The Fangsword hungers to meet your neck.
Wretch! For Ulthuan to survive, you must meet your end!
Negotiation with such as you betrays my vow.
Your dare beg time from he who would see you eviscerated?
You! I will not rest 'til all who threaten Yvresse are buried!
You dare beg favour from the grim Warden?
To even acknowledge you is far more than you deserve.
All your foul kind must die. This is my vow. My duty!
I will take your head, Greenskin. If not today, then soon.
Hated monster! In my father's name, I will hunt you down!
Greenskin filth! I'll slay you even if it costs me my soul!
Traitor! There is no lower form of life than you!
You betrayed the vow. Ulthuan weeps for your treachery.
Your bloodless heart knows no honour, reptile.
You wrong the Asur then dare beg favour, Cold One?
Know your place, vermin, or I will drive you back to it.
Pestilent beast! Your very presence is abhorrent.
I see there is no brain in that cruel and empty skull.
Speak quickly, or I will return you to dust, ghoul.
You will return to your trees if you value your life.
The Fey folk have betrayed the Asur for the last time.
Does your famed nobility extend to aiding the Asur?
Honour is a virtue I respect, human. I will listen.
How can Ulthuan ever trust your murderous kind?
Can you form words from minds clouded by hatred?
What have you dragged yourself from the deep to tell me?
I will tolerate your insult against life itself if it furthers my vow.
I tolerate you only because it aids Yvresse, Druchii.
You are aberrant, but perhaps you can be useful.
You have the Warden's ear, human. Do not squander this opportunity.
Ask no favours of Ulthuan, human. Ask only how you can help.
I will consider any suggestion that aids Tor Yvresse.
Be sure you do not waste my time.
Speak quickly, for I must not be distracted from my vow.
Have you come to help me avenge my father? If not, leave.
Do not expect pleasantries. The defence of Yvresse is all that matters.
Speak plainly, and only of matters of business.
What is it? I am a Warden, not a low-born tradesman.
State your case quickly, for countless Asur lives depend upon me.
Let your words be true, and your time here brief.
I will hear you. I promise no more than that.
You are a scourge I am sworn to eliminate.
You think your words can deter me from annihilating all your kind?
Green filth! You have mere moments to beg my mercy!
Your kind stole my father from me. Why should I heed you?
May we both serve Ulthuan unto our deaths.
I trust that you too are pledged to safeguard the Waystones?
Rare is it I encounter a soul as cold as mine own.
What care the Asur for the affairs of reptiles?
What is it you seek, rat?
Tell me - how can vermin help safeguard my homeland?
Why are you here, skeleton?
Present your case, corpse. How will you aid Ulthuan?
What lures you from your forested hiding place?
Swear that the Asrai finally stand with the Asur, or begone.
Bretonnia's Knights have tested my patience for the last time!
Human scum! Outrageous that you demand my time!
You think only of violence. This I will gladly grant you.
Your mind is clouded by darkness. My Star Lance will liberate you.
Return to your grave, or shall I send you there myself.
If only you had stayed drowned, fiend!
Treachery is ingrained in Druchii nature. It will be punished.
You are a dark mirror of Ulthuan's splendour. One I will shatter.
Great Imrik will crush your little empire, of this you can be sure.
Have you come to speak your last words, human?
All should pity you, for you have incited the fury of the Dragons.
There is a place for you on the tip of my Star Lance.
Know this: I will not remember you once I have slain you.
Do you truly believe you can avert Caledor's vengeance with words?
Face me on the battlefield, if you have the courage!
You will pay for your follies. The Prince of Dragons swears it!
I will see you burn for your transgressions against Caledor!
Your attempts to unseat me are comical. Perhaps you now realise this?
Beg me for mercy and I will consider a swift death for you.
I should hurl you into the fires of Vaul's Anvil, wretch!
The parasite speaks! I think I shall kill it.
This world will be far better without you in it, green horror!
Betrayer! You are the shame of Ulthuan!
There is no greater sin than for lesser Asur to turn upon Caledor.
Beg the Master of Dragons for your life, little lizard.
I'll adorn my cloak with your scales, monster!
I could crush you beneath my majestic heel, vermin.
Vile creature! I'll have a rug made out of you.
I will pay no heed to your hollow words, dead-thing.
There's no glory in slaying the already dead, but it must be done.
Return to your precious trees, or I'll fell you myself.
The Asrai are false Elves. They must be removed from the bloodline.
You are Knights in name, perhaps, but I rule the battlefield.
I'll admit, I find Bretonnia more tolerable than other humans.
Snarl away, brute, and I will seek to make sense of it.
I did not know your kind was capable of conversation.
Explain your presence, lifeless one.
What dark need drags you from the depths?
A Druchii seeking Ulthuani favour? 'Tis a day of madness.
Come to make amends for generations of treachery, have you?
Ah, a human. Your squat race is most amusing.
What brings your squalid little empire into the presence of greatness?
You are privileged indeed to have the ear of Prince Imrik.
Relish this chance to look upon your better.
The power and the glory of Caledor bids you welcome.
Well, what is it? Do not squander the Dragon Prince's time.
A moment can be spared, but no more.
You may gaze upon my glory.
To feel awe is only natural in the presence of the Dragon Prince.
What have I done to deserve discourse with one so lowly?
I was born to commune with Dragons, not lesser beings!
I tire of you already.
Why do I find myself conversing with a half-wit beast?
Ugh, must I really negotiate with a Greenskin, of all things?
Like all other Ulthuani, you should bow before Caledor.
I am your brother, but do not forget I am also your better.
I of all people know to respect those of reptilian origin.
Explain your alien needs. Caledor will at least listen.
Squeak whatever it is you mean to squeak, rat.
Speak quickly, rodent, for my royal nose cannot abide your stench.
What do you need, dead-thing?
May your request be less unnatural than your form.
Leaving your precious trees for a change, are you?
Have you Asrai realised that you are nothing without Ulthuan?
Your stupid man-things hide in tin suit-suits? It not protect from my warbeasts!
Will chop-slice, sew-stitch, make-turn man-thing into Throtling!
Me will put thing's brain-mind in Rat Ogre! Have done this before...
Chaos thing block-block great Moulder experiments! Must die-die!
Hated dead-thing! Me seize-take unliving organ parts!
How drowned flesh taste? Not important, me eat-gnaw anyway.
No Elf-things leave Hell Pit the same as they arrive! You no different!
Nasty Elf-thing too thin! Need-eat hundreds, NEVER ENOUGH!
Come out to play, nasty no-fur! Come be food-food for me!
Man-thing flesh-meat taste best raw-raw! You die-die screaming!
Me bite-chew! Will eat-gorge! Fool-thing die-die!
Bad thing! Will chop-slice! Put brain-brain in abomination!
Rah! Fool-fool! Me eat flesh-meat, gnaw-chew glistening bones!
Bad things still make good food!
Will kill-kill, but keep… eyes. Maybe brain. Eat rest.
Throw enemy-thing into Hell Pit! Graft-change you to Throtling…
ME HUNGRY! YOU-THING MEAT-FLESH! EAT YOU-THING!
Bad-thing fit-good only for part-parts! CHOP SLICE NOW-NOW!
ME EAT THING'S HEAD! Graft-sew rest onto warbeasts, yes?
Fool-fool brings self to be eaten, yes? Wants to be lunch-meal?
Me crush-smash green-things, then eat pulpy gore-jam!
Snarling, stupid brute-beast! Turn you into Moulder warbeast!
Me pick teeth-fangs with thing's ear-points!
Spindly snack-snack! Me will beat-hurt, kill-kill, then eat whatever left!
Will rip-tear scales away and gnaw-bite stringy meat-flesh below!
Cold-blood insult Moulder! Me slice-cut into scaly strip-strips!
Enemy rat-rat! Will stitch-sew nasty paws to mouth-mouth!
Me hate bad clan-clan! Feed all to Brood Horrors, yes?
Me make nasty bone-things dead-dead twice, yes?
Moulder Rat Ogres pound-smash bones to dust-dust!
Me will throw tricksy tree-thing into Hell Pit, slice-dice into mewling Throtling!
Elf-thing return to tree-trees or be eaten alive! Only warning, yes?
Pah! No-furs no good for experiments! All look same-same!
Man-things bring food-food? ME HUNGRY!
So big-strong! So strange-strange! Make good warbeast…
Weird-thing remind me of strangest, nastiest experiments.
Dead-things drink blood-blood? Hmm, maybe dead-things smart-smart!
Sea-thing not steal-take from Moulder Clan, yes?
Give me just one ear? Little snack-snack, hmm?
Little Elf-thing! What need from Hell Pit lord-boss?
So hungry! No-fur flesh so tasty… But no, no, me talk-talk.
Me eat many-many man-things before. Why not this one? Help experiments?
Thing, assist me now! Or will take thing's brain, put in Rat Ogre, yes?
Speak quick-fast! Too slow and you be next meal-food!
Hurrrrrr… Good organs. Nice part-parts! Maybe I put in warbeast?
MEAT-FLESH! GET IN MY GUT-GUT! Hhhn. Hhhn. Sorry-sorry. Am so hungry…
Speak too slow! I poke-stab thing's brain and make talk-speak quicker!
Thing will help with experiments, yes? Make many many strange-strong things.
What want? Bring good organ-parts for me, hmm?
Does it have food-food? Give to me now! I HUNGER!
Bring me meat-flesh or go-go! MUST EAT NOW!
Talk fast-fast! Am so hungry, so hungry. Cannot focus…
Bleh! Green meat no taste good-good. Why here-place?
Can make green-thing bigger, yes! Put brain in Rat Ogre, yes?
What Elf-thing want? Does it bring food-meal?
Hmm. This one thin-thin. Not enough flesh-meat!
Hoo, dino-things. Want use part-parts! But will talk-talk.
Lizard-things too chewy to eat. We scheme-plan instead, yes?
Want clan work together? Maybe. Only if me in charge though.
Me promise not to eat-munch other rat-rats. If obey me, hmm?
How strange bone-thing walk-move? Me want know-see!
Bone-thing has brain in skull bone? Me must look!
Why thing leave tree-trees? Why bother me, hmm?
I HUNGER! Elf-thing not need both ears, maybe?
You will always be undesired neighbours.
Your next words may be your last, man.
Violence begets violence, Chaos-child.
Leave before I show you true fear!
I will grant death to the Undying!
You transgress against the forest, you transgress against life itself!
My hand-maidens will rip the flesh from you, Elf.
All Elven-kind are monstrous. You... are somehow worse.
The only good man is a dying, screaming one!
Those who anger the forest spirits must die, man.
I will see this land soaked in your blood!
I care only for vengeance!
Speak, scum!
You will be ruined. You will be destroyed.
I can think of no reason to spare you.
Let me guide you to your grave!
I dream of your torn and bloodied carcass!
Have you come to grant me vengeance upon you?
You wish ill upon the forest spirits. You will die.
I desire your death, and vengeance for my sisters!
I will repay your savagery in kind, animal!
You are nothing more than a beast to be slain!
Your betrayal is your end, Asur scum!
Have you come to accept your penance?
Cold bloods are as despicable as any other mortal.
Begone, lest I prise every last scale slowly from you.
All vermin warrant destruction!
Return to your stinking sewers, loathsome rat!
I will bury you for your transgressions, bone demon!
I would sooner reduce your bones to dust than converse.
You have forsaken the forest!
Soon you will taste the vengeance of my fallen sisters.
Your kind has been known to ally with loathsome Elves... tread carefully!
Do you intend to trespass in the forests once more?
I see only violence in you.
You are a threat, saturated in malice.
What promises spill forth from your unnatural tongue?
Why would I align myself with death?
I despise Elves, but at least your breed displays its malice openly.
What fresh barbarity do you Elves intend for the glades?
What dare you ask of Drycha, mortal?
What would you ruin next, man?
I care not for your needs.
Swear to me that you have never claimed a Dryad life.
I speak for the Tree of Woe.
Betray me and I will fertilise the earth with your blood.
My rage is quelled… for now.
Why should I spare you?
It pains me to converse with another.
My tolerance for conversation is low.
For your own sake, pray that what you have to say is of worth.
I distrust all other beings.
You are a higher form of life than Elves, at least.
Tame your aggression and speak clearly.
Elves! Despised betrayers!
You… kin to those who despoiled the forest.
Why do jungle beasts disturb the forest spirits?
We are both ancients, but there any kinship ends.
Snickering vermin… what would you ask of the forest spirits?
Pah! Rodents! Speak, then…
What dark force animates these dry bones?
Speak, dead spirits! Drycha will listen.
Despicable Elf! Why should I let you live?
Many of my sisters have perished. Why do you deserve mercy?
Bretonnia has betrayed us.\\n\\nI always told you we should not trust our 'neighbours', sister.
You are a disgrace to your vaunted Lady.\\n\\nIndeed, you betray her noble values.
Animal! I should run you through!\\n\\nQuite. The time for mercy has passed.
Despoiler! Ruiner! Scourge!\\n\\nThat's more like it, Naestra.
The dead should stay dead!\\n\\nYou are an affront to nature's harmony.
We have no reason to trust you.\\n\\nThey desire only blood, sister!
We have no cause to converse with Naggaroth.\\n\\nNever trust a Druchii.
I trust our ancient kin come to beg for mercy.\\n\\nAnd I see no reason to grant it.
You are consumed by greed, man.\\n\\nWhy did it take you this long to realise, Naestra?
Never trust a man.\\n\\nAlas, this wretch proved you correct, Arahan.
You have proven yourself an enemy of the forest.\\n\\nIn other words, you're dead.
We should kill them now, Naestra.\\n\\nOnly when no other option remains.
With regret, I must declare you our enemy.\\n\\nFinally, my sister sees sense.
Your threat must be ended.\\n\\nIn Ariel's name.
If only we'd hunted you down long ago.\\n\\nYour bloodthirst was warranted for once, sister.
Scum! I will put you in the ground!\\n\\nIt is true. There is no other way.
You have caused untold harm.\\n\\nDon't think you can make up for it.
They've come to beg for mercy, Naestra.\\n\\nI am hesitant to grant it, Arahan.
We grant you one last audience. Squander it and doom will follow.
She is dawn and I am dusk. Either can unmake you in an instant.
Athel Loren's patience with the murderous Greenskins is exhausted.
To meet with monsters is folly!\\n\\nI concur that there is scant hope of reason, sister.
Go back to your ivory tower, preening quisling.\\n\\nI must concur.
Ulthuan brings shame upon Elven kind.\\n\\nThat's putting it lightly.
Come to offer me your scaled hide?\\n\\nIndeed, our patience is at an end.
Speak quickly, Cold One, for trust ebbs by the moment.\\n\\nYour threats need not be so veiled, sister.
Filthy little animal!\\n\\nIndeed, the time for tolerance has passed.
You must atone for your acts of destruction, Skaven.\\n\\nThey lack the wit, Naestra.
You have one last chance to escape extinction, little mouse.\\n\\nShow no mercy, sister!
Face my arrows, vile ratling!\\n\\nMy sister's aggression is, for once, warranted.
You must make amends, ghoul…\\n\\n...else I will return you to your dusty tomb.
You are not of nature.\\n\\nYou cannot be trusted.
Ariel will not forgive your betrayal.
Filthy traitor!\\n\\nThe forest does not forgive.
Athel Loren is always pleased to meet with its neighbours.\\n\\nSo long as they behave.
So the 'Lady' needs another favour?\\n\\nPoliteness is paramount, sister.
It is… difficult to trust your kind.\\n\\nIn other words, watch your step, monster.
Even Chaos can attain harmony, if it desires.\\n\\nYou are deluded, Naestra.
Welcome, creature of twilight.\\n\\nDon't stare at my throat like that.
Why would we ever work with corpses?\\n\\nAll help should be valued, sister.
Ariel bids greeting to our ancient kin.\\n\\nThey are nothing like us, Naestra!
You Druchii are like spoiled children.\\n\\nThere is no call for insults, sister.
Men destroy everything they touch!\\n\\nNot all Men are the same, Arahan.
What do the realms of men ask of Ariel?\\n\\nWe keep the Empire out for good reason, Naestra.
We grant you an audience.\\n\\nSo don't waste our time.
Should we kill them, sister?\\n\\nStay your blade, I sense no malice in them.
Athel Loren bids you greetings.\\n\\nDon't mistake my sister's pretty words for weakness.
On behalf of the Mage Queen, you are welcome.
Ariel has been watching you for some time.
Spit it out, then. I've got prey to hunt.\\n\\nHear them out, Arahan.
We speak as one, and the forest speaks through us.
Speak quickly!\\n\\nFear not, we will listen carefully.
You meet with the emmisaries of a demi-god…\\n\\n…who won't hesitate to kill in her name.
Do we have to talk to them, Naestra?\\n\\nIt is but a moment of your time, Arahan.
Can you even speak, beast?\\n\\nPetty insults are beneath you, Arahan.
Athel Loren will hear the Greenskins.\\n\\nSister, this is madness!
I have no patience for the fancy folk of Ulthuan.\\n\\nThey are still our kin, sister.
What brings the uppity Asur down from their gilded towers?\\n\\nShow tolerance, Arahan.
Let the forest and the jungle seek alignment.\\n\\nYou are so credulous, sister.
What fine prey you'd make, lizard.\\n\\nThe Cold Ones deserve our respect, Arahan.
We have to talk to rats now?\\n\\nLife is life, Arahan.
Skaven are welcome, so long as they do not threaten the forest.\\n\\nHighly unlikely, sister.
Vermin are nature's only mistake.\\n\\nNature is never wrong, sister - show kindness.
Peace and harmony to you, creature of the underground.\\n\\nYou cannot be serious, Naestra.
Behave, bone-lord, else you'll die twice.\\n\\nThreats run counter to diplomacy, sister.
You are unnatural indeed, but Athel Loren will hear you.\\n\\nThis isn't right, Naestra!
We are all Ariel's children.\\n\\nSome more so than others.\\n\\nHush, sister.
You know who we are?\\n\\nThey know, sister. Our kin will co-operate.
Your words are weak as your flesh.
Your quest ends in a cage.
Child of an Ungor! I kill you!
You dare challenge Taurox, worm?
Dark Masters demand your blood!
You fail Dark Masters! Taurox is true champion of Chaos!
Go back to your ships or feel wrath of Bloodbeast!
No more talk! No more lies! Fight!
Confuse Taurox! No more talk!
I eat Elf flesh!
Your walls not save you from Taurox.
Don't test Taurox, puny human!
Taurox tear off your head!
You want talk? Taurox want fight!
These words will be your last.
Taurox no like you!
Rune-tortured axes will taste your flesh!
You not part of Taurox's plan!
I will crush you!
I am the Slaughterhorn!
Taurox biggest! Taurox strongest! Fight me!
You want fight? You get fight!
Gutless Elf! Taurox hates fancy words!
I eat Elf flesh!
Coldskin has failed. Chaos will reign!
Gut you! Kill your masters! Burn your temples!
Taurox enjoy killing you.
Hated coldskin. Taurox crush!
I tear off head! I bathe in blood! I end your tribe!
You make the Dark Lords angry!
Soak the ground in rat-blood!
Are you afraid? You should be!
Taurox crush living, crush dead, crush everything!
Crush you to dust, bone-thing!
Taurox defile your sacred groves. Taurox crush puny Elves!
I eat Elf flesh!
You brave, to come here alone...
Taurox has no time for humans!
You bring tribute for Taurox?
You have words for Taurox, traitor?
The Dark Lords sent you?
Together we destroy the world!
Dead thing, speak quickly!
Betray the brayherd, and you will suffer.
What you want, puny Darkling?
Bring slaves. Taurox hungry!
Not so brave outside your walls, human.
Your weak gods will be destroyed!
Speak or die.
You talk with Slaughterhorn now.
Speak!
You have words?
I am strong, you are weak!
Talk is for the weak.
Why you here?
You seek mighty Taurox?
You respect strength. I am strongest.
Speak!
Your unfilthy presence displeases Taurox.
Your fancy words cannot save you.
Lizardman blood is ice. Taurox blood is fire!
Enemy of the Dark Ones…
The old gods will not save you from Taurox.
Dark Masters tell Taurox kill you. Convince me or die.
Human? You smell like Ungor.
Now you feast with herd.
I smell your musk of fear.
You come to surrender?
Talk quick, or I smash your bones.
Give me your words, dead thing.
Puny Elf, bring your words to Taurox.
Forest belongs to Taurox.
You've got the whiff of the Elves about you, manling.
Go on then, speak your words, Umgi…
Dumal! Deliver your message, and get out of my sight!
I care not for the whims of your Dark Gods.
I'm not one for ships, but I'll see my ironclads sink your lot!
Uzkular, I want nothing to do with your vile schemes!
Lowest among the Elgi, leave here while you still can.
Avaunt! Arroint! Go home! Naf Off!
You know the problem with your kind? Too much dibnin.
You've picked a bad time to interrupt me, Umgi… speak quickly.
You interrupt my work. Your first mistake.
I have little patience, so this better be important.
By Klad Brakak! I should slay you where you stand!
Only vengeance will make me happy! Is that what you offer?
Talk if you must, it won't change your fate!
I don't have time for words, the Dawi need me.
You're not welcome, so I won't pretend otherwise.
The runes of Wrath and Ruin strike for you!
By the ancestors, you've got some gall coming here.
The next time you see Klad Brakak, it'll be your doom.
Klad Brakak needs more testing. Give me cause, Greenskin!
My weapon shops work tirelessly. You lot keep me in business.
As far as I'm concerned, the War of Vengeance never ended…
Inconstant, intolerable! Never trust an Elf!
Out of respect for the elders, I'll let you walk out of here.
The Dwarfs are not pawns in the games of your masters.
Even Kraggi could deal with you. Maybe I'll let him.
Why are you here, stinkin' up my forge?
How dare you darken my hall, Uzkular!
I have nothing for the Undead. Leave, now!
Your words are twisted like the boughs of your precious trees.
I'll make your forests into fuel for my forge!
We stand united in honour, men of Bretonnia.
Greetings, knight. What can the Master of Runes do for you?
I will listen, spawn, but don't expect me to favour your vile kind.
Thungni's hammer! You've got some nerve coming here.
Plunderers and thieves… You bring Dark Magic to my hold.
Speak, Zangunaz, then I will decide if you keep your head.
I'm not wasting good ale on your treacherous ilk.
Very fine words, but you'd put a dagger in my back.
What brings you here, manling?
Greetings, son of Sigmar.
What brings you to my mighty forge?
Greetings… what do you require of Karak Azul?
You seek the favour of Iron Peak? I'm listening…
Who? Make it snappy, I've got work to do.
Can't you see I'm busy? The runes wait for no one.
What brings you to the halls of my ancestors?
First we drink, then we talk.
In these dark times, perhaps we should stand together.
Casting the runes is thirsty work. Let's drink and talk!
Our bargain will be inscribed in Klinkarhun. Binding. Enduring.
You catch me in good humour, Greenskin, I'll hear your proposal.
I'm surprised you can string two words together, Greenskin.
Have you come to atone for your transgressions against the Dawi?
I can't trust someone who's never had dirt on 'em.
I respect the ancient knowledge and wisdom of your masters. Speak.
Those who respect the old ways are welcome in my hall.
Many are the grudges against your kind.
I've not lived all these centuries to bandy words with vermin.
The Uzkular is it? Go on then, say your piece.
You reflect the fate of all who tread dark paths
You're a long way from your forest, Elgi.
This had better be good. Your magic won't protect you here.
A quest? You know nothing of quests, warmblood. You insult me.
Your armour will not protect you. Oxylotl knows every weakness.
Liars! Despoilers! Base creatures! The time of beasts is over!
Your presence here is an affront to Sotek.
Run while you can, Cloven One! The hunt begins now!
I swear by Sotek, no child of Chaos will survive this day!
In the name of Pocaxalan, I will have vengeance on your kind.
I will hunt you and your kind to the ends of the world.
You bring more lies from across the Great Pond?
There shall never be agreement with the thieves of the Great Pond!
Dark hearts, dark minds, dark Elf-things!
You have not yet begun to learn of sacrifice and pain!
A sacrifice of you warmbloods will do just fine.

Can you be civil long enough to hear my proposal, Dwarf?
Greetings, men of the Empire! I have matters I wish to discuss.
I wish to make you an offer, son of Sigmar.
By Kurnous! The smell! I have something to offer you, Greenskin.
I have matters of paramount… I forgot who I was talking to. I have something for you.
The gods will never approve, but I have a proposal for you, traitor!
Even traitors can have their uses. We should talk.
I have a proposal to discuss with you.
You will find what I have to say very interesting, Vampire.
The bounty of Athel Loren is laid before you.
Please accept this generous gift from the Lords and Ladies of Athel Loren.
I have come to offer you a gift from the Deepwood.
We offer you the might of Athel Loren, do you accept this rare and generous offer?
The might of the Asrai is ready to stand with you!
We will stand with you against your foe!
The forest cries out in pain! Let there be peace.
Now is the time for peace, surely you can see that?
Enough lives have been lost. We offer you peace.
We have enough horns to adorn our walls now, let there be peace.
Your lust for blood has grown wearisome. We are ready for peace.
Well Bretonnian, are you ready for peace?
We are willing to let you live the remainder of your short life in peace. What say you?
For the good of the Asrai I call for peace, servant of Chaos.
Tell your Dark Gods we are ready for peace.
How would you like to put down your axe and return to your gold?
Let us have peace, while you still have your beard!
It is time for us to tend the forest, we weary of your warmongering.
Enough is enough, human!
The stench of your vile armies is too much, we are ready for peace.
You may delight in war and death, but we do not! Let there be peace.
Peace, brother! Enough Elves have suffered for your vanity.
Enough Asrai blood has been spilt, let us look to peace.
We no longer have time to swat at waves of the Undead, we call for peace.
We must turn from death and concentrate on life.
The Elves of Athel Loren will never join forces with you!
The Deepwood provides all we need, we have no use for you.
No, I think not.
The Asrai are slow to forget a slight…
Our skalds will sing of your cowardice for years to come!
You desire peace? The Deepwood does not!
Twisted monsters of Chaos, I reject your offer of 'peace'.
We do not make peace with Beasts!
The weakness of men disgusts me. There will be no peace!
No Bretonnian, your people will not know peace!
There can be no peace until Chaos has been eradicated!
When we have wiped every trace of your taint from this world, then there will be peace!
You stunted fool! There can never be peace between Elf and Dwarf!
There will be no peace until you have paid for the hurts you have caused Athel Loren!
You weary of war human? Well, we do not!
There can be no peace with the Empire!
There can never be peace between us, Greenskin!
Defiler of all that is good and true, I reject your offer of 'peace'.
Your traitorous corpse will never know the peace of the Deepwood!
We do not make peace with traitors!
Our dead would never rest easy if we made peace with you!
There will be no peace for you, Undead monstrosity!
Never! Get out, you twisted creature!
You will never defile the woods of Athel Loren, no!
Just looking upon you has made me unwell, leave.
We will not aid you in your quest for blood and vengeance!
Foolish beast, not even a Dwarf would agree to these terms.
I cannot agree to this, Beastman.
No songs will be sung of your diplomatic skill. I reject your proposal!
If you wield a sword as well as you do words, Bretonnia is doomed!
We have no time for the petty woes of Bretonnia.
Your woes are your own, Bretonnian.
We cannot come to the aid of the knights of Bretonnia.
We were the obvious choice, but we cannot help you, Bretonnian.
Never! I see Rhana Dandra in your hateful eyes, servant of Chaos!
Leave while you still can, servant of Chaos! Our talks have come to nothing!
You seek the destruction of all, why would we aid you in this?!
We will never serve the dark will of your masters!
There is no room in the Deepwood for Chaos!
We will never bow to the dark desires of Chaos!
I will tear your beard off with my bare hands!
Foolish dwarf! Our hatred for your race can never be put aside!
The Elves of Athel Loren want nothing from your kind, Dwarf!
This greed is a mark of your race, but it is no excuse!
Dwarfs and Elves are ancient enemies, we cannot accept.
It will take more than that to convince me to agree with a Dwarf.
No, and may the taint of Chaos spread across your lands for asking!
By the horns of Kurnous! You have gone too far, little mayfly!
You ask too much, I will put it down to the folly of youth.
You are too hasty, little mayfly. No.
The Empire expects too much, we cannot.
Our talks have come to naught, son of Sigmar.
The halls of Athel Loren would ring with laughter if I even suggested this!
You simple creature, no.
I grow weary of these talks. The answer is no.
I'm feeling quite unwell. Leave now, we will have no agreement this day.
You delight in death and destruction. We will never come to an agreement!
Kurnous give me strength! Your stupidity knows no bounds!
Morghur's blood! You dare to come here and ask this?!
Khaine strike you down for your impudence!
You are no longer Asrai, get out!
Khaine take you and your request, traitor!
We will not see the people of Athel Loren divided for your selfish desires.
These terms are disagreeable.
Leave, before I call the Dryads!
These terms are as rotten as your heart! Get out!
The Elves of Athel Loren are not fools, we will never agree to this!
Athel Loren will not profit from this agreement.
You may want to rethink your offer.
This offer is not acceptable.
No, I cannot accept this offer.
I must reject this proposal.
I cannot accept these terms.
We want none of your 'eternal life', I have seen the price you pay!
Your vile sickness shall never hold sway in Athel Loren!
The time for talking is at an end, leave.
Return to the darkness and admit your failure.
We cannot agree to these ghoulish terms.
The Von Carsteins have nothing to offer the Elves of Athel Loren.
The power of Athel Loren rises against you, we are at war!
Kurnous has sounded his horn and we are happy to heed its call!
Sound the war horns!
Your bloody rampage ends now, Beastmen!
We are at war! Beasts of Chaos!
Tremble mortal, for you will face the full might of Athel Loren!
Your weak people will suffer for your mistakes, it is war!
We will destroy you, servants of Chaos!
The Asrai will know no rest until Chaos is driven from our lands!
You will pay for the hurt you have caused Athel Loren! To war!
Let there be war! I will enjoy killing each and every one of your stunted kind!
Today the Empire will know fear! We are at war!
We will wipe out your little Empire, once and for all!
You have burnt your last blade of grass, now you die!
We are at war! I will no longer have to suffer your stench!
We are brothers no more!
Prepare for war, traitorous scum!
We will wipe out your dark taint once and for all!
Your corpse army will be engulfed by the flames of war!
Cease your braying! What could you possibly offer the Asrai?!
Twisted beast of Chaos! What do you want?
The creatures of Chaos will find scant welcome in Athel Loren.
Beastman, any humanity you once possessed is long dead.
Beasts of Chaos, how came you to Athel Loren?
What do you seek from the Asrai, Beastmen?
Your 'chivalry' is a mantle, worn to hide the emptiness within your soul.
No songs will be sung of your valour! Your name will be lost in the mists of time!
Your pomp and ceremony fails to impress me, Bretonnian.
Many a Bretonnian knight has found himself lost in the dark pathways of Athel Loren.
I have heard much of Bretonnian knights and their 'chivalry'.
Hail men of Bretonnia! What word from the Lady?
The Asrai do not bandy words with the servants of Chaos!
Your vile taint shall spread no further, Dark Lords of Chaos!
The servants of Chaos will find no welcome in the halls of Athel Loren!
You are but a vassal of the Dark Lords of Chaos. Speak, loathsome vassal.
Can the servants of Chaos ever be loyal friends?
Those you serve have caused untold misery to our Lady, did you expect a welcome?
You dare trample the earth of Athel Loren?! The forest does not welcome your kind!
I should have your beard for entering our halls uninvited!
Return to your cold stone halls, Mountain Dweller. There is nothing for you here.
I think it unlikely that we will agree on anything, but please, do try.
Have you no gold to polish or jewels to count? Very well, speak.
What would you have of the Lord and Lady of Athel Loren, Dwarf?
Your reach exceeds your grasp, son of Sigmar. Leave, while you still can.
Long have my people hunted yours for sport. Do you imagine us equals!?
Your short life is as the blinking of an eye to me. Think on that.
Speak briefly, I can see your life draining away before my very eyes.
Men of the Empire, why do you seek the halls of Athel Loren?
How can we help the devout men of the Empire?
Your coming is ill starred. Speak briefly, then remove your vile taint from the hallowed halls of Athel Loren.
Consider yourself lucky that we didn't send you to parley with the Dryads!
Not since the coming of Morghur has Athel Loren been so tainted!
This is Athel Loren, home of the Oak of Ages and the Asrai.
The Deepwood protects its sons and daughters. Tread carefully...
We will see our homeland persist through all the coming ages of the world.
The woods of Athel Loren welcome you. Deliver your message.
Welcome to the halls of Athel Loren! What do you want?
You have been granted access to the halls of Athel Loren.
Burn so much as a blade of grass and I will see your hovels raised to the ground!
This will end in fire and blood, for that is all that you Greenskins know!

You inconstant worm! You shall suffer!

What business do the Undead have here?
The King in the Woods does not treat with beasts!
Twisted creatures of Chaos! Speak quickly, before I unleash my hounds!
What has driven you to darken my door? Make it brief foul creature.
What brings the Beastmen to the Deepwood? We are not friends.
Beastmen! What brings you here with your dark tongue?
There is a low cunning glinting in those red eyes. What do you seek?
Gilles le Breton dogs your steps Bretonnian, can you not see him?
The Lady must weep to see her people brought so low. What do you want from us?
The friendship of our great ladies has bought you passage to Athel Loren, nothing more.
Why do you cling to the deeds of long dead men, Bretonnian?
My lady welcomes the brave knights of Bretonnia to our halls! What do you wish to discuss?
I am drawn to the nobility of your cause, Bretonnian.
Your twisted Gods have no power here!
Your demented thoughts flit like flies upon a corpse. Gather them and speak quickly.
You have been permitted to enter Athel Loren, whether you will leave is another matter entirely...
You are a puppet to the twisted desires of Chaos! What does your infernal master want?
How you made it across our borders is a mystery to me. Speak.
I see the eyes of your masters peering forth from your empty mind... How queer…
How dare you enter the hallowed halls of Athel Loren, Mountain Dweller?!
Does your gold comfort you in the still watches of the night?
You do well to kneel before me... oh, I thought those were your knees. An easy mistake to make.
Scamper back to your empty halls, Dwarf.
Long have our races fought in the battle against the darkness.
Set aside your Book of Grudges for a moment, Dwarf.
Your time on this world is short, you would be unwise to waste it here!
Your forebears weep tears of blood in their eternal halls, such is their disappointment!
What word from the Emperor?
Sigmar's 'wrath' is of little consequence to me, mortal.
Welcome, son of mighty Sigmar. What would you have of the King in the Woods?
Greetings, short-lifer. I will be brief.
If I had my way, the Wild Hunt would trample you into the earth!
Were it not for the kind heart of The Lady Ariel, you would already be dead!
Your words and heart are hollow. My hounds will gorge themselves upon your flesh!
You stand before the King in the Woods. Speak and I shall consider your request.
You have been granted access to my halls. Don't make me regret my act of kindness.
My lady informs me that I must listen to you.
I welcome you to the King's Glade. Sit, we have much to discuss.
The mighty deepwood welcomes you beneath its bower.
Come, The beauty of Athel Loren is seldom seen by outsiders.
Take your hulking carcass beyond our Waystones and never darken this forest again!
You defilers of all that is good and true, what could you possibly want of the King in the Woods?!
Those who delight in destruction reap what they sow.
Very well, poison my halls with your words.
Speak slowly, your drivel is incomprehensible to me.
It spews forth sounds but I fail to understand it!
You dare to come before your true king?!
Your corpse will be left beyond the Waystones for Slaanesh!
In my halls, the words of the faithless seldom make it past their lips.
Speak your lies and be gone from Athel Loren!
A traitor stands before me. Speak, traitor.
You may speak your honeyed words but I will see the lie concealed within.
Undead cretin! Your witch-scent is anathema to the forest and all those who serve its will!
Your presence in our halls is like the coming of a great plague!
You think yourselves 'immortal'? You stand before a god in mortal form, filth!
You're awfully pale, perhaps a walk in the sun would do you some good?
A 'pleasure'. What do the denizens of Sylvania seek in Athel Loren?
The Von Carsteins have grown great indeed if they think to treat with me.
Creature of Chaos, your end draws near!
I will hang your carcass as a warning to others!
You are far from welcome here.
Leave and never darken this forest again.
Deliver your message and be gone!
Child of Chaos, what brings you here?
Your body will never be found, Bretonnian!
Your Lady has no power here.
I care little for the desires of men.
Your mortal ambitions are pointless.
What do the men of Bretonnia seek?
Welcome, Bretonnian mayfly.
You poison the forest with your taint, servant of Chaos!
Your will is weak, puppet of Chaos!
No good can come from you.
Your masters will devour your soul.
I have seen your like before…
What do your masters want?
Axe-wielding filth!
Greed taints the minds of all Dwarfs!
Speak, Dwarf.
Lay down your axe and we will speak.
What you have to say may seem important to you, Dwarf.
What treasure do you seek?
I will end your short life, Son of Sigmar!
Your blood will nourish the Deepwood, child of the Empire!
The desires of men are folly.
Little mayfly, what do you want?
The forest welcomes the men of the Empire.
What can you hope to achieve during your short life?
The Deepwood does not welcome outsiders!
The forest will have its vengeance!
Athel Loren does not welcome strangers.
Why have you come here?
Beware stranger, Athel Loren is treacherous.
The Asrai grant you passage, but you are not welcome here!
Behold, the ancient forest of Athel Loren!
Welcome, how can I help you?
Greetings, Athel Loren will hear your words.
Your presence poisons Athel Loren!
There shall be no mercy for you, Greenskin!
Your presence here, disturbs the forest.
Well, Greenskin, speak.
I have no time for your kind.
Creatures of destruction, what do you seek?
Your soul will feed the Dark Prince!
Your dark desires have rotted your heart!
Be gone, faithless sapling!
Don't test me, child.
The Deepwood has a long memory.
You are no longer part of the forest.
I will see you returned to the earth!
The witch-scent is upon you!
Your words are poison.
Your dark heart carries only dark tidings.
You know nothing of eternity.
What brings you here, mayfly?
Your words cannot move me, so why try?
Tell your Lady she shall have nought from me, Bretonnian!
Bretonnians, you think over much of yourselves.
So, the umgi are here… why?
Do you seek an end to these dark days, Bretonnian?
The Knights of Bretonnia, what would you have of me?
I care not for the whims of your Dark Gods, Northman!
How dare you attempt to taint me with your madness?!
What do your dark masters want from me?
Gather your chaos addled thoughts and speak.
Vassal of Chaos, why are you here?
The times are dark indeed when I must speak with the likes of you!
If you are not with me you are my enemy, kin or no!
By the Silver Tower, don't waste my time!
Speak then, the gods gave you a tongue, did they not?
I care little for empty words, it is vengeance I crave.
Have you come to pledge me your loyalty?
Together we are stronger, let our Clans be as one!
The history our peoples share is exactly that, history!
The fate of the Empire is in your hands, not mine!
What makes you think I'll help you, manling?
Yes, yes! Speak your flowery words and be gone from my halls!
In these dark times, we should stand together.
Men of the Empire, what brings you here?
I am revenge incarnate! Know this and weigh your words!
By my hammer! I should slay you where you stand!
Only true vengeance will make me happy! Is that what you offer?!
The Ironhammer weighs heavy in my grip. Speak your words…
I stand strong behind the Shield of Defiance. Speak.
Long have I fought and suffered for my people.
I am Belegar, True King of the Eight Peaks!
Step forth, true friend of the Angrund Clan!
What brings you before the Heir of Lunn?
I shall avenge the grudges bequeathed to me, Greenskin!
You shall pay for the suffering you have heaped upon my kin!
I do not treat with Greenskins!
Leave, while you still can!
I am forced to hear your words, Greenskin.
Speak, if you must, but make it quick.
I have nothing for the Undead. Leave, now!
Uzkular, I want nothing to do with your vile schemes!
Vampire… very well, speak your dark words and be gone.
